 \"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/#/schema/logo/image/\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/RecipeTinEats_logo_for_Knowledge_Graph_card.png\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/RecipeTinEats_logo_for_Knowledge_Graph_card.png\", \"width\": 2591, \"height\": 347, \"caption\": \"RecipeTin Eats\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/#/schema/logo/image/\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/RecipeTinEats\", \"http://instagram.com/recipe_tin\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/nagi-maehashi-9779648b\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/recipetin/\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/recipetineats\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/#/schema/person/1d495a057e0419b552333c8526d827a9\", \"name\": \"Nagi\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/#/schema/person/image/\", \"url\": \"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/400004f5258d5b43d30deed3aa6e9566?s=96&d=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.recipetineats.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fonce-coupled-recipe-tin-eats%2Fassets%2Fimages%2Favatar-guest-temp-cache-bust-duplicate.png&r=g\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/400004f5258d5b43d30deed3aa6e9566?s=96&d=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.recipetineats.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fonce-coupled-recipe-tin-eats%2Fassets%2Fimages%2Favatar-guest-temp-cache-bust-duplicate.png&r=g\", \"caption\": \"Nagi\"}, \"description\": \"I believe you can make great food with everyday ingredients even if you\\u2019re short on time and cost conscious. You just need to cook clever and get creative!\", \"sameAs\": [\"http://www.recipetineats.com/about-me/\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"name\": \"Beef Stroganoff\", \"author\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/#/schema/person/1d495a057e0419b552333c8526d827a9\"}, \"description\": \"RECIPE VIDEO ABOVE. Juicy strips of beef smothered in a sour cream mushroom gravy - a quick dinner everyone will love! KEY STEPS: Sear beef super quickly for maximum juiciness and use a large skillet (for quick sear + fast sauce reduction).\\u00a0Stroganoff calls for good beef but if you only have a budget cut, use this easy Chinese method to tenderise the beef (it&#x27;s called &quot;velveting&quot;). It&#x27;s life changing - and perfect for Stroganoff.\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-02-28T10:35:05+00:00\", \"image\": [\"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Beef-Stroganoff_2-1-1.jpg\", \"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Beef-Stroganoff_2-1-1.jpg?w=500&h=500&crop=1\", \"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Beef-Stroganoff_2-1-1.jpg?w=500&h=375&crop=1\", \"https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Beef-Stroganoff_2-1-1.jpg?w=480&h=270&crop=1\"], \"recipeYield\": [\"4\", \"4 - 5 people\"], \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT15M\", \"totalTime\": \"PT30M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"600 g / 1.2 lb   scotch fillet steak / boneless rib eye ((Note 1))\", \"2 tbsp vegetable oil (, divided)\", \"1  large onion ((or 2 small onions), sliced)\", \"300 g / 10 oz   mushrooms (, sliced (not too thin))\", \"40 g / 3 tbsp   butter\", \"2 tbsp flour ((Note 2))\", \"2 cups / 500 ml   beef broth (, preferably salt reduced)\", \"1 tbsp Dijon mustard\", \"150 ml / 2/3 cup   sour cream\", \"Salt and pepper\", \"250 - 300 g / 8 - 10 oz   pasta or egg noodles of choice ((Note 3))\", \"Chopped chives (, for garnish (optional))\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Use your fist (or rolling pin or mallet) to flatten the steaks to about 3/4cm / 1/3\\\" thick. Slice into 5mm / 1/5\\\" strips (cut long ones in half), discarding excess fat.\", \"name\": \"Use your fist (or rolling pin or mallet) to flatten the steaks to about 3/4cm / 1/3\\\" thick. Slice into 5mm / 1/5\\\" strips (cut long ones in half), discarding excess fat.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-0\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Sprinkle with a pinch of salt and pepper.\", \"name\": \"Sprinkle with a pinch of salt and pepper.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-1\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet over high heat. Scatter half the beef in the skillet, QUICKLY spread it with tongs. Leave untouched for 30 seconds until browned. Turn beef quickly (as best you can!). Leave untouched for 30 seconds to brown. Immediately remove onto a plate. Don't worry about pink bits and that it will be raw inside.\", \"name\": \"Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet over high heat. Scatter half the beef in the skillet, QUICKLY spread it with tongs. Leave untouched for 30 seconds until browned. Turn beef quickly (as best you can!). Leave untouched for 30 seconds to brown. Immediately remove onto a plate. Don't worry about pink bits and that it will be raw inside.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-2\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add remaining 1 tbsp oil and repeat with remaining beef.\", \"name\": \"Add remaining 1 tbsp oil and repeat with remaining beef.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-3\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Turn heat down to medium high. Add butter, melt. Then add onions, cook for 1 minute, then add mushrooms.\", \"name\": \"Turn heat down to medium high. Add butter, melt. Then add onions, cook for 1 minute, then add mushrooms.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-4\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Cook mushrooms until golden. Scrape bottom of fry pan to get all the golden bits off (this is flavour!).\", \"name\": \"Cook mushrooms until golden. Scrape bottom of fry pan to get all the golden bits off (this is flavour!).\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-5\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add flour, cook, stirring, for 1 minute.\", \"name\": \"Add flour, cook, stirring, for 1 minute.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-6\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add half the broth while stirring. Once incorporated, add remaining broth.\", \"name\": \"Add half the broth while stirring. Once incorporated, add remaining broth.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-7\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Stir, then add sour cream and mustard. Stir until incorporated (don't worry if it looks split, sour cream will \\\"melt\\\" as it heats).\", \"name\": \"Stir, then add sour cream and mustard. Stir until incorporated (don't worry if it looks split, sour cream will \\\"melt\\\" as it heats).\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-8\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bring to simmer ,then reduce heat to medium low. Once it thickens to the consistency of pouring cream (3 - 5 minutes), adjust salt and pepper to taste.\", \"name\": \"Bring to simmer ,then reduce heat to medium low. Once it thickens to the consistency of pouring cream (3 - 5 minutes), adjust salt and pepper to taste.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-9\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add beef back in (including plate juices). Simmer for 1 minute, then remove from stove immediately. (Note 4)\", \"name\": \"Add beef back in (including plate juices). Simmer for 1 minute, then remove from stove immediately. (Note 4)\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-10\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Serve over pasta or egg noodles, sprinkled with chives if desired.\", \"name\": \"Serve over pasta or egg noodles, sprinkled with chives if desired.\", \"url\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#wprm-recipe-27097-step-0-11\"}], \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.94\", \"ratingCount\": \"413\"}, \"recipeCategory\": [\"Main\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"Russian\", \"Western\"], \"keywords\": \"Beef Stroganoff, Beef Stroganoff recipe\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"servingSize\": \"243 g\", \"calories\": \"586 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"9 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"37 g\", \"fatContent\": \"44 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"24 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"125 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"449 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"1 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"3 g\"}, \"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://www.recipetineats.com/beef-stroganoff/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Stuffed Cabbage Rolls", "yields": "5 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT25M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT2H20M"}, "ingredients": ["2 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil", "1/2 large onion, chopped", "3 cloves garlic, minced", "2 tbsp. tomato paste", "1 (28-oz.) can crushed tomatoes", "2 tbsp. balsamic vinegar", "1 tbsp. brown sugar", "2 tsp. dried oregano", "Kosher salt", "Freshly ground black pepper", "15 cabbage leaves", "1 lb. ground beef", "1/4 c. uncooked white rice", "1/4 c. Italian bread crumbs", "1/2 large onion, chopped", "2 tbsp. freshly chopped parsley, plus more for garnish", "Kosher salt", "Freshly ground black pepper"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "For the sauce", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat oven to 350°. In a large deep skillet (or large pot) over medium heat, heat oil. Add onion and cook until soft, 5 minutes. Stir in tomato paste and garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Pour over tomatoes then add vinegar, sugar, and oregano.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Lower heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper."}]}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "For the rolls", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large pot of boiling water, blanch cabbage leaves until tender and flexible, about 1 minute."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Make filling: In a large bowl, combine ground meats, 1 cup sauce, rice, bread crumbs, onion, and parsley. Season with salt and pepper."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Spread a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of a large baking dish.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Using a paring knife, cut out the hard triangular rib from each cabbage leaf. Place about ⅓ cup filling into one end of each leaf, then roll up, tucking in the sides as you roll. Place rolls seam side-down on top of sauce in baking dish. Spoon remaining sauce on top of cabbage rolls then cover dish with foil. Bake 1 hour 15 minutes, until rice and meat are cooked through.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Garnish with more parsley before serving."}]}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.0637xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2018-10-03T12:29:40.965148Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Stuffed Cabbage Rolls\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.0637xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.0637xw,0&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.0637xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.8888043133523629xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.0637xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-cabbage-rolls-horizontal-2-1538569228.jpg?crop=1xw:0.8438302883242934xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a23481075/stuffed-cabbage-rolls/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"htt