andkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#primaryimage\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#primaryimage\"}, \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1.jpg\", \"datePublished\": \"2012-09-28T15:05:03+00:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-02-22T20:47:44+00:00\", \"description\": \"Hearty vegetarian chili made with butternut squash and black beans. This chili satisfies carnivores, vegans and gluten-free eaters alike. Everyone loves it!\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"ReadAction\", \"target\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/\"]}]}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#primaryimage\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1.jpg\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1.jpg\", \"width\": 1100, \"height\": 1643, \"caption\": \"butternut squash chipotle chili recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"WebSite\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#website\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\", \"description\": \"Whole Foods and Vegetarian Recipe Blog\", \"publisher\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#organization\"}, \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"SearchAction\", \"target\": {\"@type\": \"EntryPoint\", \"urlTemplate\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/?s={search_term_string}\"}, \"query-input\": \"required name=search_term_string\"}], \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\"}, {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#organization\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/logo/image/\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2023/06/header-google-resized.png\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2023/06/header-google-resized.png\", \"width\": 696, \"height\": 696, \"caption\": \"Cookie and Kate\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/logo/image/\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://twitter.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://instagram.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kathryne-taylor-20012213/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/cookieandkate/\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/cookieandkate/\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/person/c609c24a34a1976d0a3c1a1b0cd7f46a\", \"name\": \"Kate\", \"description\": \"Vegetable enthusiast. Dog lover. I'm probably making a big mess in my Kansas City kitchen right now. More about me \\u00bb\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com\"]}, {\"@context\": \"https://schema.org/\", \"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"name\": \"Vegetarian Butternut Squash Chipotle Chili with Avocado\", \"description\": \"Hearty, spicy and sweet vegetarian chili made with butternut squash and black beans. Top with creamy avocado for an easy meal that satisfies vegans, carnivores and gluten-free eaters alike. This recipes serves 3 to 4. This chili is very hearty, but feel free to add another can of tomatoes or more vegetable broth if you want to thin it out a bit. Double the recipe for a crowd.\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\"}, \"keywords\": \"butternut squash chili, vegan chili, game days\", \"image\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1-225x225.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1-260x195.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1-320x180.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2012/09/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-recipe-0-1.jpg\"], \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"2 tablespoons olive oil\", \"1 medium red onion, chopped\", \"2 red bell peppers, chopped\", \"1 small butternut squash (1 1/2 pounds or less), peeled and chopped into 1/2-inch cubes\", \"4 garlic cloves, pressed or minced\", \"1 tablespoon chili powder\", \"1/2+ tablespoon chopped chipotle pepper in adobo* (start with 1/2 tablespoon and add more to taste, I thought mine was just right with 1 tablespoon)\", \"1 teaspoon ground cumin\", \"1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\", \"1 bay leaf\", \"2 cans (15 ounces each) black beans, rinsed and drained, or 3 cups cooked black beans\", \"1 small can (14 ounces) diced tomatoes, including the liquid**\", \"2 cups vegetable broth (or one 14-ounce can)\", \"Salt, to taste\", \"2 Avocados from Mexico, diced\", \"3 corn tortillas for crispy tortilla strips (or substitute crumbled tortilla chips)\", \"Optional additional garnishes: Chopped fresh cilantro and/or red pepper flakes\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a 4- to 6-quart Dutch oven or stockpot over medium heat, warm the olive oil until shimmering. Add the onion, bell pepper and butternut squash and cook, stirring occasionally, until the onions are turning translucent.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#instruction-step-1\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Turn the heat down to medium-low and add the garlic, chili powder, 1/2 tablespoon chopped chipotle peppers, cumin and cinnamon. Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add the bay leaf, black beans, tomatoes and their juices and broth. Stir to combine and cover for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Taste about halfway through cooking and add more chopped chipotle peppers if you&#8217;d like.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#instruction-step-2\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"You\\u2019ll know your chili is done when the butternut squash is nice and tender and the liquid has reduced a bit, producing the hearty chili consistency we all know and love. Remove the bay leaf and add salt to taste.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#instruction-step-3\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"To make the crispy tortilla strips: stack the corn tortillas and slice them into thin little strips, about 2 inches long by 1/4 inch wide. Warm a drizzle of olive oil in a medium pan over medium heat until shimmering. Toss in the tortilla slices, sprinkle with salt and stir. Cook until the strips are crispy and turning golden, stirring occasionally, about 4 to 7 minutes. Remove tortilla strips from skillet and drain on a plate covered with a piece of paper towel.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#instruction-step-4\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Serve the chili in individual bowls, topped with crispy tortilla strips and plenty of diced avocado. I added a little sprinkle of red pepper flakes (optional). Cilantro would be nice as well. You might want to serve this along with some chipotle hot sauce (Tobasco makes one) for the spice addicts like myself.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#instruction-step-5\"}], \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT1H\", \"totalTime\": \"PT1H20M\", \"recipeYield\": \"4\", \"recipeCategory\": \"Main\", \"cookingMethod\": \"Stovetop\", \"recipeCuisine\": \"American\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"reviewCount\": \"231\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.9\"}, \"nutrition\": {\"servingSize\": \"One bowl with crispy tortilla strips\", \"calories\": \"591 calories\", \"sugarContent\": \"12.5 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1069.4 mg\", \"fatContent\": \"23.9 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"3.5 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0 g\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"84 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"29.8 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"20.3 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"0 mg\", \"@type\": \"nutritionInformation\"}, \"video\": {\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"name\": \"Butternut Squash Chipotle Chili with Avocado\", \"description\": \"Watch how to make butternut squash chipotle chili with avocado in this short recipe video. Hearty, spicy and sweet vegetarian chili made with butternut squash and black beans. \", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/wDaDb7TF.mp4\", \"thumbnailUrl\": [\"https://content.jwplatform.com/thumbs/wDaDb7TF-720.jpg\"], \"uploadDate\": \"2023-02-22T20:36:05+00:00\"}, \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Wendy Rasmussen\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-02-29\", \"reviewBody\": \"Soooo yummy!! One of my new favorites, for sure.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jessi\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-01\", \"reviewBody\": \"I made this for about 12 friends for a party at my place last night and it was a huge hit! I quadrupled the recipe and played around with the spices a little bit (always more garlic!) but I'm so pleased with how it turned out. We sprinkled some shredded cheddar to the final product and what a masterpiece!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rob clements\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-07\", \"reviewBody\": \"Made this last night. WOW, tasted amazing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Debi Petersen\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-14\", \"reviewBody\": \"Can you freeze the butternut chili?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kavita\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-31\", \"reviewBody\": \"Hi Kate, would it work if I used sweet potato in place of the butternut squash? I don't have any squash in my kitchen right now! Thanks! \\r\\n\\r\\nP.S. I've made this recipe before (from your cookbook) and loved it so much!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sarah\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-04-06\", \"reviewBody\": \"Made this for dinner tonight with a few changes to accommodate ingredients on hand. It was absolutely fabulous! Will definitely make again! I did find that we needed more beans because I like lots of beans.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MJ\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-04-13\", \"reviewBody\": \"By far the most flavorful chili recipe I've made to date. Love the addition of cinnamon. I never would have though to add taht, but it complemented the flavors amazingly well! 1 tbsp of the peppers added just enough heat without overpowering the flavor. I might try a touch more next time as I like things with a little extra kick.\\r\\n\\r\\nAny thoughts on carrots or zucchini for those who want a little extra vegetable matter in their meals?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ashley\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-04-13\", \"reviewBody\": \"Is it possible to use frozen sweet potatoes (it has added brown sugar) and maybe some extra green peppers instead of the butternut squash? The pre-chopped fresh squash I bought went bad very quickly.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jolene\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-05-06\", \"reviewBody\": \"Hi Kate. I've been following your blog for a while now and love your recipes. Your sweet potato black bean enchiladas are fantastic; the Thai red curry, delicious; and the super veggie fried rice, super! I needed to cook a butternut that had been sitting in my kitchen for weeks, and I couldn't think of anything interesting to make until I chanced upon this chili recipe. I didn't have chipotle pepper or chili powder, so I used what I had: 1 teaspoon of smoky chipotle paste and 1/2 teaspoon of cayenne pepper (blasphemy, I know!). It certainly doesn't taste anything like yours, but it turned out delicious!! It's one of the most flavourful chilis I've ever eaten. We ate it with white rice, and it went down a treat. Thank you for these amazing recipes. You make me enjoy cooking veggie food \"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Do No\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-05-18\", \"reviewBody\": \"One of the best chilis that I've ever had. My husband agreed.  The ONLY \\\"change\\\" that I made was to top it with shredded jack cheese.  So good!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jenni\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-07-28\", \"reviewBody\": \"This is hands down the best chili I've EVER eaten. I used crushed tomatoes instead of diced (my hubby doesn't like chunks of tomatoes) and MOST IMPORTANTLY I made my black beans from Kate's 'from scratch black bean' recipe on this site. I doubt I will ever buy canned black beans again. I added dried oregano and thyme (just because why not) and diced avocado and shredded cheese to the finished product.  Subbed trisquit crackers in place of the tortilla chips for added whole grain goodness.  I wish I had doubled the recipe to freeze, but here in NY winter will come too soon and I plan to make this again and again. Thanks Kate!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jan\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-08-12\", \"reviewBody\": \"So grateful for your recipe!! Loved the combination of flavors! Just made this with a 4lb squash that\\u2019s been sitting on my counter for weeks, that our local farm delivered! I wanted something besides soup as it\\u2019s too hot &amp; they also brought 2avocados Housebound limits my options I had grain free Cassava chips I was saving so this was a real treat! I used smoked paprika &amp; Chipolte powder instead of Chipolte in adobo sauce.  I gave it a 10+ hubby had seconds &amp; he\\u2019s not vegetarian! Thx\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Honey\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-09-04\", \"reviewBody\": \"Made this chili today. Love it!  I really like heat, so I upped the Adobe sauce a little, as well as the chili powder. Did mash it a good bit at the end to thicken it. I put a dollop of plain no fat Greek yogurt, some fat free cheddar cheese, and a generous squeeze of lime on my bowl right before I ate it. Chili heaven! I like the tortilla strips(have made them for another recipe)but I was lazy. Next time I will do them. \\r\\nThanks for your blog and your cookbook!! I\\u2019m a huge fan!\\r\\n\\r\\nHoney\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Samantha\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-09-11\", \"reviewBody\": \"Thanks for this recipe, so delicious and healthy! I usually eat plant based meals, and I looove how the squash gave the same heartiness to the chili that meat normally provides. To top it off, the cinnamon and chipotle flavors were so fallish and such a good complement. Can't wait to make this one again :)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kate\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-09-12\", \"reviewBody\": \"Making this again tomorrow, it\\u2019s so satisfying and delicious.  I tell all of my friends to check out the site and cookbook.  Love your soups!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jen D\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-09-14\", \"reviewBody\": \"Great rich, smoky flavor! Do you have the base calorie info, without the tortilla strips? Is the avocado included in your calculation? \\r\\n\\r\\nThanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"kiley\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-09-28\", \"reviewBody\": \"LOVE this chili, this is my third time making it and my favorite chili recipe I have ever made. Definitely a keeper!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lauri\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-10-06\", \"reviewBody\": \"My family loves this chili!  I make it regularly, as I do with many of your delicious recipes.  \"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kim\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-10-19\", \"reviewBody\": \"This is our absolutely favorite chili recipe. Even my meat eating husband loves it! So great to have a vegan recipe that everyone enjoys. It\\u2019s the best!!! I think the chipotle in adobo sauce and the cinnamon are key ingredients.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Peter\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2020-10-24\", \"reviewBody\": \"what do you think about roasting the Butternut squash (as in your other recipe), and add once the Bell peppers are almost done?\"}], \"datePublished\": \"2012-09-28\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/butternut-squash-chipotle-chili-with-avocado/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Best Bolognese", "yields": "4 servings", "time": {"prep": 0, "cook": 0, "total": 0}, "ingredients": ["1 medium onion, chopped", "1 celery stalk, chopped", "1 small carrot, peeled, chopped", "3 Tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil", "1 lb. ground beef chuck (20% fat), patted dry", "Kosher salt", "3 oz. thinly sliced pancetta, finely chopped", "1 cup dry white wine", "⅓ cup tomato paste", "1 bay leaf", "Pinch of finely grated nutmeg", "2 cups (or more) homemade chicken stock or low-sodium chicken broth", "1 cup whole milk", "1 lb. fresh tagliatelle or pappardelle, or dry rigatoni", "2 oz. finely grated Parmesan (about ½ cup), plus more for serving"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Pulse onion, celery, and carrot in a food processor until very finely chopped. Transfer to a small bowl."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat oil in a Dutch oven or other large pot over medium. Break beef into small clumps (about 1½\") and add to pot; season lightly with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally but not breaking meat apart, until beef is lightly browned but not crisp, 6–8 minutes. It may be gray in spots (that’s okay!) and still a little pink in the center. Using a slotted spoon, transfer beef to a medium bowl."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Wipe out pot. Cook pancetta in pot over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until pancetta has released some of its fat and is crisp, 6–8 minutes. Add onion mixture to pot and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are very soft and beginning to stick to surface, 6–8 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Return beef to pot and pour in wine. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, smashing down on beef with a wooden spoon, until wine is evaporated, surface of pot is almost dry, and meat is finely ground, 12–15 minutes. (The meat should be reduced to what looks like little bits. It takes a bit of effort, but you can take breaks.) Add tomato paste, bay leaf, and nutmeg and cook, stirring occasionally and still pressing down on meat, until tomato paste is slightly darkened, about 5 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Pour stock and milk into pot; add a pinch of salt. Reduce heat to the lowest setting and cook, uncovered and stirring occasionally, until meat is very, very tender, 2–2½  hours. There shouldn’t be any rapid bubbles at this stage. Instead, the sauce should release the occasional small bubble or two. When finished, the sauce should have the texture of and look like a sloppy joe mixture. If the liquid reduces before the meat is completely tender, add an extra ½ cup stock and continue cooking. Discard bay leaf. Taste sauce and adjust seasoning with salt; keep warm."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water. If using fresh pasta, cook about 3 minutes. If using dry, cook until very al dente, about 2 minutes less than package directions."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Using tongs, transfer pasta to pot with sauce. Add 1 cup pasta cooking liquid and ½ cup Parmesan. Increase heat to medium, bring to a simmer, and cook, tossing constantly, until pasta is al dente and liquid is slightly thickened, about 2 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Transfer pasta to a platter and top with more Parmesan.\nDo Ahead: Sauce can be made 4 days ahead. Cover and chill."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"articleBody\": \"It doesn\\u2019t take a lot of ingredients (or a lot of money) to make a classic Bolognese recipe. What it does take, though, is patience for the sauce to achieve the ideal authentic texture. You\\u2019re going to go low and slow\\u2014it\\u2019ll take around 3 hours, but most of that cook time is hands-off.\", \"alternativeHeadline\": \"It doesn\\u2019t take a lot of ingredients (or a lot of money) to make a classic Bolognese recipe. What it does take, though, is patience for the sauce to achieve the ideal authentic texture. You\\u2019re going to go low and slow\\u2014it\\u2019ll take around 3 hours, but most of that cook time is hands-off.\", \"keywords\": [\"pasta\", \"italian\", \"ground beef\", \"pancetta\", \"tagliatelle\", \"pappardelle\", \"rigatoni\", \"main\", \"nut-free\", \"simmer\", \"dinner\", \"web\"], \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5c2f8fe26558e92c8a622671/1:1/w_2700,h_2700,c_limit/bolognese-1.jpg\", \"publisher\": {\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Bon App\\u00e9tit\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.bonappetit.com/verso/static/bon-appetit/assets/logo-seo.png\", \"width\": \"479px\", \"height\": \"100px\"}, \"url\": \"https://www.bonappetit.com\"}, \"isPartOf\": {\"@type\": \"CreativeWork\", \"name\": \"Bon App\\u00e9tit\"}, \"isAccessibleForFree\": true, \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Andy Baraghani\", \"sameAs\": \"https://www.bonappetit.com/contributor/andy-baraghani\"}], \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.7, \"ratingCount\": 524}, \"description\": \"It doesn\\u2019t take a lot of ingredients (or a lot of money) to make a classic Bolognese recipe. What it does take, though, is patience for the sauce to achieve the ideal authentic texture. You\\u2019re going to go low and slow\\u2014it\\u2019ll take around 3 hours, but most of that cook time is hands-off.\", \"image\": [\"https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5c2f8fe26558e92c8a622671/16:9/w_4800,h_2700,c_limit/bolognese-1.jpg\", \"https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5c2f8fe26558e92c8a622671/4:3/w_3600,h_2700,c_limit/bolognese-1.jpg\", \"https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5c2f8fe26558e92c8a622671/1:1/w_2700,h_2700,c_limit/bolognese-1.jpg\"], \"headline\": \"Best Bolognese\", \"name\": \"Best Bolognese\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 medium onion, chopped\", \"1 celery stalk, chopped\", \"1 small carrot, peeled, chopped\", \"3 Tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil\", \"1 lb. ground beef chuck (20% fat), patted dry\", \"Kosher salt\", \"3 oz. thinly sliced pancetta, finely chopped\", \"1 cup dry white wine\", \"\\u2153 cup tomato paste\", \"1 bay leaf\", \"Pinch of finely grated nutmeg\", \"2 cups (or more) homemade chicken stock or low-sodium chicken broth\", \"1 cup whole milk\", \"1 lb. fresh tagliatelle or pappardelle, or dry rigatoni\", \"2 oz. finely grated Parmesan (about \\u00bd cup), plus more for serving\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Pulse onion, celery, and carrot in a food processor until very finely chopped. Transfer to a small bowl.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat oil in a Dutch oven or other large pot over medium. Break beef into small clumps (about 1\\u00bd\\\") and add to pot; season lightly with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally but not breaking meat apart, until beef is lightly browned but not crisp, 6\\u20138 minutes. It may be gray in spots (that\\u2019s okay!) and still a little pink in the center. Using a slotted spoon, transfer beef to a medium bowl.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Wipe out pot. Cook pancetta in pot over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until pancetta has released some of its fat and is crisp, 6\\u20138 minutes. Add onion mixture to pot and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are very soft and beginning to stick to surface, 6\\u20138 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Return beef to pot and pour in wine. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, smashing down on beef with a wooden spoon, until wine is evaporated, surface of pot is almost dry, and meat is finely ground, 12\\u201315 minutes. (The meat should be reduced to what looks like little bits. It takes a bit of effort, but you can take breaks.) Add tomato paste, bay leaf, and nutmeg and cook, stirring occasionally and still pressing down on meat, until tomato paste is slightly darkened, about 5 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Pour stock and milk into pot; add a pinch of salt. Reduce heat to the lowest setting and cook, uncovered and stirring occasionally, until meat is very, very tender, 2\\u20132\\u00bd  hours. There shouldn\\u2019t be any rapid bubbles at this stage. Instead, the sauce should release the occasional small bubble or two. When finished, the sauce should have the texture of and look like a sloppy joe mixture. If the liquid reduces before the meat is completely tender, add an extra \\u00bd cup stock and continue cooking. Discard bay leaf. Taste sauce and adjust seasoning with salt; keep warm.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water. If using fresh pasta, cook about 3 minutes. If using dry, cook until very al dente, about 2 minutes less than package directions.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Using tongs, transfer pasta to pot with sauce. Add 1 cup pasta cooking liquid and \\u00bd cup Parmesan. Increase heat to medium, bring to a simmer, and cook, tossing constantly, until pasta is al dente and liquid is slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Transfer pasta to a platter and top with more Parmesan.\\nDo Ahead: Sauce can be made 4 days ahead. Cover and chill.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"4 servings\", \"url\": \"https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/bas-best-bolognese\", \"dateModified\": \"2019-01-07T06:00:00.000-05:00\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-01-07T06:00:00.000-05:00\"}"}
