oms-and-fresh-oregano/#primaryimage\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#primaryimage\"}, \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe.jpg\", \"datePublished\": \"2014-11-07T14:39:08+00:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-03-03T21:00:17+00:00\", \"description\": \"Creamy baked brown rice risotto with minimal stirring required! Brown rice risotto is healthier and so delicious. Feel free to change up the flavors!\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"ReadAction\", \"target\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/\"]}]}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#primaryimage\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe.jpg\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe.jpg\", \"width\": 1100, \"height\": 1643, \"caption\": \"Easy Brown Rice Risotto with Mushrooms and Fresh Oregano\"}, {\"@type\": \"WebSite\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#website\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\", \"description\": \"Whole Foods and Vegetarian Recipe Blog\", \"publisher\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#organization\"}, \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"SearchAction\", \"target\": {\"@type\": \"EntryPoint\", \"urlTemplate\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/?s={search_term_string}\"}, \"query-input\": \"required name=search_term_string\"}], \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\"}, {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#organization\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/logo/image/\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2023/06/header-google-resized.png\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2023/06/header-google-resized.png\", \"width\": 696, \"height\": 696, \"caption\": \"Cookie and Kate\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/logo/image/\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://twitter.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://instagram.com/cookieandkate\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kathryne-taylor-20012213/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/cookieandkate/\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/cookieandkate/\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/#/schema/person/c609c24a34a1976d0a3c1a1b0cd7f46a\", \"name\": \"Kate\", \"description\": \"Vegetable enthusiast. Dog lover. I'm probably making a big mess in my Kansas City kitchen right now. More about me \\u00bb\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com\"]}, {\"@context\": \"https://schema.org/\", \"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"name\": \"Easy Brown Rice Risotto with Mushrooms and Fresh Oregano\", \"description\": \"Creamy, delicious, healthier baked brown rice risotto with minimal stirring required! This recipe is designed for brown arborio/short grain brown rice so any grain substitutions will affect baking time. (White arborio rice will only need to be baked for 40 to 45 minutes.) Look for brown arborio/short-grain brown rice at well-stocked grocery stores or health food stores. Skip the wine if you don't drink, but it adds a lovely depth of flavor. Recipe yields 4 to 6 servings.\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cookie and Kate\"}, \"keywords\": \"brown rice risotto\", \"image\": [\"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe-225x225.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe-260x195.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe-320x180.jpg\", \"https://cookieandkate.com/images/2018/08/easy-brown-rice-risotto-recipe.jpg\"], \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"3 tablespoons olive oil, divided\", \"1 small yellow onion, chopped\", \"2 cloves garlic, pressed or minced\", \"5 cups (40 ounces) vegetable broth, divided (if your broth comes in 32-ounce containers, feel free to avoid opening another container by substituting 1 cup water for 1 cup broth in step 3)\", \"1 1/2 cups brown arborio/short-grain brown rice\", \"12 to 14 ounces sliced Cremini (baby portobello) mushrooms, debris rinsed from mushrooms and drained\", \"1 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese\", \"1/2 cup dry white wine, optional\", \"3 tablespoons unsalted butter, diced\", \"2 teaspoons tamari (for extra flavor, optional)*\", \"1 teaspoon sea salt, more to taste\", \"Freshly ground black pepper, to taste\", \"4 sprigs fresh oregano, leaves removed from stems and larger leaves torn into small pieces\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Make sure your oven rack is in the middle position. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#instruction-step-1\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a medium Dutch oven over medium heat until shimmering. Add onion and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for ten minutes, then add the minced garlic. Cook for another 2 to 4 minutes, until the onions are well browned.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#instruction-step-2\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add 4 cups broth (or 3 cups broth and 1 cup water), cover, and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Remove from heat and stir in the rice. Cover the pot and bake until rice is tender and cooked through, about 65 to 70 minutes. It will seem pretty dry when you take off the lid, but don&#8217;t worry!\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#instruction-step-3\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"During the last 20 minutes of baking time, prepare the mushrooms. Warm 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet until shimmering. Add the cleaned, sliced mushrooms to the pot with a dash of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms are darker in color, fragrant and have soaked up most of their own juices, about 13 minutes.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#instruction-step-4\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Remove the pot from the oven. Pour in the remaining cup of broth, the Parmesan, wine, butter, tamari, salt, and a generous amount of pepper. Stir vigorously for 2 to 3 minutes, until the rice is thick and creamy. Stir in the mushroom mixture and any remaining juices. Season to taste with salt and pepper, divide into bowls and top with a generous sprinkling of torn, fresh oregano leaves.\", \"url\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#instruction-step-5\"}], \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT1H\", \"totalTime\": \"PT1H20M\", \"recipeYield\": [\"4\", \"4 to 6 servings\"], \"recipeCategory\": \"Main\", \"cookingMethod\": \"Baked\", \"recipeCuisine\": \"Italian\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"reviewCount\": \"171\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.9\"}, \"nutrition\": {\"servingSize\": null, \"calories\": \"387 calories\", \"sugarContent\": \"4 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1319.7 mg\", \"fatContent\": \"21.2 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"8.8 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0.1 g\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"41.6 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"3.7 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"13.1 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"34.4 mg\", \"@type\": \"nutritionInformation\"}, \"video\": {\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"name\": \"Easy Brown Rice Risotto with Mushrooms and Fresh Oregano\", \"description\": \"Watch how to make easy brown rice risotto with mushrooms in this short recipe video. Creamy, delicious, healthier baked brown rice risotto with minimal stirring required! \", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/lIMl95wj.mp4\", \"thumbnailUrl\": [\"https://content.jwplatform.com/thumbs/lIMl95wj-720.jpg\"], \"uploadDate\": \"2023-03-03T20:50:18+00:00\"}, \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"rach\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-07-30\", \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this recipe, thanks so much.. have a veggie hating kidult so tend to hide things (mushrooms, onion and celery) in risotto by blending... so that's what i did and then used silver beet sauteed in garlic and olive oil on the top (as all the other texture veg were hidden) and veggie hater had some of the silver beet raw on the side of his plate...  i just love the fact that this recipe was so good. Used red wine too .. veggie hater knows there's sneaky stuff in there but just doesn't want to have to eat chunks of it. No pinenuts so used flaked almonds and also swapped fresh oregano for basil (as that and the silverbeet (chard) come from my container garden.   This is a keeper !!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nicole Hughes\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-08-08\", \"reviewBody\": \"I just made this and OMGgggg I can\\u2019t wait to eat it! Just took a bite and it is soooo good!! Used par boiled brown rice (maybe it was 75% already cooked) and it was only 20 min needed in the oven. Delicious!!!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cari\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-08-24\", \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe has changed my risotto game! Absolutely spot on that the brown rice gives it a nuttiness and a new depth that was unanticipated. This was truly a hug in a bowl and was so simple. This is going to be on repeat from now on. While the locally foraged chanterelles were what I thought would be the star of the dinner, my husband said that it was truly this risotto.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Joanne D\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-09-11\", \"reviewBody\": \"Love this easy bake and delicious recipe. I have made it several times. If i double the recipe does the cook time stay the same? has anyone tried that?\\r\\nthanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nancy\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-09-12\", \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe - doubled it for a crowd and everyone came back for seconds! I also added a squeeze of lemon juice for a touch of acidity. Thank you for creating this delishnous!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Meinrad from Canada\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-09-30\", \"reviewBody\": \"Hi Kate (and Cookie),\\r\\nI was sceptical about a brown rice risotto recipe, but my wife's new dietary restrictions dictate that I abandon my traditional arborio rice risotto recipe.  I can report that your recipe was a hit: with me, with my wife, and with my stepson. I will try other recipes of yours, but I thought you would like to hear my full-throated praise for this particular one.\\r\\nBest regards,\\r\\nMeinrad from Canada\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ML\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-10-02\", \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is a keeper!  I loved it.  Makes alot, so next time I think I will invite friends over.\\r\\n\\r\\nUsed sushi rice (simply because that is what I had).  Had to reduce the baking time (thank you for the timing notes), but it was still awesome.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Shell\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-11-21\", \"reviewBody\": \"I'm making this wonderful recipe for Thanksgiving, but all I can find is short grain brown rice. Online sources are telling me traditional arborio rice absorbs liquid differently than short grain rice. Has that been your experience? Would you recommend arborio over short grain? If so, where do you find it?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sara Corson\"}, \"datePublished\": \"2023-11-29\", \"reviewBody\": \"Is this possible with a brown basmati rice?\"}], \"datePublished\": \"2014-11-07\", \"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://cookieandkate.com/easy-brown-rice-risotto-with-mushrooms-and-fresh-oregano/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Keto Beef Stroganoff", "yields": "4 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT10M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT10M"}, "ingredients": ["3 tbsp. butter, divided", "1 lb. 80% lean ground beef", "Kosher salt", "Freshly ground black pepper", "1 1/2 lb. mushrooms, sliced&nbsp;", "1 garlic clove, minced", "1 c. low-sodium beef stock or bone broth", "4 oz. cream cheese", "1/2 c. sour cream", "2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce", "2 tsp. Dijon mustard", "1/2 tsp. paprika", "Finely chopped parsley, for garnish", "steamed&nbsp;cauliflower rice, for serving&nbsp;"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat a large skillet over medium-high and melt&nbsp;1 tablespoon of butter. Add ground beef and season with salt and pepper. Cook beef, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, about 10 minutes. Transfer meat to a plate."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Return skillet to medium-high heat and add remaining butter and mushrooms. Cook, tossing occasionally, until mushrooms are golden, about 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and add garlic. Cook until fragrant, 1 minute.&nbsp;Add broth, cream cheese, sour cream, Worcestershire, Dijon, and paprika to skillet. Bring to a simmer, stirring.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Return beef to skillet and stir to combine. Serve over cauliflower rice with garnish with parsley."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-202001-keto-beef-stroganoff-0130-landscape-pf-1583437740.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-05T21:43:53.445117Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Keto Beef Stroganoff\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-202001-keto-beef-stroganoff-0130-landscape-pf-1583437740.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del