, \"target\": {\"@type\": \"EntryPoint\", \"urlTemplate\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/?s={search_term_string}\"}, \"query-input\": \"required name=search_term_string\"}], \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\"}, {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/#organization\", \"name\": \"Live Eat Learn\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/#/schema/logo/image/\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/live_eat_learn_logo.jpg\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/live_eat_learn_logo.jpg\", \"width\": 600, \"height\": 221, \"caption\": \"Live Eat Learn\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/#/schema/logo/image/\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/liveeatlearn/\", \"https://twitter.com/liveeatlearn\", \"https://instagram.com/liveeatlearn/\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarahlorrainebond\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/live_eat_learn/\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/#/schema/person/41b184b76b12c4abd4f5e62b67620b36\", \"name\": \"Sarah Bond\", \"description\": \"A flavor-loving nutritionist and sensory science specialist showing you how to make easy vegetarian recipes, one ingredient at a time. Read more\\u2026\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/about/\", \"https://www.facebook.com/liveeatlearn/\", \"https://www.instagram.com/liveeatlearn/\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarahlorrainebond/\", \"http://pinterest.com/live_eat_learn/\", \"https://twitter.com/liveeatlearn\"], \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/about/\"}, {\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"name\": \"BBQ Pulled Mushrooms (Best Ever Vegan Pulled Pork!)\", \"author\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/#/schema/person/41b184b76b12c4abd4f5e62b67620b36\"}, \"description\": \"By shredding king oyster mushrooms, seasoning with spices, and baking, you can create a vegan mushroom pulled pork that rivals the real stuff!\", \"datePublished\": \"2018-07-10T11:15:38+00:00\", \"image\": [\"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bbq-pulled-mushrooms-vert.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bbq-pulled-mushrooms-vert-500x500.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bbq-pulled-mushrooms-vert-500x375.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bbq-pulled-mushrooms-vert-480x270.jpg\"], \"video\": {\"name\": \"BBQ Pulled Mushrooms (Vegan Pulled \\\"Pork\\\"!)\", \"description\": \"By shredding king oyster mushrooms, seasoning with spices, and baking, you can create a vegan mushroom pulled pork that rivals the real stuff! the perfect pulled pork alternative for sandwiches, tacos, nachos\\u2026or whenever you need pulled pork.\\n\\nGet the full recipe here: https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/\", \"uploadDate\": \"2019-02-23T16:14:46+00:00\", \"duration\": \"PT57S\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Y-g92CZfAZk/hqdefault.jpg\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y-g92CZfAZk?feature=oembed\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y-g92CZfAZk\", \"@type\": \"VideoObject\"}, \"recipeYield\": [\"3\", \"3 servings\"], \"prepTime\": \"PT5M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT25M\", \"totalTime\": \"PT30M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"4  king oyster mushrooms*\", \"2 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil (30 mL, divided)\", \"1 tsp smoked paprika\", \"\\u00bc tsp salt\", \"\\u00bc tsp cayenne pepper\", \"2 cloves garlic (minced)\", \"\\u00bc cup BBQ sauce (60 g)\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Shred Mushrooms: Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0F (204\\u00b0C). Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel. Using two forks, shred the stems and caps roughly into pieces. Set on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.\\u00a0\", \"name\": \"Shred Mushrooms: Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0F (204\\u00b0C). Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel. Using two forks, shred the stems and caps roughly into pieces. Set on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.\\u00a0\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/#wprm-recipe-16230-step-0-0\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bbq-pulled-mushrooms-1.jpg\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bake: Drizzle with 1 Tbsp of the oil, paprika, salt, cayenne, and garlic. Toss around to evenly coat the mushrooms, then bake for 20 minutes, or until mushrooms are a bit crispy and brown on the edges.\", \"name\": \"Bake: Drizzle with 1 Tbsp of the oil, paprika, salt, cayenne, and garlic. Toss around to evenly coat the mushrooms, then bake for 20 minutes, or until mushrooms are a bit crispy and brown on the edges.\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/#wprm-recipe-16230-step-0-1\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/step2-bbq-pulled-mushrooms-3.jpg\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Saut\\u00e9: Heat remaining 1 Tbsp oil in a large saute pan over medium high. Transfer cooked mushrooms to pan and add BBQ sauce. Stir and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until mixture is thick and fragrant.&nbsp;Serve warm on sandwiches, nachos, salads, tacos...or whenever you eat pulled pork!\", \"name\": \"Saut\\u00e9: Heat remaining 1 Tbsp oil in a large saute pan over medium high. Transfer cooked mushrooms to pan and add BBQ sauce. Stir and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until mixture is thick and fragrant.&nbsp;Serve warm on sandwiches, nachos, salads, tacos...or whenever you eat pulled pork!\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/#wprm-recipe-16230-step-0-2\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/step3-bbq-pulled-mushrooms-4.jpg\"}], \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.82\", \"ratingCount\": \"152\"}, \"recipeCategory\": [\"Main Dishes\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"suitableForDiet\": [\"https://schema.org/DiabeticDiet\", \"https://schema.org/GlutenFreeDiet\", \"https://schema.org/HalalDiet\", \"https://schema.org/HinduDiet\", \"https://schema.org/KosherDiet\", \"https://schema.org/LowCalorieDiet\", \"https://schema.org/LowFatDiet\", \"https://schema.org/LowLactoseDiet\", \"https://schema.org/VeganDiet\", \"https://schema.org/VegetarianDiet\"], \"keywords\": \"mushroom pulled pork, pulled mushrooms, vegan pulled pork, vegetarian pulled pork\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"163 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"15.4 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"0.3 g\", \"fatContent\": \"10.2 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"1.3 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"448 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"1.8 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"6.9 g\", \"servingSize\": \"1 serving\"}, \"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/mushroom-pulled-pork/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Lentil Bolognese", "yields": ["4"], "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT32M", "total": "PT52M"}, "ingredients": ["1 tablespoon olive oil, or to taste", "1 onion, finely chopped", "2 cloves garlic, crushed and finely chopped", "0.5 red bell pepper, thinly sliced", "1 carrot, cut into small cubes", "0.5 cup thinly sliced mushrooms", "0.5 cup red wine", "1 (14 ounce) can diced tomatoes", "1 cup vegetable broth", "1 (15 ounce) can green lentils, drained", "1 teaspoon ground paprika, or more to taste", "1 teaspoon dried basil, or more to taste", "1 teaspoon dried oregano, or more to taste", "1 teaspoon mixed dried herbs, or to taste", "1 pinch ground nutmeg"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Cook and stir onion and garlic until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in red bell pepper and carrot; cook for 4 to 5 minutes. Add mushrooms; cook and stir until softened, about 2 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/FveTR5egCQXhn0BLIVhuAnBPBPQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4573958-ac38ed49317b4c47a3d382800e0a8e39.jpg"}], "text": "Pour wine into the pot; simmer until slightly reduced, about 1 minute. Stir in diced tomatoes and vegetable broth. Bring sauce to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until flavors combine, 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in lentils, paprika, basil, oregano, dried herbs, and nutmeg; cook until lentils are heated through, about 5 minutes."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Lentil Bolognese\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-09T22:52:59.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2020-03-09T22:52:59.000-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sorchaspud\"}], \"description\": \"Lentils take the place of ground beef in this savory bolognese sauce made with red wine and mushrooms that&#39;s delicious served over pasta.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/FveTR5egCQXhn0BLIVhuAnBPBPQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4573958-ac38ed49317b4c47a3d382800e0a8e39.jpg\", \"height\": 1500, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/yk7o4njn-ma1DlVvV.mp4\", \"description\": \"Lentils, red wine, nutmeg, and tomatoes blend perfectly in this Bolognese rendition of a classic sauce. Wine and broth, with fresh herbs like basil and oregano pair beautifully with simmering onion, garlic, and mushrooms. Place sauce atop your favorite noodles and you\\u2019ll have a filling and delicious Italian-inspired meal.\", \"duration\": \"PT1M40S\", \"name\": \"Lentil Bolognese\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/yk7o4njn/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2020-12-03T09:57:40.058-05:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Lentil Bolognese\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.3\", \"ratingCount\": \"30\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT32M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"202 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"27 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"11 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"9 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"1 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"399 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"8 g\", \"fatContent\": \"4 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 tablespoon olive oil, or to taste\", \"1 onion, finely chopped\", \"2 cloves garlic, crushed and finely chopped\", \"0.5 red bell pepper, thinly sliced\", \"1 carrot, cut into small cubes\", \"0.5 cup thinly sliced mushrooms\", \"0.5 cup red wine\", \"1 (14 ounce) can diced tomatoes\", \"1 cup vegetable broth\", \"1 (15 ounce) can green lentils, drained\", \"1 teaspoon ground paprika, or more to taste\", \"1 teaspoon dried basil, or more to taste\", \"1 teaspoon dried oregano, or more to taste\", \"1 teaspoon mixed dried herbs, or to taste\", \"1 pinch ground nutmeg\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Cook and stir onion and garlic until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in red bell pepper and carrot; cook for 4 to 5 minutes. Add mushrooms; cook and stir until softened, about 2 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/FveTR5egCQXhn0BLIVhuAnBPBPQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4573958-ac38ed49317b4c47a3d382800e0a8e39.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Pour wine into the pot; simmer until slightly reduced, about 1 minute. Stir in diced tomatoes and vegetable broth. Bring sauce to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until flavors combine, 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in lentils, paprika, basil, oregano, dried herbs, and nutmeg; cook until lentils are heated through, about 5 minutes.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"4\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT52M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"RonGoings\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was excellent, made exactly as written. Made more food than I thought it would, easily could serve 6.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was so good and extremely easy to make and follow the recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BLUEGIRL5\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A wonderful recipe! Vegans and carnivores alike thought it was great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chrissie Lamos Pollock\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added chili powder for a nice kick. I also used red lentils and served over black bean noodles.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ginny\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"family loved it, so easy and healthy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Markdd\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Didn't have canned lentils. Made up a batch the day before. Managed to cut the pepper and carrot very small. Tastes good but , I'm still missing real meat sauce.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jacqui\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I thought this was very bland and not much sauce. I would not make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Seelerco\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Added more spices as it was rather bland and also slightly dry. Maybe more tomatoes or something juicy. Wouldn\\u2019t make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"AshB\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Dallas Morris\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'm not sure if I'll make this again, but if I do I'll be sure to use canned lentils (I made mine separately in a pressure cooker) and cut the peppers and carrots smaller. The flavor was fine, nothing special or WOW inducing. All the other amazing reviews make me think I should give it another shot.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Christie Crawford\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy dinner and loved by company. I cooked a sprouted lentil variety and used angel hair for the pasta.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Caroline\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I don\\u2019t often review recipes but in my 20 years of using Allrecipes this is one of my favorite recipes. This makes a perfect vegan bolognese. Even husband who is a meat eater had two bowls. It\\u2019s delicious and if you are watching sodium it has low sodium since you don\\u2019t add any salt! I used no salt added tomatoes and low sodium vegetable broth. Excellent recipe! Thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"szieg\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Good meatless option.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jamaican Jade\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very nice. It has great flavour and texture. Very similar to the beef version.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Judith Kelly\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I was having company for dinner and was serving spaghetti and meatballs. One of my guests is a vegetarian. I made this recipe as written for that guest, the day before my company since I felt the flavours would meld better after being reheated. As I taste tested it, there was something missing so I added about 3/4 of a tsp of salt in addition I added 2 or 3 tbsp of tomato paste as I wanted the bolognese to thicken up as I found it quite loose and watery. The bottom line was that my guest loved it. Since there were leftovers, the next day I added some italian sausage chunks, baby quartered potatoes and beef broth and made a lovely soup for dinner for my husband and myself.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"djwillie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I did not expect the flavor to be the same as a meat version, so I was pleased with this recipe. I added finely chopped celery because I can't imagine bolognese (even adapted for veggies) without it. I, too, added a pinch of hot pepper flakes. Since this makes more than I can eat, I am going to try and freeze some and see how that goes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Zehra Ali\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was quite tasty but a bit dryer than i expected, perhaps because of my noviceness. :/ \\ni used white vinegar instead of the wine because im muslim. \\nthere was no menion of salt so i used black salt, about a teaspoon.\\nOverall, its a wonderful recipe because all my relatives loved it, i would make it again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kaceygee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We enjoyed this with some modifications. I used beef broth in place of the wine and veggie broth. I also added a spoonful of basil pesto. Served over zucchini noodles, it was delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kathryn Tuckerman Little\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Chose because of lentils rather than beef; made as directed; didn\\u2019t have the flavor I\\u2019m accustomed to; will not make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"jean labreck\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"i made no changes. i followed the recipe to the tee and i'm glad i did. it was wonderful!!!! my family thanks you for a great meal, and i thank you for and easy and quick one. jean, mass.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Susie Rahe\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made it exactly as stated! AWESOME! Next time I will double the sauce so I can drink it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Connie Castner Deemer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I mixed the sauce with macaroni noodles. And added some crushed red peppers and Parmesan cheese. It was very good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Carol Milo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe. If you are not a strict vegan, you can top with Parmesan for an extra kick.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"PM\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I eliminated the mushrooms as I am the only one who likes them .. we are having it tonight .. however I made the Bolognese Friday evening and trust me its worth a do ahead if you are looking forward as the flavors were so much better. Great recipe....\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Buckwheat Queen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was excellent. It tastes just like rag\\u00f9 alla Bolognese is supposed to taste. I think the red wine and nutmeg are key. At first, the kids didn\\u2019t even notice there were lentils instead of meat. The only thing I will change next time is to omit the broth and simply use broth powder. The extra liquid made cooking time a bit long as it took a long time to reduce risking to over cook the lentils. Excellent recipe, thank you for sharing it with us.\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/256885/lentil-bolognese/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/496/side-dish/sauces-and-condiments/sauces/pasta-sauces/\", \"name\": \"Pasta Sauces\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/1200/side-dish/sauces-and-condiments/sauces/pasta-sauces/vegetarian/\", \"name\": \"Vegetarian\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/256885/lentil-bolognese/\", \"name\": \"Lentil Bolognese\"}}]}}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Keto Stuffed Cabbage", "yields": "1 dz.", "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT1H45M"}, "ingredients": ["1 (14-oz.) can diced tomatoes", "1 tbsp. apple cider vinegar", "1/2 tsp. red pepper flakes", "1 tsp. onion powder", "1 tsp. garlic powder", "1 tsp. dried oregano", "Kosher salt", "Freshly ground black pepper", "1/4 c. extra-virgin olive oil", "12 cabbage leaves", "1 lb. ground beef", "3/4 lb. ground pork", "1 c. riced cauliflower", "3 green onions, thinly sliced&nbsp;", "1/4 c. chopped parsley, plus more for serving&nbsp;", "Freshly ground black pepper"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "For the sauce: ", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat oven to 375°.&nbsp;Puree tomatoes, apple cider vinegar, red pepper flakes, onion powder, garlic powder, and oregano in a blender; season with salt and pepper."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large deep skillet (or large pot) over medium heat, heat oil. Add pureed tomato sauce, bring to a&nbsp;simmer, then lower to medium-low and simmer for 20 minutes, until slightly thickened."}]}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "For the cabbage rolls:", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large pot of boiling water, blanch cabbage leaves until tender and flexible, about 1 minute.&nbsp;Set aside."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Make filling: in a large bowl, combine ½ c. tomato sauce, ground meats, cauliflower rice, scallions, and parsley. Season with salt and pepper."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Spread a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of a large baking dish.&nbsp;Using a paring knife, cut out the hard triangular rib from each cabbage leaf. Place about ⅓ cup filling into one end of each leaf, then roll up, tucking in the sides as you roll. Place rolls seam side-down on top of sauce in baking dish. Spoon remaining sauce on top of cabbage rolls. Bake 45 minutes to 55 minutes,&nbsp;until the meat is cooked through and internal 