{"recipe_name": "Pulled Pork Sandwich", "yields": "8", "time": {"prep": "PT10M", "cook": "PT165M", "total": "PT175M"}, "ingredients": ["For the sauce:", "1 large onion, chopped", "6 garlic cloves, peeled", "1 pickled jalapeño pepper, seeded and chopped", "2 teaspoons Chipotle chile powder", "1 tablespoon tomato paste", "2 tablespoon Dijon mustard", "3/4 cup distilled white vinegar", "1 teaspoon paprika", "1/3 cup ketchup", "2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce", "1/4 cup light brown sugar", "Salt", "For the pork:", "1 bay leaf", "3 pounds pork butt shoulder roast", "Hamburger buns"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/jRGIAQPjU6-2fVyfEl-ibo7nvWA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-1-4e6f6f15aca445209eb14255fa78bfa0.jpg"}], "text": "Purée sauce ingredients in blender: Purée all of the sauce ingredients (everything except the bay leaf, the pork and the buns) in a blender until smooth. If you have extra time, marinate the pork in the sauce overnight or for several hours before cooking."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/jOsicRm9sObD_kgtYUIgrDlr1pE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-3b-7eb510bcfb124dce8bdc91705f683299.jpg"}], "text": "Simmer pork: Put sauce, bay leaf, and pork into a large pot and add 1 quart of water. Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, covered, turning frequently, for 2 hours or until the meat pulls apart easily with a fork."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/hNuPdyarBTVx_vRJbqxlMACeITo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-4a-85ae196ce8ea4088b2ec0d72c2c40d50.jpg"}], "text": "Shred the pork: Remove from heat and cool pork in the sauce. When cool enough to touch, remove the pork from the sauce and shred into small pieces. Set aside."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/bGgkBElIVOghsbMyU3MA0FRwLUs=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-7a-ce62a6979b874665b9e714cd85ae5f71.jpg"}], "text": "Reduce sauce, return pork to sauce: Put the sauce back on the stove and bring it to a low boil. Let the sauce boil down until it has been reduced by two thirds. Add the pork back to the sauce. Salt to taste."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/0iY8Mzbx1XEgUuDQd2Ys6sUpGvI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Lead-5b-02fd41ceee474beca0f5b3a3e24bee26.jpg"}], "text": "Serve: Remove the bay leaf before serving. Serve the pork hot over open-face hamburger buns."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\"], \"headline\": \"Pulled Pork Sandwich\", \"datePublished\": \"2007-11-04T15:35:28.000-05:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2022-02-06T11:21:26.204-05:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Elise Bauer\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/elise-bauer-5091824\"}], \"description\": \"Skip the jarred BBQ sauce! This pulled pork comes together easily and the homemade marinade makes the difference. Slowly cooked pork shoulder becomes fall-off-the-bone tender.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/X3Hzg36FHEhr_UDdob6sgx7wRqw=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Lead-3b_recirc-11bef20a2da0462d93959411a7dba7e1.jpg\", \"height\": 1000, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/ZkpVnBic-px9BSfP1.mp4\", \"description\": \"In this video you'll learn how to make sweet royal icing to use on cookies. This recipe is a basic recipe with tips and instructions to decorate sugar cookies for celebrations. See how royal icing is made quickly and easily for use in dessert making. This recipe uses egg whites and can be colored with food coloring. Watch how you can color your royal icing with professional grade gel food coloring for the best results. This recipe is beginner-friendly.\", \"duration\": \"PT1M22S\", \"name\": \"Pulled Pork Sandwich\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/ZkpVnBic/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2021-09-10T16:19:27.303-04:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Simply Recipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/QvixEwCD02s_lnkgkVb6mHwKS7c=/1125x320/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/SimplyRecipesLogoTransparent-07a297c54b2142ae9c079abb2f0fa639.png\", \"width\": 1125, \"height\": 320}, \"brand\": \"Simply Recipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/about-us-5096129#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/simplyrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/simplyrecipes\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/simplyrecipes\"]}, \"name\": \"Pulled Pork Sandwich\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\", \"ratingCount\": \"28\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT165M\", \"keywords\": \"Budget, Comfort Food, Pork, Pulled Pork, Sandwich, American, Dinner\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"515 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"28 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"114 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"2 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"36 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"9 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"615 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"10 g\", \"fatContent\": \"28 g\", \"servingSize\": \"Serves 6 to 8\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT10M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\", \"Sandwich\", \"Budget\", \"Comfort Food\", \"Pork\", \"Pulled Pork\", \"Sandwich\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"For the sauce:\", \"1 large onion, chopped\", \"6 garlic cloves, peeled\", \"1 pickled jalape\\u00f1o pepper, seeded and chopped\", \"2 teaspoons Chipotle chile powder\", \"1 tablespoon tomato paste\", \"2 tablespoon Dijon mustard\", \"3/4 cup distilled white vinegar\", \"1 teaspoon paprika\", \"1/3 cup ketchup\", \"2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce\", \"1/4 cup light brown sugar\", \"Salt\", \"For the pork:\", \"1 bay leaf\", \"3 pounds pork butt shoulder roast\", \"Hamburger buns\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/jRGIAQPjU6-2fVyfEl-ibo7nvWA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-1-4e6f6f15aca445209eb14255fa78bfa0.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Pur\\u00e9e sauce ingredients in blender: Pur\\u00e9e all of the sauce ingredients (everything except the bay leaf, the pork and the buns) in a blender until smooth. If you have extra time, marinate the pork in the sauce overnight or for several hours before cooking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/jOsicRm9sObD_kgtYUIgrDlr1pE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-3b-7eb510bcfb124dce8bdc91705f683299.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Simmer pork: Put sauce, bay leaf, and pork into a large pot and add 1 quart of water. Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, covered, turning frequently, for 2 hours or until the meat pulls apart easily with a fork.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/hNuPdyarBTVx_vRJbqxlMACeITo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-4a-85ae196ce8ea4088b2ec0d72c2c40d50.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Shred the pork: Remove from heat and cool pork in the sauce. When cool enough to touch, remove the pork from the sauce and shred into small pieces. Set aside.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/bGgkBElIVOghsbMyU3MA0FRwLUs=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Method-7a-ce62a6979b874665b9e714cd85ae5f71.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Reduce sauce, return pork to sauce: Put the sauce back on the stove and bring it to a low boil. Let the sauce boil down until it has been reduced by two thirds. Add the pork back to the sauce. Salt to taste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/0iY8Mzbx1XEgUuDQd2Ys6sUpGvI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pulled-Pork-Sandwich-Lead-5b-02fd41ceee474beca0f5b3a3e24bee26.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Serve: Remove the bay leaf before serving. Serve the pork hot over open-face hamburger buns.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"8\", \"totalTime\": \"PT175M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bertandherb\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've always just improvised when it comes to pulled pork, with good results cooking it in the oven. But for some reason after buying a Boston butt I decided to look for recipes, and found this one. The method was so different that I was intrigued and decided to make it. I'm sorry I did. First, two hours on the stove top does not yield meat that's cooked enough to be shredded. Second, the quart of water is crazy -- no way to meaningfully reduce it unless you boil the sauce for hours. Last, way too much vinegar.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"GG\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Too much vinegar in the sauce. Wish I would have added 1/4 cup instead.\\nI wanted to love this some homemade bbq sauce, but we just didn't. \\nPrep was easy\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mark\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"How many Pounds of Pork is this recipe for ?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jarrett\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"What this would with a pork sirloin? All the pork shoulders were 4-5 lb\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kristin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Hey Elise! This sounds wonderful! Could I make this a day ahead, refrigerate, and then reheat the meat before assembling the sliders?\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/pulled_pork_sandwich/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/dinner-recipes-5091433\", \"name\": \"Dinners\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/family-dinner-recipes-5091349\", \"name\": \"Family Dinners\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/pulled_pork_sandwich/\", \"name\": \"Pulled Pork Sandwich\"}}]}}, \"about\": []}"}
