is about to revolutionize your vegetarian cooking. With fried mushrooms and a crunchy coating, it tastes just like fried chicken!\", \"datePublished\": \"2021-01-08T13:20:55+00:00\", \"image\": [\"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/vegetarian-fried-mushroom-chicken-air-fryer-vert.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/vegetarian-fried-mushroom-chicken-air-fryer-vert-500x500.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/vegetarian-fried-mushroom-chicken-air-fryer-vert-500x375.jpg\", \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/vegetarian-fried-mushroom-chicken-air-fryer-vert-480x270.jpg\"], \"video\": {\"name\": \"\\\"Fried Chicken\\\" Made With Oyster Mushrooms!\", \"description\": \"This Buttermilk Fried Mushrooms recipe is about to revolutionize your vegetarian cooking. With air fried oyster mushrooms and a crunchy coating, it tastes just like fried chicken!\\n  \\nGet the recipe here: https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/\\n\\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/liveeatlearn/\\nTikTok: https://tiktok.com/@liveeatlearn/\\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/liveeatlearn/\\nPinterest: https://www.pinterest.com/live_eat_learn\", \"uploadDate\": \"2023-01-21T19:56:41+00:00\", \"duration\": \"PT55S\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gyGdrX7X2mA/hqdefault.jpg\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/embed/gyGdrX7X2mA?feature=oembed\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gyGdrX7X2mA\", \"@type\": \"VideoObject\"}, \"recipeYield\": [\"2\", \"2 servings\"], \"prepTime\": \"PT30M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT15M\", \"totalTime\": \"PT45M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"2 heaping cups oyster mushrooms (125 g)\", \"1 cup buttermilk (240 mL, see notes for vegan substitute)\", \"1 \\u00bd cups all-purpose flour (200 g)\", \"1 tsp each salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, cumin\", \"1 Tbsp oil* (15 mL)\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Marinate: Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 C). Clean mushrooms then toss together with buttermilk in a large bowl. Let marinate for 15 minutes.\", \"name\": \"Marinate: Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 C). Clean mushrooms then toss together with buttermilk in a large bowl. Let marinate for 15 minutes.\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/#wprm-recipe-20891-step-0-0\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/step1-buttermilk-fried-mushrooms.jpg\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Breading: In a large bowl combine flour and spices. Spoon mushrooms out of the buttermilk (save the buttermilk). Dip each mushroom in the flour mixture, shake off excess flour, dip once more in the buttermilk, then once more in the flour (in short: wet &gt; dry &gt; wet &gt; dry).\", \"name\": \"Breading: In a large bowl combine flour and spices. Spoon mushrooms out of the buttermilk (save the buttermilk). Dip each mushroom in the flour mixture, shake off excess flour, dip once more in the buttermilk, then once more in the flour (in short: wet &gt; dry &gt; wet &gt; dry).\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/#wprm-recipe-20891-step-0-1\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/step2-buttermilk-fried-mushrooms.jpg\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Cook: Grease the bottom of your air fry pan well, then place mushrooms in a single layer, leaving space between mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, then roughly brush all sides with a little oil to promote browning. Continue cooking 5 to 10 more minutes, until golden brown and crispy.\", \"name\": \"Cook: Grease the bottom of your air fry pan well, then place mushrooms in a single layer, leaving space between mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, then roughly brush all sides with a little oil to promote browning. Continue cooking 5 to 10 more minutes, until golden brown and crispy.\", \"url\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/#wprm-recipe-20891-step-0-2\", \"image\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/step3-buttermilk-fried-mushrooms.jpg\"}], \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.81\", \"ratingCount\": \"106\"}, \"recipeCategory\": [\"Main Dishes\", \"Side Dishes\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"keywords\": \"fried mushrooms, fried oyster mushrooms, vegetarian fried chicken\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"servingSize\": \"1 serving\", \"calories\": \"355 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"57 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"12.4 g\", \"fatContent\": \"9.7 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"1.7 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"5 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1012 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"3 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"6.7 g\"}, \"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://www.liveeatlearn.com/buttermilk-fried-mushrooms/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Chicken Pot Pie", "yields": ["8"], "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT50M", "total": "PT80M"}, "ingredients": ["1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cubed", "1 cup sliced carrots", "1 cup frozen green peas", "0.5 cup sliced celery", "0.33333334326744 cup butter", "0.33333334326744 cup chopped onion", "0.33333334326744 cup all-purpose flour", "0.5 teaspoon salt", "0.25 teaspoon black pepper", "0.25 teaspoon celery seed", "1.75 cups chicken broth", "0.66666668653488 cup milk", "2 (9 inch) unbaked pie crusts"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/SMMTlCCsBe1nxndDnCNOu6qzi3A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-1-437-37e574602aa14705a9055079b394e273.jpg"}], "text": "Gather all ingredients and preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C.)"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/N5mwz4LxAR1uNcIQlXSFpYBXSWo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-2-440-b0b5c2dc59a44385801b76b13946ce7e.jpg"}], "text": "Combine chicken, carrots, peas, and celery in a saucepan; add water to cover and bring to a boil. Boil for 15 minutes, then remove from the heat and drain."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/mF0wKLB37PpkbsWoF41WTPCipeE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-4-449-0395855878f04080b27c0ced0b7a9243.jpg"}], "text": "While the chicken is cooking, melt butter in another saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft and translucent, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, and celery seed"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/E2ktPyYLmQ8PqvELq3X_AykF_k0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-5-454-e0b5f720d2d345399d8d150500108748.jpg"}], "text": "Slowly stir in chicken broth and milk."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ehlYkqTsqYkWIdJP5aLcP1JZ78Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-5-459-16f6e9b9350a48eeb10cbe4dffb9188d.jpg"}], "text": "Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until thick, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/B9tYe7lFUrVpxMgKS4P4L5qz0y4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-6-462-699787c97281479c9cdf8dc1fc8e2541.jpg"}], "text": "Place chicken and vegetables in the bottom pie crust. Pour hot liquid mixture over top."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9m_M6S1OobAhKcE3HrxtZ-31iU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-7-466-0c57b9ee2a0146ed9ad4f9c41654bb7b.jpg"}], "text": "Cover with top crust, seal the edges, and cut away any excess dough. Make several small slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/l2xNBnBqq8qi3Khnz0DQ4l9y65A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-8-469-75ff348079b740c3ba081c212640927e.jpg"}], "text": "Bake in the preheated oven until pastry is golden brown and filling is bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before serving."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/vlTW2Csu30V0zGDOm-5C4LDVGhA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-xi-MFS_275-4x3-87a594bb9406495cbf51b166f7112e5c.jpg"}], "text": "Serve immediately and enjoy!"}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Chicken Pot Pie\", \"datePublished\": \"2000-06-13T06:16:24.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-09-14T16:43:15.952-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Robbie Rice\"}], \"description\": \"A delicious, homemade chicken pot pie made from scratch with carrots, peas, and celery. This comfort food classic will be a hit with your family.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/vlTW2Csu30V0zGDOm-5C4LDVGhA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-xi-MFS_275-4x3-87a594bb9406495cbf51b166f7112e5c.jpg\", \"height\": 1125, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/fF3Om66k-ma1DlVvV.mp4\", \"description\": \"Learn how to make an amazing chicken pot pie. It may look difficult, but it\\u2019s actually very simple to prepare. The key is to use unbaked pie crusts. See how it\\u2019s done!\", \"duration\": \"PT4M12S\", \"name\": \"Chicken Pot Pie IX\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/fF3Om66k/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2021-02-27T16:19:40.948-05:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Chicken Pot Pie\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.8\", \"ratingCount\": \"13269\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT50M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"412 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"30 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"55 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"3 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"18 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"9 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"517 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"3 g\", \"fatContent\": \"24 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cubed\", \"1 cup sliced carrots\", \"1 cup frozen green peas\", \"0.5 cup sliced celery\", \"0.33333334326744 cup butter\", \"0.33333334326744 cup chopped onion\", \"0.33333334326744 cup all-purpose flour\", \"0.5 teaspoon salt\", \"0.25 teaspoon black pepper\", \"0.25 teaspoon celery seed\", \"1.75 cups chicken broth\", \"0.66666668653488 cup milk\", \"2 (9 inch) unbaked pie crusts\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/SMMTlCCsBe1nxndDnCNOu6qzi3A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-1-437-37e574602aa14705a9055079b394e273.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Gather all ingredients and preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C.)\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/N5mwz4LxAR1uNcIQlXSFpYBXSWo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-2-440-b0b5c2dc59a44385801b76b13946ce7e.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Combine chicken, carrots, peas, and celery in a saucepan; add water to cover and bring to a boil. Boil for 15 minutes, then remove from the heat and drain.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/mF0wKLB37PpkbsWoF41WTPCipeE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-4-449-0395855878f04080b27c0ced0b7a9243.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"While the chicken is cooking, melt butter in another saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft and translucent, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, and celery seed\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/E2ktPyYLmQ8PqvELq3X_AykF_k0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-5-454-e0b5f720d2d345399d8d150500108748.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Slowly stir in chicken broth and milk.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ehlYkqTsqYkWIdJP5aLcP1JZ78Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-5-459-16f6e9b9350a48eeb10cbe4dffb9188d.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until thick, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/B9tYe7lFUrVpxMgKS4P4L5qz0y4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-6-462-699787c97281479c9cdf8dc1fc8e2541.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Place chicken and vegetables in the bottom pie crust. Pour hot liquid mixture over top.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9m_M6S1OobAhKcE3HrxtZ-31iU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-7-466-0c57b9ee2a0146ed9ad4f9c41654bb7b.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Cover with top crust, seal the edges, and cut away any excess dough. Make several small slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/l2xNBnBqq8qi3Khnz0DQ4l9y65A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-IX-mfs-step-8-469-75ff348079b740c3ba081c212640927e.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Bake in the preheated oven until pastry is golden brown and filling is bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before serving.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/vlTW2Csu30V0zGDOm-5C4LDVGhA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/26317-chicken-pot-pie-xi-MFS_275-4x3-87a594bb9406495cbf51b166f7112e5c.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Serve immediately and enjoy!\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"8\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT80M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"NH Grammy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent recipe. Used more carrots, less peas and added poultry seasoning and thyme. Sooooo good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sue H. West Manlove\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Alittle too much celery taste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Green recipe. Mines slightly different but the I use leftover rotisserie chicken the day before or cooked thanksgiving leftover turkey . Store bought crust.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I make pot pie for special family occasions at the holidays and use this recipe as my basis (with some alterations) my entire family and extended family are obsessed and demand I make at least two to three of these every time we get together. I add some of my own touches (a little extra garlic powder, light dash of smoked paprika, finely chopped brown mushrooms and a slice or two of diced bacon) definitely need the celery seed - super important. Recommend making one with a mashed potato top - sublime\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jamie P.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is not as difficult as I at first thought it would be. It tastes fantastic. The only thing I changed, was to add a sprinkle of cayenne pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved. I cut my chicken pieces larger, passed on celery, added potatoes. Scrumptious. My first chicken pot pi!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"gjmstarman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great use of some left over homemade chicken soup. Added that broth to the recipe total liquid for the sauce. Topped with the left over stuffing instead of the second top crust.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Gail \"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was a little dry, but may have been my mistake. I loosely followed the recipe. I will make it again. Very good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mary Ellen Sorci\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I really like the results of the pie crust. Make sure you dont make more filling than crust.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MzPamD\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a great way to use what I had on hand. I used frozen cooked chicken thighs and a store bought frozen pie crust. We loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Danell Underwood\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Sauteed the diced chicken. Eliminated the celery and added some cooked potatoes instead. Used canned carrots I cut up, microwaved the peas and potatoes. Added some fresh parsley, rosemary and sage. Brushed egg wash on bottom crust and top crust. Turned out great! Not too runny or dry.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Suzanne Sheffield\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A family favorite. It's so comforting and delicious. I add a little more peas, carrots, and onions, but really no changes are needed in this recipe. We just like the extra veggies.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The water I boiled the chicken an veggies in I used as my broth, why waste it, it's got the Flava flavs\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shark byte\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delish. Family loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KirstiJoy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Been making it for years!! Everyone who tastes is ruined forever and this is the only pot pie they want. Waaay Better than Costco. Make sure to bake in a DEEP DISH pan or you\\u2019ll leak all over.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only change I made was using Cumin instead of celery seed (because I didn\\u2019t have any) so DELICIOUS!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Not great. Followed the recipe exactly. Came out very bland. Not what I expected. I'll probably move on from this one.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Just perfect and delicious as is.. I didn\\u2019t change a thing.. will definitely keep this recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good pot pie! I sprinkled a little bit of ground thyme on top of the chicken!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made it for my family and it was absolutely delicious. Everyone loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"byoung1961\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made exactly according to the recipe and it was delicious! My husband kept going back to \\\"even up the edges!\\\"\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Robin Livengood\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Pretty good but better if you first saute the veggies and chicken. I also added some soy sauce and 1 tsp worstershire sauce. I had some mushrooms and green beans which I cut up and added, too.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Renee Hinton\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used can of Veg-All vegetables. Very delicious\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Aprildawn Britnell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Taste so good! I enjoyed making this with my boyfriend\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tara Chisholm\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I followed the recipe, however I sauted the chicken, onions, and garlic , parsley, poultry seasoning, thyme , and salt and pepper together. Then I set the chicken aside. Next I melted the butter, and sauted the carrots, celery , and peas, then added the flour and then gradually added the chicken broth, and finally the cream then i added in the chicken, and simmered until the broth was thickened. Finally poured it into the pie shell and rolled out the crust to cover it . Can't wait to taste it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"hyedi Johnson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Disguarding thr first broth that was used to stew the chicken and veggies\\u2026this is a common practice actually. Not all stews or soups do this, but it\\u2019s done to get rid of the \\u2018cloudy broth and the bits \\u2019 that come from cooking chicken and veggies. It\\u2019s purely a choice, some don\\u2019t want a cloudy soup. Ya, sounds weird but to each their own. Delicious pot pie!! My family raves about it last night when I made it\\ud83c\\udf72\\ud83e\\udd58\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Did it exactly the way the recipe called the first time and loved it! Was wondering if anyone has used some skinless thigh meat with the breast?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chef Mom\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent. I didn\\u2019t have thawed chicken breast, so I cooked the veggies without the chicken. Added the chicken breast meat after cooking the breasts in the instapot, then tossed together. Very flavorful just as it is! Made the recommended buttery flaky crust prior. Absolutely amazing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sharlene Barnum\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have to laugh when I read, I made it but changed all the ingredients and methods. I have followed the recipe and it is a family favorite. The fact the chicken is boiled is the secret. The chicken is moist and tender. Many recipes that used pre-cooked chicken or saute the chicken end up having tough meat in the pie. One of my favorite sayings \\\"If it ain't broke, don't fix it.\\\" applies here.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very nice challenge \\ud83d\\udc4f\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I give a 5 just because is the first time I make it but I change everything use the broth from my fresh chicken and vegetables, used fresh heavy cream instead of milk and fresh homemade butter and it came out perfect and delicious \\ud83d\\ude0b\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Dana Richardson Leas\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Appreciated the info and outline of steps. I used frozen mixed veggies and chicken and onions. Also added frozen crinkle cut potatoes and saut\\u00e9ed in butter then chicken stock. Separately I made a roux using flour chicken stock, celery seed and half and half as I had no cream soups. All ingredients were cooked in a deep dish pan using ready made pie crusts. We liked the dish and will make again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jmnels6\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have been making this recipe for years now and I make it according to the recipe with slight changes and it always turns out amazing. I usually do 2 glass deep dish pans so I double the recipes and it turns out great every time. I also boil the chicken and veggies in chicken stock or broth for a little extra flavoring.. I hate reading review when people say \\u201cI gave this recipe 4stars but I made these many modifications\\u201d either make the recipe as is or don\\u2019t comment and move on\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made it and doubled the recipe for 2 pies! I used a bit more salt and pepper, mixed frozen vegetables and some potatoes. It was delicious! Will definitely make this many more times in the future, loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tracey Paris\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I absolutely loved it!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Steffie326\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The recipe was easy to follow. The only thing I did differently was added garlic and extra chicken (used rotisserie chicken). Like others mentioned, it came out too dry. So I'll have to adjust for that next time. The flavor though was awesome!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First time making this dish and it turned out fantastic. Husband said it was the best he's ever had. Followed recipe exactly as written. Will definitely be making it again. Thank you for sharing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MDR\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my go-to recipe for the sauce. I triple the ingredients and make 2 pies. It\\u2019s easy, no fail and delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Amazing pie!! Needs extra salt and pepper but also good with some garlic powder in the onion mixture.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It's good! I made it using rotisserie chicken and canned veggies. I also added sage, rosemary, and thyme. Next time I'm going to follow the suggestion in the reviews.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sandy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Didn\\u2019t change anything very good we all enjoyed it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Amy Lynn Fennell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used left over rotisserie ckn Added drippings from ckn to cup and added the rest of the ckn broth and milk. Added 2.5 cups frozen veg and 1/2c frozen corn to saut\\u00e9ed celery and onion then added flour and broth/milk mixture with salt and pepper. Then added ckn and mixed until thick. Just seemed easier to do the gravy that way other than separate.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Luv cooking \"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Everything was great, definitely will be making it again. Made mine with chicken bone broth, and added a little more because the rue got a little thicker than I liked. Will substitute Chicken for Rabbit next time I prepare it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ruohan Hsieh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Followed the recipe almost exactly, except for using chicken thigh instead of breast. Very good pie, I thought it could use a bit more salt but husband loved it just the way it is. We ate half and freeze the remainder of the pie. Reheating was very easy too and tasted just as good. Great comfort food. Thank you for the recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Drinkflinger\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"great recipe I made 1 large pie and 8 5 \\\" pies , I don't measure but everything was great ! My gravy was thinner but that was my own fault , no dry pie here ! lol\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The white cream sauce is excellent. I used pre-made pie crusts for this recipe and (although I usually cut up all the vegetables for a pot pie), this time I cut only celery and onion and used 1 1/2 small bags of frozen vegetables for the filling.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stephanie Donaldson Pressman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent! Will make it weekly.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"kdonahue\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We loved this dish. I pre-baked the bottom crust for about 10 mins. Poke a few holes in it so it doesn't bubble. I added the carrots, onions, celery and peas in a pan and cooked it in butter. I then used salt, pepper and garlic on the chicken and cooked it in a pan. I didn't add any salt and pepper or celery seed. Hubby said he would have wanted pepper added to the liquid. I made the sauce/liquid as directed\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We love this recipe! Making it again for Football Sunday. It\\u2019s truly perfect!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent! Easy and really tasty, my husband and picky 15-year-old loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Deborah\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this according to the recipe &amp; my family LOVED it!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jtms\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So I only made the innards to this, adding the chicken and veggies to the onion roux and simmering it a bit, but doggone was it good! Only thing I'd add is a few more pinches of salt, maybe when saut\\u00e9ing the onions? Fantastic chicken pot pie guts!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Carrie Burke\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I make this on a regular basis. It is always a hit. I would not change a thing although I may mix the chicken and veggies with the wet mixture prior to adding to the pie crusts next time I make this.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Vernon Chamberlain\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used this recipe for years now.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Wonderful recipe! I used a Costco rotisserie chicken instead of raw chicken breast (the whole reason I decided to make chicken pot pie was to get rid of it lol) and it turned out amazing. The only thing I\\u2019ll add is, I wish I would have mixed the chicken and veggies with the wet mixture before I put it in the pie crust because I noticed that some parts were drier than others. Other than that, wonderful recipe and I plan to make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tara Watson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my go to recipe for chicken pot pie. My family loves it. I tried it without celery seed and didn\\u2019t enjoy it as much as following the recipe to the fullest. I do too like with ketchup lol\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Karen Singleton-wray\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"There are not enough stars for this, at all. I didn't use salt and pepper and celery seed. I used Tony chachere seasoning. I also used half and half, for chicken breasts and thighs. When I say this was great, I truly mean it! I hate cooked carrots and they were delicious too. This recipe doesn't make any sense on how good it was!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! \\u2764\\ufe0f\\u2764\\ufe0f\\u2764\\ufe0f\\u2764\\ufe0f\\ud83d\\udc95\\ud83d\\udc95\\ud83d\\udc95\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Barbara\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019ve never made pot pie. It turned out great. I would make again and share with family.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Heather West\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this pretty close to the recipe and it was delicious not dry at all perfect consistency thank you\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Holly Lynn Loussaert\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Your sauce is amazing. I did omit the onions because I was sharing this with my dog also.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lvnalrge1\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've made this more than a dozen times now. In the beginning I always follow instructions exactly as written. Over time I precooked the bottom crust with a little garlic powder and parsley sprinkled over it and pierced it with a fork. Next I mixed the (rotisserie because I get lazy sometimes) chicken and veggies all together with the sauce instead of poring over them in the dish. We rarely have leftovers. I also made the crust using Nana's pie crust on YouTube. It's also a fan favorite and very savory. I use it for apple pies as well. Thanks for sharing your recipe!It has been very loved.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Half a teaspoon of salt for the entire dish is insane. It came together fine but was severely underseasoned. Subbed chicken breasts with thighs as well. As pointed out by another user, don't boil the chicken + veg. I ended up making the roux/gravy in the same pan after taking the chicken + veg out and deglazing it after cooking the onions and garlic a bit. The crust should have an egg wash too. On another note, I will never understand American's insistence on using a unit of measurement intended for volume when weight is much simpler. If not explicitly labeled on the packaging, how is one supposed to measure 1/3 cup of butter? Something else occurred to me: placing the hot gravy sauce directly on top of a puff pastry or pie crust dough is a sure way to have a soggy, chewy bottom crust. It will heat up the cold butter, melt it, and prevent the formation of those flaky layers you'd want to have in a pie. You can put the filling in the fridge or a cool place for a few minutes until at least room-temperature before having it come in contact with the puff pastry. The recipe leaves a lot to be desired, though not technically bad.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shugurl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Oh this is amazing!! It\\u2019s so good!!! I used lactose free milk Highly recommend this recipe! Family devoured it!! I boiled veggies in chicken broth &amp; added a few tsp to the onion flour mix\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Dusty\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made as is and it was perfect!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Love the recipe. the only thing differently that we did was cooked the chicken separately and omitted the celery.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My grandmother would be proud of this recipe . I use local produce to make this and even added a parsnip for giggles. Outstanding !\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Laura Couch Strebler\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This turned out beautifully! I added 1/4 tsp thyme and a sprinkle of turmeric instead of the celery seed. Also added a bullion cube to the boiling water for the chicken and veggies, and used that water plus about a 1/2 cup of chicken broth to get my gravy to the right consistency. The flavors and textures were perfect! Thanks for a great recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Terry Smith Tipton\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my go to pot pie recipe! I do add some cooked fresh mushrooms and poultry seasoning. I also use a cup of milk and two cups of chicken broth as I like it a little more juicy. For me, it makes two casserole dishes which is great for two meals.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"James Harvey\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made it with a homemade pie crust. It was wonderful!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was perfectly balanced with just enough sauce. I added cubed potatoes and boiled the veggies in chicken broth instead of water. I used precooked chicken so I added that with the cooked veggies into the crust. Very tasty!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Marsha Randolph\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"added a little more liquid because the potatoes seemed to soak up the liquid. I also cooked my potato cubes until about 1/3 done.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jens recipes\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Love this recipe, my family loves it too !\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was delicious. My family and I loved it. I even tried the pie crust recipe which came out great.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Marilyn\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious and filling. Easy to put together.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So yummy!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Forrest Halford\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First three times making this I followed the recipe exactly and had great results. Today I followed other users' advice and boiled the chicken and veggies in the chicken broth and after draining added more broth to make 2 cups instead of 1 3/4 cups. Everything else was the same. Really tasty improvement.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Laura the Cook\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is our goto recipe for over 2 years. My husband has perfected this pot pie so he's in charge of dinner when we are in the mood for it. Changes in cooking for us: chicken is cooked with the onion and spices (we add clove of garlic, marjoram, tarragon and rosemary (dash of each for added flavor). When chicken is cooked but not brown, flour is added, chicken broth, one chicken bullion cube and milk. When mixture is starting to thicken, the drained vegetables are added to the mixture. Once thickened, the mixture is poured into a 9 inch deep dish pie pan. We only use one pie crust (to reduce calories on top). This is the best recipe we have found for a pot pie.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Awesome!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sandy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I followed for the most part except the waste of the broth of the veggies. I used it and it\\u2019s tasty,\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"cmach\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This pie was delicious- I was surprised how easy and quick it was to make. I made as directed, using and saving chicken broth to add back in. I added 2 cups of the broth with the milk to the roux. I also used 3/4 cup onion. No other changes. Next time I may use a deep dish crust as I couldn\\u2019t fit in all of the yummy roux. Thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious, easy to follow, made the crust from scratch though. Family loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pamela L. Fandrich\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have used this recipe for years, and it\\u2019s delicious with or without the celery seed.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy to follow recipe and it turned out great. I didn't add onion or Celery or celery seed and was still amazing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sfleck\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love this recipe. The only thing I changed is to make a single crust and 5 inch ramekins. It makes 4 full ramekins. This picture is prior to cooking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Was very easy to make and very delicious. 10/10 will make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"catcando56\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I use this recipe often it is a good solid meal to share with families in my community through my church who help people who are recovering from surgeries, just had a baby, caregivers.nice to make ahead and let them bake it in the oven\\u2026..my family gets jealous when they see it and realize it\\u2019s not for them\\u2026I often make 2 at a time because of that thanks for the recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It's a delicious recipe! The only different thing is I like my peas crunchy so I added it at the last step before covering the pie.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Been trying different recipes and this was a huge success! The only thing I do differently is I use Frozen Mixed Vegetables that I buy at Sam\\u2019s Club ( steam in a bag). This is so much better then store bought chicken pot pie- you will not regret making this!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rochelle Beach Rasper\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"As is... perfect.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"D\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Added thyme and parsley. Put the veggies and chicken in the pie plate as directed. Then I added the sauce. Family loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"AmberG\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious!!!!!! I followed the directions exactly. No modifications. I found the sauce to be so delicious when I tasted it with a spoon before adding the veggies and chicken. The ingredients barely fit in my pie pan, lol (I'm glad I diced the chicken pretty small). It came out wonderful and my husband was really happy!! We both added more salt and pepper to our servings. I wonder if that's because the veggies and chicken added to the sauce made it less seasoned?? Next time I will season the chicken and veggies with salt and pepper before adding the sauce. Next time I will use chicken broth to cook the veggies and half way through, add and cook the chicken AND THEN use the broth to make the sauce-no water. Leftovers were a little dry so next time I will double the sauce recipe and whoever wants more sauce can pour it over their serving for more creamy deliciousness!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Toss the cube chicken in a little bit of flour, and seasonings, sauteed on high for a couple mins (not too long). Add your veggies and turn the stove to low, cover. Don't boil.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I only changed one thing. Instead of putting celery in, I add cubed potatoes. The way I was raised in Pa Dutch country. The flavor was perfect!! And everyone absolutely loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michael Smith\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Outstanding recipe! I\\u2019ve made it plenty of times. Trader Joe\\u2019s pie crust off the charts!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nancy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So very good! It is the perfect Chicken Pot Pie!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have been making this recipe for years and a family and friend favorite. I have made a few changes to adjust to my taste and preference. - boil the water first, add fresh veggies for about 5 minutes, and then add chicken and frozen peas. Veggies become overcooked and chicken becomes dry if boiled for too long. Check the chicken to make sure done. - I use boneless chicken thighs instead of breasts - substitute 1/2 tsp of poultry seasoning (or season to taste) for celery seed. - add more chicken broth if the gravy is too thick (it will thicken while baking). -\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made this three times and enjoy it with the kids. I omit the celery seed (to me, the taste is overpowering), saute the chicken pieces with a little adobo seasoning before adding them to the pot with the veggies to cook with just a little stock, and add corn niblets.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"irolland\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my very favorite recipe. All of my family loves it and it\\u2019s always a crowd pleaser no matter where I take it. I do not use a bottom crust because in my opinion isn\\u2019t necessary, and it just adds calories. Sometimes I have added potato or corn, occasionally a little extra butter and flour if I want it extra thick. I have put green beans in it and definitely do not care for that, but honestly, the recipe is just perfect the way it is. For quite some time I just cut slits in the top of the crust, but there was a lot of boil over which made it less aesthetically pleasing. By cutting openings instead of just slits the crust stays perfectly placed, there\\u2019s no boil over, and then I can make the pretty little flowers.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"SSCheves\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"yum yum\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/26317/chicken-pot-pie-ix/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/2268/main-dish/savory-pies/pot-pie/\", \"name\": \"Pot Pie Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/16181/main-dish/savory-pies/pot-pie/chicken-pot-pie/\", \"name\": \"Chicken Pot Pie Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/26317/chicken-pot-pie-ix/\", \"name\": \"Chicken Pot Pie\"}}]}, \"reviewedBy\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Test Kitchen\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/allrecipes-test-kitchen-7553892\"}], \"lastReviewed\": \"2023-09-14T16:43:15.952-04:00\"}, \"about\": []}"}
