Url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe1.jpg\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-01-17T06:00:12+00:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-02-23T12:44:15+00:00\", \"description\": \"This chunky chipotle chili recipe is made with a mix of peppers, chili seasoning, and lots of chipotles in adobo sauce for the best rich and smoky flavor.\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#breadcrumb\"}, \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"ReadAction\", \"target\": [\"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/\"]}]}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#primaryimage\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe1.jpg\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe1.jpg\", \"width\": 1200, \"height\": 1800, \"caption\": \"Chipotle Chili Recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#breadcrumb\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"name\": \"Home\", \"item\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/\"}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"name\": \"Recipes\", \"item\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/\"}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"name\": \"Chipotle Chili Recipe\"}]}, {\"@type\": \"WebSite\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#website\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/\", \"name\": \"Chili Pepper Madness\", \"description\": \"Bold and Spicy Food and Recipes\", \"publisher\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#organization\"}, \"potentialAction\": [{\"@type\": \"SearchAction\", \"target\": {\"@type\": \"EntryPoint\", \"urlTemplate\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/?s={search_term_string}\"}, \"query-input\": \"required name=search_term_string\"}], \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\"}, {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#organization\", \"name\": \"Chili Pepper Madness\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#/schema/logo/image/\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Logo-SQ.jpg\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Logo-SQ.jpg\", \"width\": 800, \"height\": 800, \"caption\": \"Chili Pepper Madness\"}, \"image\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#/schema/logo/image/\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/chilipeppermadness/\", \"https://twitter.com/jalapenomadness\", \"https://www.instagram.com/chilipeppermadness/\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelhultquist/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/jalapenomadness/\", \"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2VP-UJuszHFPnTYa7BsSqA\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#/schema/person/4fb0a50661f1022cc3fff1d09a3a6886\", \"name\": \"Mike Hultquist\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"inLanguage\": \"en-US\", \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#/schema/person/image/\", \"url\": \"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/96278a487dc8089a6be967b2a0215288?s=96&d=mm&r=g\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/96278a487dc8089a6be967b2a0215288?s=96&d=mm&r=g\", \"caption\": \"Mike Hultquist\"}, \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/general-content/welcome-to-chili-pepper-madness/\"]}, {\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"name\": \"Chipotle Chili Recipe\", \"author\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/#/schema/person/4fb0a50661f1022cc3fff1d09a3a6886\"}, \"description\": \"This chunky chipotle chili recipe is made with a mix of peppers, chili seasoning, and lots of chipotles in adobo sauce for the best rich and smoky flavor.\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-01-17T00:00:12+00:00\", \"image\": [\"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe5.jpg\", \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe5-500x500.jpg\", \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe5-500x375.jpg\", \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chipotle-Chili-Recipe5-480x270.jpg\"], \"video\": {\"name\": \"Chipotle Chili - Spicy, Chunky, DELICIOUS!\", \"description\": \"This chunky chipotle chili recipe is made with a mix of peppers, chili seasoning, and lots of chipotles in adobo sauce for the best rich and smoky flavor.\\n\\nCHAPTERS:\\n0:00 Delicious Chipotle Chili\\n0:29 Onion and Peppers\\n1:11 Spices & Seasonings List\\n1:31 Garlic\\n1:55 Ground Meats\\n2:28 Adding the Seasonings\\n3:29 Other Ingredients\\n5:22 Let it Simmer\\n5:49 Taste Test\\n\\nTHINGS YOU\\u2019LL NEED:\\n1 tablespoon olive oil\\n1.5 pound ground turkey or ground beef - I\\u2019m using a combination of both\\n1 large onion, chopped\\n1 jalapeno pepper, chopped\\n1 poblano pepper, chopped\\n1 hot chili pepper, chopped (for a spicier version \\u2013 try a habanero or ghost pepper \\u2013 optional for a nice and extra spicy chili)\\n4 cloves garlic, chopped\\n2 cans red kidney beans\\n3 cans fire-roasted tomatoes 42 ounces, or use equivalent fresh\\n2 tablespoons chili powder - I like to use a blend of ancho and guajillo powder, but use your favorite blend, or try this homemade chili powder blend\\n1 7- ounce can chipotles in adobo sauce - use half the can for a milder chipotle flavor\\n1 teaspoon freshly ground cumin\\n1 teaspoon red chili flakes\\nSalt and pepper to taste\\nFOR SERVING: Sliced roasted jalapenos, spicy chili flakes, fresh chopped parsley, or cilantro\\n\\nGET THE FULL RECIPE: https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/\\n\\nYOU MAY ALSO LIKE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pl_M4_axwRI\\n\\nSUBSCRIBE \\u25ba https://www.youtube.com/@ChiliPepperMadness?sub_confirmation=1\\n\\nCHECK OUT ALL OF MY BOLD AND ZESTY RECIPES \\u25ba https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLCEFD77D654F1F737\\n\\nGET YOUR COPY OF ONE OF MY COOKBOOKS \\u25ba https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/chili-pepper-cookbooks/ \\n\\nSHOP: https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/shop/ \\n\\nFOLLOW ME ON: \\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/chilipeppermadness \\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/jalapenomadness \\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/chilipeppermadness/ \\nPinterest: https://www.pinterest.com/chilipeppermadness/ \\nWebsite: https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/\\n\\nI had so much fun making this! What other videos would you like to see?\\n-Mike\\n\\n#chili #chipotle #chilirecipe #spicyfood #spicyfoods\", \"uploadDate\": \"2020-01-13T16:22:46+00:00\", \"duration\": \"PT6M25S\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4KuWtDR_XV0/hqdefault.jpg\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/embed/4KuWtDR_XV0?feature=oembed\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4KuWtDR_XV0\", \"@type\": \"VideoObject\"}, \"recipeYield\": [\"8\"], \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT80M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 tablespoon olive oil\", \"1.5 pound ground turkey or ground beef (I\\u2019m using a combination of both)\", \"1  large onion chopped\", \"1  jalapeno pepper (chopped)\", \"1  poblano pepper (chopped)\", \"1  hot chili pepper (chopped (for a spicier version \\u2013 try a habanero or ghost pepper \\u2013 optional for a nice and extra spicy chili))\", \"4 cloves garlic chopped\", \"2  cans red kidney beans\", \"3  cans fire roasted tomatoes (42 ounces, or use equivalent fresh)\", \"2 tablespoons chili powder\", \"1 7- ounce can chipotles in adobo sauce (use half the can for a milder chipotle flavor)\", \"1 teaspoon freshly ground cumin\", \"1 teaspoon red chili flakes\", \"Salt and pepper to taste\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat the oil in a large pot to medium-high heat and add the ground turkey (or beef), onion and peppers. Cook them down about 10 minutes, or until the meat is cooked through and the vegetables are softened.\", \"name\": \"Meat\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-0\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add the garlic and cook another minute, stirring.\", \"name\": \"Garlic\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-1\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"If using fresh tomatoes, chop them and add them to the pot. Cook about 10 minutes to let them break down. If using canned fire roasted tomatoes, just add them to the pot and go to the next step.\", \"name\": \"Tomatoes\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-2\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add the remaining ingredients and give it all a good stir.\", \"name\": \"Stir\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-3\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Reduce the heat and cook the chili on low heat for at least 1 hour to let the flavors develop, stirring every now and then. Adjust for seasonings if you wish. Alternatively, you can transfer everything to a slow cooker or crock pot at this stage and cook on high for 1-2 hours, or on low for 3-4 hours, until the flavors develop to your preference.\", \"name\": \"Simmer\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-4\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Serve in bowls with your favorite fixin\\u2019s.\", \"name\": \"Serve\", \"url\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#wprm-recipe-18366-step-0-5\"}], \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\", \"ratingCount\": \"10\"}, \"recipeCategory\": [\"Main Course\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"keywords\": \"chili, chipotle, jalapeno, one pot, poblano, recipe, spicy\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"151 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"9 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"21 g\", \"fatContent\": \"4 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"1 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"47 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"442 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"4 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"3 g\", \"servingSize\": \"1 serving\"}, \"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#recipe\", \"isPartOf\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/#article\"}, \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://www.chilipeppermadness.com/recipes/chipotle-chili/\"}]}"}
{"recipe_name": "Philly Cheesesteaks", "yields": "4 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT45M"}, "ingredients": ["2 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil, divided", "2 green peppers, seeds and ribs removed,&nbsp;thinly sliced", "2 red peppers, seeds and ribs removed,&nbsp;thinly sliced", "1 large yellow onion, sliced", "Kosher salt", "1 1/2 lb. sirloin steak, thinly sliced", "Freshly ground black pepper", "8 slices provolone", "4 hoagie rolls"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add bell peppers and onion; season with salt. Cook, stirring often, until caramelized, 12 to 15 minutes. Transfer bell peppers and onion to a plate."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In same skillet over medium-high heat, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Cook steak, turning occasionally, until desired degree of doneness, about 5 minutes; season with salt and pepper."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Return veggies to skillet and toss to combine with steak. Top with provolone. Cover and cook until cheese is melted, about 3 minutes more."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Divide cheesesteak mixture among rolls and serve."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-index-64de7f154d853.jpg?crop=0.502xw:1.00xh;0.0112xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2017-06-30T19:50:00Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Philly Cheesesteaks\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-index-64de7f154d853.jpg?crop=0.502xw:1.00xh;0.0112xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-index-64de7f154d853.jpg?crop=0.502xw:1.00xh;0.0112xw,0&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-