elized onions, and melted cheese is unmatched.\", \"duration\": \"PT56S\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://glimmer.hearstapps.com/amp.html?embedId=242e3a39-2e91-4d2e-bb62-663bcbb7ae11\", \"name\": \"No Trip To Philly Required To Enjoy This Ridiculously Good Cheesesteak\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-index-64de7f154d853.jpg?crop=0.8891277732986951xw:1xh;center,top\", \"uploadDate\": \"2023-10-10T17:58:24.261752Z\"}, \"author\": {\"name\": \"Lena Abraham\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/author/17077/lena-abraham/\", \"@type\": \"Person\", \"description\": \"<p>Lena Abraham is a freelance contributor with Delish, and was formerly Senior Food Editor, where she developed and styled recipes for video and photo, and also stayed on top of current food trends. She\\u2019s been working in the food industry for over 10 years, and will argue that the best fish tacos in the world are made in New York. Don\\u2019t @ her.</p>\", \"jobTitle\": \"Contributor\", \"image\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/846121db-9644-42e0-a4fd-cf5d105bfdf9_1576786748.file\", \"email\": \"Lena.Abraham@hearst.com\", \"sameAs\": []}, \"name\": \"Philly Cheesesteaks\", \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT0S\", \"totalTime\": \"PT45M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"2 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil, divided\", \"2 green peppers, seeds and ribs removed,&nbsp;thinly sliced\", \"2 red peppers, seeds and ribs removed,&nbsp;thinly sliced\", \"1 large yellow onion, sliced\", \"Kosher salt\", \"1 1/2 lb. sirloin steak, thinly sliced\", \"Freshly ground black pepper\", \"8 slices provolone\", \"4 hoagie rolls\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a large skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add bell peppers and onion; season with salt. Cook, stirring often, until caramelized, 12 to 15 minutes. Transfer bell peppers and onion to a plate.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In same skillet over medium-high heat, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Cook steak, turning occasionally, until desired degree of doneness, about 5 minutes; season with salt and pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Return veggies to skillet and toss to combine with steak. Top with provolone. Cover and cook until cheese is melted, about 3 minutes more.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Divide cheesesteak mixture among rolls and serve.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"4 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [], \"recipeCategory\": [\"Super Bowl\", \"weeknight meals\", \"dinner\"], \"description\": \"The combination of thinly sliced ribeye, jammy caramelized onions, and melted cheese makes these classic Philly cheesesteaks iconic sandwiches. \", \"keywords\": \"homemade philly cheesesteaks, philly cheesesteak recipe, cheesesteak recipe, easy weeknight dinner recipe, how to make philly cheesesteak, sub sandwich recipe, \", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.3, \"reviewCount\": 10, \"worstRating\": 1, \"bestRating\": 5}, \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \" 771 Calories\", \"fatContent\": \"48 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"21 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"171 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"994 mg\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"26 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"4 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"6 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"53 g\"}, \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Beef Pot Pie", "yields": ["6"], "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT150M", "total": "PT175M"}, "ingredients": ["1 pound sirloin steak, cubed", "salt and ground black pepper to taste", "1 (14 ounce) can beef broth", "3 large carrots, diced", "3 potatoes, cubed", "1 cup frozen green peas, thawed", "3 tablespoons cornstarch", "0.33333334326744 cup water", "2 (9 inch) refrigerator pie crusts"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/G74K2P01eN-876iwTKF8bv2B01A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-1-BG-4331-94127d4efabf4c8da0a37163a55e2bc5.jpg"}], "text": "Gather all ingredients."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/81rwcpVjSJQ0dMOp4hVLMX1GY4I=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-3-BG-4356-0ab125dd75e24b499a2510855413d5c3.jpg"}], "text": "Brown pieces of meat on all sides in a saucepan over medium heat. Pour in some water to almost cover. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer until meat is tender and falls apart easily; 2 to 3 hours."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/i0U1NVit9Vgh0UsMF8bq_1whHiE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-4-BG-4517-eb28f0b686a04d68b374897d96f332ad.jpg"}], "text": "Transfer meat to a large mixing bowl. Shred the meat slightly and add salt and pepper to taste."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/r_OEFL-4dYVX__0qemfDNTOWIdg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-5-BG-4369-69cd0412699c489a9a2633b4086e75f6.jpg"}], "text": "Meanwhile, in another 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, pour in beef broth and add carrots and potatoes. Cook until almost tender; 15 to 20 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/_n1Q9YLAuzEhIeKcBxSYI6Jqtpk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-6-BG-4519-18efab9c87724f5292f4be8a2834207a.jpg"}], "text": "When carrots and potatoes are done, transfer to the large mixing bowl with the beef; leaving the liquid in the pan. Combine peas with carrots, potatoes, and beef."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/aJeVN2aKA8Welic6uw6Hgp_t2FQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-7-BG-4384-cde9210a1f7a432a9674af0c34e69b2b.jpg"}], "text": "Dissolve cornstarch with 1/3 cup water. Pour into the saucepan with beef broth, stirring constantly. Bring to a simmer and reduce heat; cook for 5 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/VdQ28_xLZFFieE76t8yihT0ze8Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-9-BG-4533-35647c207b4649e2be0ee3de4117a22e.jpg"}], "text": "Line a 9-inch pie plate with one of the pie crusts following the package directions. Place the beef mixture into the pie crust. Pour the gravy over the top of the mixture, then cover with the other pie crust."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/XNMXAC5nb5rX04yPlhpT8JrMyFI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-beauty-4x3-BG-4644-d4d01ddf022e480e9a69ac143e732e5e.jpg"}], "text": "Bake in the preheated oven until the crust is golden brown; about 25 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes before serving."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Beef Pot Pie\", \"datePublished\": \"2000-10-16T23:17:20.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-05-16T10:13:37.648-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stephanie\"}], \"description\": \"This beef pot pie is delicious. Cubed beef, carrots, potatoes, and peas are combined with a homemade gravy and baked in between flaky pie crusts.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/XNMXAC5nb5rX04yPlhpT8JrMyFI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-beauty-4x3-BG-4644-d4d01ddf022e480e9a69ac143e732e5e.jpg\", \"height\": 1125, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/rdb6kMjv-ma1DlVvV.mp4\", \"description\": \"AR1146\", \"duration\": \"PT6M\", \"name\": \"Beef Pot Pie III\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/rdb6kMjv/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2021-07-14T13:23:44.748-04:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Beef Pot Pie\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.4\", \"ratingCount\": \"253\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT150M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"527 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"58 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"33 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"4 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"20 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"5 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"661 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"4 g\", \"fatContent\": \"24 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 pound sirloin steak, cubed\", \"salt and ground black pepper to taste\", \"1 (14 ounce) can beef broth\", \"3 large carrots, diced\", \"3 potatoes, cubed\", \"1 cup frozen green peas, thawed\", \"3 tablespoons cornstarch\", \"0.33333334326744 cup water\", \"2 (9 inch) refrigerator pie crusts\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/G74K2P01eN-876iwTKF8bv2B01A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-1-BG-4331-94127d4efabf4c8da0a37163a55e2bc5.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Gather all ingredients.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/81rwcpVjSJQ0dMOp4hVLMX1GY4I=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-3-BG-4356-0ab125dd75e24b499a2510855413d5c3.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Brown pieces of meat on all sides in a saucepan over medium heat. Pour in some water to almost cover. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer until meat is tender and falls apart easily; 2 to 3 hours.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/i0U1NVit9Vgh0UsMF8bq_1whHiE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-4-BG-4517-eb28f0b686a04d68b374897d96f332ad.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Transfer meat to a large mixing bowl. Shred the meat slightly and add salt and pepper to taste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/r_OEFL-4dYVX__0qemfDNTOWIdg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-5-BG-4369-69cd0412699c489a9a2633b4086e75f6.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Meanwhile, in another 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, pour in beef broth and add carrots and potatoes. Cook until almost tender; 15 to 20 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/_n1Q9YLAuzEhIeKcBxSYI6Jqtpk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-6-BG-4519-18efab9c87724f5292f4be8a2834207a.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"When carrots and potatoes are done, transfer to the large mixing bowl with the beef; leaving the liquid in the pan. Combine peas with carrots, potatoes, and beef.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/aJeVN2aKA8Welic6uw6Hgp_t2FQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-7-BG-4384-cde9210a1f7a432a9674af0c34e69b2b.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Dissolve cornstarch with 1/3 cup water. Pour into the saucepan with beef broth, stirring constantly. Bring to a simmer and reduce heat; cook for 5 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/VdQ28_xLZFFieE76t8yihT0ze8Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-step-9-BG-4533-35647c207b4649e2be0ee3de4117a22e.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Line a 9-inch pie plate with one of the pie crusts following the package directions. Place the beef mixture into the pie crust. Pour the gravy over the top of the mixture, then cover with the other pie crust.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/XNMXAC5nb5rX04yPlhpT8JrMyFI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/22851-beef-pot-pie-III-DDMFS-beauty-4x3-BG-4644-d4d01ddf022e480e9a69ac143e732e5e.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Bake in the preheated oven until the crust is golden brown; about 25 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"6\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT175M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"All recipes from this site are fantastic. Use All receipts when i don't feel like looking up in cook book.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ginny Evans\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"minaayindra\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"There were a few things about this pie that made me downgrade it to three stars. Number one, it takes an extraordinary length of time to make, something I really don't have that much of. Second, it is dry from lack of gravy. Perhaps doubling or tripling thegravy woud have helped that, I don't know. Also, if you are using the frozen peas, don't let them thaw. The ingredients you are adding them to are hot enough to melt them on the spot so save yourself mushy peas and skip that step. On the other hand, the beef was incredibly tender and the veggies were tasty... but I can't justify spending this much time on a recipe when I could make it more quickly with a few pre-made items from the store.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"HillSlug98239\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used this recipe as a template and made a few changes that suited me. I had a 1-pound crossrib roast. I diced it &amp; simmered it. (I didn't shred the meat.) I added the vegetables to the pot about 30 minutes before it was done, and I added a few sprigs of fresh rosemary &amp; tarragon. I drained this and used the reserved liquid instead of beef broth. I made pie crust instead of store bought. (I had the time.) Based on the reviews, it sounds like most of us have used this recipe as a starting point &amp; made adjustments that work for us. I'll follow this recipe again as it's definitely a good starting point.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Avery\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I feel obliged to make one constructive criticism: Why would you boil beef chunks in water, and then throw away the water, with all that delicious beef essence? I boiled the beef in the broth itself (in a pressure cooker, requiring only 45 minutes), and used the browning fond as well. That's where the flavor is. Having said that, it's not fair for me to rate this recipe, given all the changes I made (added vegetables and garlic, etc). I'll just say that my version was excellent. And I used guidance for technique, amounts, timing and temperature from this recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very tasty! I used leftover venison shoulder and it was a hit! Will definitely be making again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"tedleyt32\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this with some beef brisket that I canned. It was delicious. I will make it again with some canned beef, canned potatoes and canned carrots that I made.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Becky Tierney-Fisher\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very tasty and pretty easy to make\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Deb McCleary\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Not very beefy tasting very bland, it could have used a packet of beef gravy mix for more flavor. I made a roux using butter and flour for a thicker gravy. Not sure I will make this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Vickie effinger\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made a couple of changes to the recipe, I will let you know how it turns out and what I changed, and if the changes worked out.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bdub Holmes\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My first savory pie. Easy to follow instructions and it came out delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"hinesmarie2\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It came out perfectly..my family loved it..Thank You.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sue E Troutt-Reynolds\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was super easy and I even made my homemade crust..\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"My Recipes\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I followed the recipe with just a few changes. I added a cup of diced onion, a little worschire sauce to meat and used jar gravy. This is a great cold weather comfort food and really filling! I will make it again! But I will cut back on the potatoes and use more meat. But it is definitely a great start to a recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jennifer Reynolds\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Because I used left over pot roast with potatoes and green beans, I found that it was too much gravy, it ran out of the crust when cut. But since this is my first time making any pot pie.. I am thrilled at how good it tasted! I made gluten free crusts using King Arthur 1:1 flour. Makes a wonderful crust.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mina Y\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was delicious and incredibly easy to make! We enjoyed it so much that I have remade it more than once. You can play with the vegetables that you put in- so far I've found a simple can of mixed vegetables and the frozen peas creates the easiest preparation and the best tasting pie. As it says, salt to taste... I haven't needed any at all so be careful before you shake a lot on. Love it. Thanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Karen Lindower\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is a keeper. My husband couldn't stop raving about it. He kept calling it comfort food. I made it as written, with the addition of onions, celery, and minced garlic, just because we like that combination and I rarely make a dinner without onions. However, I'm sure it would be fine without my additions. The beef broth and carnstarch made a tasty gravy for the filling. I don't think it needs a gravy packet as some reviewers have used. I did make sure to season with salt and pepper each step of the way, meat, potatoes, and gravy, and it turned out perfectly seasoned, needing no adjustment in seasoning at the table. Great recipe. My husband will be requesting this quite often.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Angela\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Was delicious. I did cook it about 10m longer than the recipe stated. The crust still could have cooked longer. Might wack up the heat 25 degrees next time. I will make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"rayann bois\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Needed a little more spices and a thicker gravy\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"marian\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made this last night with a few changes....used ground venison, a jar of chicken gravy with some beef bullion mixed in and adjusted quantities of vegies. It was very good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"karen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made a chicken pot pie and this beef pot pie in the same night. This pie was awesome but next time I will use less peas. They were overpowering. Other than that my family of 7 loved both.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jim\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The recipe turned out really dry. The taste was good but I would have preferred more of a gravy consistency. The next time I make it I will increase the liquid by at least 50 percent.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Scott Headley\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"we made this recipe exactly as is directed and it had really great flavor but it was too dry. next time i'll double the gravy recipe and put it on the bottom and the top of the vegetable beef mixture. Otherwise perfect and delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Gugelhupf\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used cooked prime rib I had cut up and frozen. I browned the pieces after thawing. Worked great for this recipe! And used Trader Joe\\u2019s pie crust. Yum! The vegetable proportions seemed huge, so I used one carrot, two medium Yukon golds, and a half cup of peas.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pam Martello\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious and very easy. Substituted corn for peas (husband won't touch a pea). He loved it. Will definitely make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bonnie Edgerly\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"very much enjoyed it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Derek\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this recipe with a few of the changes recommended by others. Always enjoy reading recommended changes submitted by people who have made it so you can adjust to your tastes. Those who think others should not suggest their ideas should not read them.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ba r\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"way too many mods to be considered a useful recipe. did not shred the meat. what a ridiculous idea. cooked the cubes for about an hour and they were fork tender. cooked the vegetables one type at a time in the liquid the beef was cooked in and added with broth to cover. when they were done, all three were seasoned together. enough broth was added to the liquid to make 2 cups and then the cornstarch mixture was added to that. the pillsbury crust has to cook at 425 for something like 45 minutes. c'mon, you're not even close with that 25 min at 350. i was going to give this recipe 2 stars but after typing this it's easy to knock this down to 1\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lisa Mitchall-Zuk\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Need to mix the broth/gravy to beef &amp; veg. Also, gravy not thick enough. I would use regular gravy method of: melt fat in pan (butter), add flour, stir until browned. THEN add the broth and simmer until thickened. I just added the broth with cornstarch (that hadn't thickened enough... even after adding more cornstarch) and it was great! Also added some onions &amp; celery and only used top crust. Excellent base recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Catherine Mottier Sylva\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Awesome! Great for leftover pot roast!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MichelleIrace\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe, as listed, is good but not great. It is a good recipe to use as a base to be able to customize the pot pie though!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"skiducious\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was really good, whole family pleased and so filling we had some leftover (2adult and 2 teen girls).\\nI bought pie crusts they were a little sweet to our taste so home made next time great recipe though with great results.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jan W\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious! I used leftover chuck roast with gravy from that. I pre-boiled 1/4 c. chopped onion &amp; a few sliced white mushrooms in the gravy. If the gravy is not thick enough add some water mixed with cornstarch and stir it in when it boils. Pour it in the pie dish with the meat &amp; veggies and follow the recipe the rest of the way.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bunky\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a puff pastry for the top. Cooked the beef for 4 hours in a slow cooker.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shirl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made as per recipe and was very good....little bit runny though....maybe should have left sit a bit longer\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rab\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I pretty much followed the directions a written but used venison instead of beef. There is not enough gravy so next time I will make twice the amount, it was a little dry but still tasty.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Candace Walton\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used this recipe as my guide, but had to make adjustments due to time and money constraints. I was able to use frozen peas and carrots (99 cents) and leftover prime rib from a holiday dinner. Fundamentally the same concepts as the recipe. Thank you for posting.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jean Osbon\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Katrina Mckee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I carmelized some onions and added it to the beef broth when I was reducing it for gravy. It was delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jacqueline Rayyan\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this recipe exactly as it states. Overall it was great. It was a bit dry. Not sure what I can do for next time. Maybe not add cornstarch part at all and just cover with beef broth. Or maybe use a jar of gravy and top-it with that. If anyone had a suggestion on how to make it more saucy, I would appreciate that.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"anco314\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"me and my husband made this beef pot pie was really good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nanci Hollis Perez\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My family and I loved this. I tweaked it a little by adding some chopped onion, garlic powder , cayenne pepper, ginger. Also, I omitted the corn starch and use a dry pack of McCormick Brown gravy mix as the thickener. \\nYum!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"De\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the second pot pie I've made from this site. My husband definitely prefers this one. The only thing I added was some garlic while cooking the meat. This is a great recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jeremy Oesterreicher\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I took advantage of a cold weekend to make this. With one little twist, venison was used instead of the beef. It was a little time consuming but all I had to do was tend the fire and watch some football I made do.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tammy Dufresne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this using some left over prime rib from Christmas. I used a frozen vegetable bag that had carrots, peas, corn, and green beans. It's convenient and adds great color. I found this recipe to be good and it's a very filling meal. I love pot pies for the convienence and getting another meal out of left overs. I'll make it again but next time I'm going to add more seasoning because it seemed to be missing the pop of flavor I was looking for.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Gary T\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added fresh rosemary to the beef and 1/2 cup marsala wine to the gravy mix, otherwise stuck the recipe. A little dry, could've used more of the gravy in the pie. Otherwise, it turned out excellent!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tiffany Marie Lusk\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was pretty good, definitely needed more gravy. It was a little dry which is why I have it 4 stars.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Layne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"On this occasion, I was using up left overs, so I eliminated some of the precooking steps. Otherwise I followed the recipe completely and it came it out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Doris Tucker\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Amazing! I used leftover beef roast and a bag of frozen peas and carrots. My family loved it so much they requested again it two days later!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Granny4075\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy and delicious. I did start with leftover roast though.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kd Pascarella\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Started out making this exactly as the recipe said and it would have been very bland. Added a bay leaf to the simmering meat, and some thyme and rosemary.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michele\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was very good, but I did make some changes. I browned 1# hamburger with a chopped onion, and garlic. After browning, I sprinkled the cornstarch on the meat/onion mixture, then slowly added the broth and some Worcestershire sauce. I then added a can of mushrooms and a bag of frozen mixed vegetables as well as 3 (boiled/baked/microwaved) potatoes (diced). I mixed it all together with S &amp; P, garlic powder, and a bit of seasoned salt. I then dumped it in a crust ( I prefer homemade crust), sprinkled a bit of flour over the top, and then put on the top crust. While eating dinner, my husband asked me if I'd written down what I'd done for this one so we can have it again! It was a hit!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sondra Albright\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I will definitely make again! Great! I'd add some onion next time..I also used rib eye steak! Was done faster, &amp; super tender!..thanks Steph!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tiffypoo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I tweaked this recipe a lot. I would give my version 5 stars as the original lacked flavour. There was enough filling for 2 pies but not enough gravy, although I doubled the beef broth. I would also simmer the beef in a concoction like braised short ribs rather than water. I added a lot of seasoning, including Emeril's Essence, Italian seasoning, parsley, paprika, Montreal steak spice. I added pur\\u00e9ed onion and garlic to the broth to enhance the flavour. This had a bit of heat. Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Erika O\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"we added red wine to the ingredients. delicious\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Starlove3\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"No. I was very disappointed with my pot pie. I think IF I attempted this I would do the gravy packets like others said they did. What a waste of money...\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"marlee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a great way to use up my leftovers.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Danielle Wynne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made but changed a few things. I cooked stew beef in pressure cooker only took 25 mins. I used diced potatoes , and frozen carrots, corn, green beans and peas. Baked for 45 mins. Baked on cookie sheet. It was excellent.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Corrine\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I liked this a lot, but added some italian seasoning and garlic and onions to give it a little kick. Overall- really delicious- I will be making this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"nwilburn23\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great Recipe, Everything was good just wish there would have been more gravy in the pie. Next time I will increase the gravy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pamela\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Always looking for new recipes. I loved this one with all fresh ingredients and not all frozen, but big ingredient I love is cinnamon. Its been a staple of my beef pot pie, and my mother's and my grandmother's, for years. Cinnamon really enhances the flavor of the beef. I personally also like onion. But otherwise kudos to this recipe. And to the reviewers that made so many changes that it was no longer the recipe posted - just please stop. Post your recipe separately.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"miobertolo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used lean ground beef and I bought the individual size pie shells. I was able to make 24 servings in a short time. They freeze well!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tgviolet\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made this last night and it was really good. However, next time I believe I would prefer mixing the meat/veggie mixture into the gravy before filling the pie shell.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KSills\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a left over roast and gravy for the meat and added garlic and extra onion. Made homemade crust too. Turned out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"phnxrth\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made pie crusts from scratch, used med. rare prime rib left over from Christmas, cut into small pieces. I saut\\u00e9ed the vegetables in 2 tblsps. butter before adding broth and I also benefited by the user comment to use 1 packet gravy mix and 1 cup water. Instead of the cornstarch I added 2 tblsps. flour to the vegetables before the broth and combined it well. I added 2 tblsps. red wine and 1 tsp. herbs provence, baked in a 10 inch pie pan at 375 for 40 minutes. This made 4 generous servings. Would definitely make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mary P.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I agree with Frammel Pie that a true rating should be on the exact way a recipe is written on this sight, BEFORE you make your own alterations to it. That being said, as is, this recipe is just okay. It needs onion and herbs. To bland.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sabrina Roschbach\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"SO GOOD! My family loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"pulpeux\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was pretty good. The only confusing thing was how much gravy you should have. My potatoes and carrots absorbed a lot of liquid while cooking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"simplynewt\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very Good Recipe But The Finished Product Turned Out A Little Dry For Me. Overall It Was A Very Tasty Dish Though And Will Make This Again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Margaret Becker\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Hi Stephanie,\\nI never knew how to make a beef pot pie. I made your recipe and it was terrific! I didn't change a single thing. You're a good cook, dearie!\\nMaggie\\nP.S. This is one of my favorite recipes and I make it often...\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"CrawfordMomof2\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This turned out really well. The only suggestions I have are to double the gravy (tastes great but just not enough) and maybe add some onion. This was very good and very easy to make.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"etholijack\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really tasty. Used the slow cooker instead of the stove top but used the same ingredients. I browned the meat first, put it in the slow cooker then mixed it with the cornstarch salt and pepper. I topped it with the carrots And potatoes and poured 20 ounces of beef broth on top. Let it cook for a few hours then put it in the pie shell and baked for 25 minutes at 350 degrees. It was a hit.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Janice Davidson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I had a whole ribeye steak left over from yesterday's BBQ dinner and looked for a recipe to use it in today. The idea of a beef pot pie sounded fabulous so I printed this one off! I thought that a beef gravy sounded tastier instead of corn starch and beef broth; just a personal taste. So what I did was use a beef gravy package! I steamed some garden fresh chopped carrots and onion, small cubed potatoes and sliced celery. I salted and peppered those veggies once they were tender. Then I cubed up the BBQ'd ribeye which had already been seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic powder when it was BBQ'd. I placed the chopped steak and the steamed veggies in a bowl and mixed them up and then after stirring the dried, crushed thyme into the hot gravy, I put the veggies and steak into the deep dish pie plate and poured the gravy on top and then placed the pie crust on top. Baked as in the recipe at 400F for 35 minutes. Let it rest for 20 minutes when done. The flavors were scrumptious and a five star, for sure. I don't normally change recipes and then rate them but I just wanted to share this outcome as it was just so good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Anne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was really bland even after adding garlic powder sage salt-and-pepper\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kelly McNulty\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I started with leftover pot roast and potatoes and carrots that I cooked with it. I pre-cooked the bottom crust. I used 8 oz. of the pot roast, 1C carrots, 1C potatoes, and 1 C peas. I used a combination of chicken gravy I had and some beef soup base and a bit of leftover pot roast mushroom gravy with a little corn starch and had about 3C thickened gravy. Everything had already been well-seasoned when first cooked with garlic, bay leaves, thyme, salt and pepper, so I just heated everything on the stove to a slow boil, dumped it in the crust, added the top crust, and baked for 45 minutes. It's much quicker to throw this together from leftovers, and it is very delicious!!! It's also very easy to change based on what's on hand or individual preferences.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KATKOMP\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a blade roast and while it was simmering I added 2 bay leaves. I didn't use the beef broth or frozen peas because I didn't have either on hand so I used onion, celery and carrots. With a little salt and pepper I found it was quite tasty. My hubby ate as a stew for two days and loved it then I made pie crust and made meat pies for him to have when I work afternoons.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"thecritic\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Good\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bebe\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used leftover roast so I was able to skip a step. Added some rosemary to the mix. I did have trouble getting my crust to brown enough. I would probably make this again if I have leftover beef but to me, then end result doesn't justify the trouble of starting completely from scratch. So, this won't be a ''go to\\\" recipe for me.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Patty\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This had a good home made taste and my whole family liked it. I added worcheshire, sirracha and some chopped onion and asparagus.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michael Nelson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Family loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Karen Wagner\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this. Did not use the canned beef broth. Since the roast is getting cooked in water, it's easy to make gravy from this rather than canned broth. I threw in bay leaves, some dry onions and garlic (the last 2 cook down to mush, pretty much, but help flavor the meat as it simmered.) When I made the gravy, I removed the bay leaves. You could strain the liquid and remove fat, if you like. Figure a thin gravy ratio of 1 TBL cornstarch to thicken each cup of roast-cooking water you'd like to turn into gravy. \\n\\nOnce the gravy thickens and I salt/pepper/season it to suit us, I combine with the meat and vegetables so I can make sure I have enough gravy before putting it in the shells. I follow another poster's suggestion to make from-scratch crusts and to pre-bake the bottom shell. I like to make this as a multiple-meal dish (ie Once a Month Cooking.) It can be done without crust if you can't be bothered, or with biscuit for a top crust. \\n\\nWhen freezing this for later meals, I PRECOOK until crust just starts to brown before freezing. This means that I only have to bake until hot (165 degrees in center) before serving. This also allows me to use the dish from frozen if I need to. There is some time penalty from frozen, but nothing like it would be if it had to COOK as well as thaw in the oven. Thawing first works better, but life is busy. \\n\\nNote: a layer of parchment paper under your bottom crust will allow you to remove the frozen pie from your baking dish for storage.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Buzzingcat\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My husband gave this two thumbs up and said he would like to have it again...soon. I used cooked, cubed london broil that I had in the freezer so it only took a little over an hour to prepare and cook the pot pie. I don't like peas so I left them out and added one stalk of celery and three green onions, sliced. I also reduced the cornstarch and added three tablespoons of brown gravy mix to help thicken the broth and make it richer. It is a very adaptable recipe that allows you to add and delete vegetables to your taste. It was perfect comfort food on a cold, snowy day.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"S.E.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a good start for a beef pot pie. I will however experiment with different herbs to try to make it taste more like Swanson's hungry man's beef pot pie...my favorite.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Deborah Doyle\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only thing I changed was the crust. Made my own. I used the home made crust from a chicken pot pie recipe and used it, nothing like home made pie crust !\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"tracey\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was really good.I will be making this again.Did us a box of veg broth mixed in with the beef broth.They were both opened so I wanted to use it.I also added onions,as my family loves onions and added garlic powder to the beef.With the veggies I also added frozen mix veggies as I only had a few left.good way of using up ingreds.I will be making this more often.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"nancy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"EXCELLENT!!! I did add some extra seasonings based on other people's suggestion. I added sage, thyme, rosemary, celery salt, &amp; garlic powder to the gravy mixture. \\nI also recomend using 2-3 times the beef broth so you have something to make the gravy with. My first can of broth was almost gone by the time my carrots and potatoes where done coooking. \\nI highly recommend this recipe as everyone in my family loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"missrochester\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Im only giving 4 stars because i added alot more seasoning's! and i used a bag of frozen mixed veggies and used stew meat this was simple to prepare and Tasted amazing!! I made my own pie crust from this site!! A keeper in my house!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Shar Pei\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is awesome! My whole family loved it. The only thing was that it was kind of bland tasting. Next time I am going to add garlic. I did frozen mixed veggies instead of the veggies listed, and it was still great.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Grow Family Love\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"LOVE! LOVE! LOVE!! Worth the time to put into this. Made this with homemade pie crust for the next day! Daddy had to eat some right away, he just couldn't resist! :)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KellyK\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was very good and delivered an excellent meal! I used leftover prime rib from our Christmas dinner, so I did not have to go through all the meat prep - I would probably only make this using some sort of meat leftovers. I also added 1/2 yellow onion, diced very finely and did not add the carrots to the broth until the last 5 minutes so that they did not get too mushy. A full cup of peas was a bit much (and I like peas!)\\nI used 16oz water and 2 boullion cubes rather than beef broth and did find that I needed to add more liquid when I made my gravy (I actually ended up just adding some leftover gravy from Christmas dinner).\\nThe bake time ended up being more like an hour; when I make it again I will raise the heat just a bit and aim for a bake time of about 45 minutes.\\nAll in all, really, really good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"walkingfit\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a delicious beef pie. I had leftover pot roast and au jus that I put to use instead of the sirloin steak and canned beef broth. And since there are only 2 of us at home I cut the recipe in half, cooked it in a small casserole dish and only used a top crust. This is a real keeper for using up leftover roast beef.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Topaz1948\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have made chicken, turkey &amp; veggie pot pies since I was about 10, but never a traditional \\\"homemade\\\" from scratch beef pot pie. I've made Shepard's pie, enchilada pie, and every kind of quiche imaginable (including about 8 original quiche recipes, like my Reuben quiche). I already had a good idea about what to put in a beef pot pie, &amp; how to season it to our taste, but wasn't sure about how to thicken the gravy so it isn't too thin or to thick. I just found this site last week, when looking for a recipe for a Barbie Doll Cake. Everyone was so helpful I figured I could get some info here. This recipe was most helpful regarding thickening, so I based my beef pot pie on this procedure. Admittedly, I also added some veggies I like, like celery &amp; mushrooms, and more seasonings, but it came out perfect with respect to the sauce, and we all loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Andrea\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was very good. I wanted to cut down on the time, so instead of boiling the meat for 2-3 hours, I browned with onions and garlic and then boiled for 30-45 minutes. It wasn't fall apart tender, but got it done much sooner. I also used canned potatoes and carrots to cut down on the prep time of the veges. When making the gravy, I added onion powder, garlic salt, salt and pepper. I baked for 25 minutes, that wasn't nearly long enough for crust to get crisp, so had to double the time. Overall the finished product was very good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"angelkellymarie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a really easy recipe, though it takes a long time to make. Took me almost 5 hours total. But it was DELICIOUS!!! My husband had seconds so I know it was really good because he hardly ever has seconds. I did make a few modifications: used a beef bouillon cube when simmering the steak and added some red cooking wine. Then when the carrots and potatoes were cooking, I added garlic, onion, thyme and fresh rosemary. I had to add some water to the gravy mixture because there wasn't much left after cooking everything else. I might use 2 cans of beef broth next time. The one thing that annoyed me a little was that it made a lot, way too much for 1 pie pan. So I used a bigger dish, which the pie crust didn't exactly fit but I stretched it out to fit. Baked it for 50 mins and it was perfect. Definitely will be making this one again; it's a keeper!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Frammel Pie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Why do people CONSTANTLY rate their OWN version of these recipes 5 stars?! The entire point is to give feedback to the person who created/posted it. If you're going to change it up then don't bother rating it at all, because that's not accurate. I made this recipe EXACTLY AS STATED and it turned out great! Kudos to you for coming up with something tasty!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lynn\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was simply AWESOME! I cheated and had leftover prepared beef pot roast from Costco (Mortons) and used it in place of the first two ingredients. Everyone loved it and you can add whatever vegetables you prefer or have in the fridge!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mommyluvs2cook\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious! I loved the way the steak was cooked to get it really tender. I did have to keep adding water but I used a VERY big wide pan. I used that pan because I had decided I would just throw all the veggies (except the peas) in the last 15 minutes or so of the beef cooking to make everything easier and quicker. Worked like a charm ;) Of course like all my pot pies I can never seem to get it to look pie-ish on the plate lol! Unless I completely cool it down I see it impossible! Anyway, my family REALLY enjoyed this (especially the hubs) so thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Joycegl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was good, but I miss the potatoes that they use to put in the frozen pot pies so I added a can of diced potatoes and that made it perfect\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Helen S.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"just sat down to eat our beef pot pie.. and it was delious.. cooked as directed.. the only thing is oven time was to short left it in for 45 mins.. perfect..\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/22851/beef-pot-pie-iii/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/252/main-dish/savory-pies/\", \"name\": \"Savory Pie Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/2268/main-dish/savory-pies/pot-pie/\", \"name\": \"Pot Pie Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/22851/beef-pot-pie-iii/\", \"name\": \"Beef Pot Pie\"}}]}, \"reviewedBy\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Test Kitchen\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/allrecipes-test-kitchen-7553892\"}], \"lastReviewed\": \"2023-05-16T10:13:37.648-04:00\"}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Keto Fried Chicken", "yields": "6 - 8 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT1H15M"}, "ingredients": ["6 bone-in, skin-on chicken breasts (about 4 lbs.)", "Kosher salt&nbsp;", "Freshly ground black pepper", "2 large eggs", "1/2 c. heavy cream", "3/4 c. almond flour", "1 1/2 c. finely crushed pork rinds", "1/2 c. freshly grated Parmesan&nbsp;", "1 tsp. garlic powder", "1/2 tsp. paprika", "1/2 c. mayonnaise", "1 1/2 tsp. hot sauce"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat oven to 400° and line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. Pat chicken dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a shallow bowl whisk together eggs and heavy cream. In another shallow bowl, combine almond flour, pork rinds, Parmesan, garlic powder, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Working one at a time, dip chicken in egg mixture and then in almond flour mixture, pressing to coat. Place chicken on prepared baking sheet.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Bake until chicken is golden and internal temperature reaches 165°, about 45 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Meanwhile, make dipping sauce:&nbsp;In a medium bowl, combine mayonnaise and hot sauce. Add more hot sauce depending on preferred spiciness level.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Serve chicken warm with dipping sauce.&nbsp;"}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-10-21T18:24:46.614172Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Keto Fried Chicken\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.8891228070175439xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/20191011-keto-fried-chicken-delish-ehg-2642-1571677665.jpg?crop=1xw:0.8435280189423836xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29537911/keto-fried-chicken-recipe/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"http://instagram.com/delish\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/Delish/\"], \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/_assets/design-tokens/delish/static/images/logos/logo-jsonld.1396ea2.png\", \"width\": 312, \"height\": 60}, \"parentOrganization\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Hearst Corporation\"}}, \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29537911/keto-fried-chicken-recipe/\", \"isBasedOn\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29537911/keto-fried-chicken-recipe/\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-02-27T13:48:59Z EST\", \"isAcce