inely crushed pork rinds\", \"1/2 c. freshly grated Parmesan&nbsp;\", \"1 tsp. garlic powder\", \"1/2 tsp. paprika\", \"1/2 c. mayonnaise\", \"1 1/2 tsp. hot sauce\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0 and line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. Pat chicken dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a shallow bowl whisk together eggs and heavy cream. In another shallow bowl, combine almond flour, pork rinds, Parmesan, garlic powder, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Working one at a time, dip chicken in egg mixture and then in almond flour mixture, pressing to coat. Place chicken on prepared baking sheet.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bake until chicken is golden and internal temperature reaches 165\\u00b0, about 45 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Meanwhile, make dipping sauce:&nbsp;In a medium bowl, combine mayonnaise and hot sauce. Add more hot sauce depending on preferred spiciness level.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Serve chicken warm with dipping sauce.&nbsp;\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"6 - 8 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [], \"recipeCategory\": [\"gluten-free\", \"low-carb\", \"easy chicken\", \"dinner\"], \"description\": \"Don't sacrifice when it comes to comfort food.\\u00a0\", \"keywords\": \"dinner, easy chicken, gluten-free, low-carb\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.677419, \"reviewCount\": 31, \"worstRating\": 1, \"bestRating\": 5}, \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \" 844 Calories\", \"fatContent\": \"61 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"18 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"281 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"980 mg\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"3 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"2 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"1 g\", \"proteinCont