{"recipe_name": "Easy Ravioli Bake", "yields": "8", "time": {"prep": "PT0H10M", "cook": 0, "total": "PT1H10M"}, "ingredients": ["1  jar (25.5 oz) Muir Glen™ organic pasta sauce (any variety)", "1  package (25 to 27 1/2 oz) frozen cheese-filled ravioli", "2  cups shredded mozzarella cheese (8 oz)", "2  tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat oven to 350°F. Spray bottom and sides of rectangular baking dish, 13x9x2-inches, with cooking spray."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Spread 3/4 cup of the pasta sauce in baking dish. Arrange half of the frozen ravioli in single layer over sauce; top with half of the remaining pasta sauce and 1 cup of the mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers once, starting with ravioli. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Cover with foil; bake 40 minutes. Remove foil; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and hot in center. Let stand 10 minutes before serving."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"@context\": \"http://schema.org/\", \"name\": \"Easy Ravioli Bake\", \"keywords\": \"easy ravioli bake\", \"recipeCategory\": \"Entree\", \"recipeCuisine\": \"Italian\", \"image\": \"https://mojo.generalmills.com/api/public/content/itXHUQC8jkSsdaQf8K5gig_gmi_hi_res_jpeg.jpeg?v=91c83762&t=b5673970ed9e41549a020b29d456506d\", \"description\": \"If cheese ravioli is one of your go-to meals at your favorite Italian eatery, this Easy Ravioli Bake is sure to compete. Get restaurant quality at home with this no-fuss baked ravioli recipe. Only ten minutes to prep and using simple ingredients you have on hand, this baked ravioli is as easy as it gets. Using frozen ravioli means you can get right to assembling your baked ravioli for a quick, yet impressive, family dinner.\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1  jar (25.5 oz) Muir Glen\\u2122 organic pasta sauce (any variety)\", \"1  package (25 to 27 1/2 oz) frozen cheese-filled ravioli\", \"2  cups shredded mozzarella cheese (8 oz)\", \"2  tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT1H10M\", \"prepTime\": \"PT0H10M\", \"recipeYield\": \"8\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"285\", \"bestRating\": \"5\", \"worstRating\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Betty Crocker Kitchens\"}, \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat oven to 350\\u00b0F. Spray bottom and sides of rectangular baking dish, 13x9x2-inches, with cooking spray.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Spread 3/4 cup of the pasta sauce in baking dish. Arrange half of the frozen ravioli in single layer over sauce; top with half of the remaining pasta sauce and 1 cup of the mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers once, starting with ravioli. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Cover with foil; bake 40 minutes. Remove foil; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and hot in center. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.\"}], \"mainEntity\": [], \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"300 \", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"25 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"100 mg\", \"fatContent\": \"1 \", \"fiberContent\": \"2 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"16 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"7 g\", \"servingSize\": \"1 Serving\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1070 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"4 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"dateCreated\": \"02/18/2004\", \"dateModified\": \"12/28/2020\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Vegetarian Sloppy Joes", "yields": ["6"], "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT20M", "total": "PT40M"}, "ingredients": ["0.25 cup vegetable oil", "0.5 cup minced onion", "2 (8 ounce) packages tempeh", "0.5 cup minced green bell pepper", "2 cloves garlic, minced", "0.25 cup tomato sauce", "1 tablespoon vegetarian Worcestershire sauce", "1 tablespoon honey", "1 tablespoon blackstrap molasses", "0.25 teaspoon cayenne pepper", "0.25 teaspoon celery seed", "0.25 teaspoon ground cumin", "0.25 teaspoon salt", "0.5 teaspoon ground coriander", "0.5 teaspoon dried thyme", "0.5 teaspoon oregano", "0.5 teaspoon paprika", "1 pinch ground black pepper", "hamburger buns"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat oil in a deep, 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat. Cook the onion in the oil until translucent. Crumble the tempeh into the skillet; cook and stir until golden brown. Add the green pepper and garlic; cook another 2 to 3 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Stir in the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, honey, molasses, cayenne pepper, celery seed, cumin, salt, coriander, thyme, oregano, paprika, and black pepper; stir. Simmer another 10 to 15 minutes. Spoon hot onto hamburger buns to serve."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\"], \"headline\": \"Vegetarian Sloppy Joes\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-04-02T02:50:20.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2022-09-16T23:06:02.000-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Aberdeen Smith\"}], \"description\": \"Tempeh stands in for the traditional ground beef in a vegetarian version of the all-American classic sandwich.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/PY3gAfAaGLvn2BvOAHrAqJ2Rgd0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/422585-vegetarian-sloppy-joes-Alberta-Rose-4x3-1-6ed0c52f1be847acba95c8ca897fcdf9.jpg\", \"height\": 1125, \"width\": 1500}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Vegetarian Sloppy Joes\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.2\", \"ratingCount\": \"104\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT20M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"384 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"37 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"2 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"18 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"5 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"425 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"9 g\", \"fatContent\": \"20 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\", \"Lunch\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"0.25 cup vegetable oil\", \"0.5 cup minced onion\", \"2 (8 ounce) packages tempeh\", \"0.5 cup minced green bell pepper\", \"2 cloves garlic, minced\", \"0.25 cup tomato sauce\", \"1 tablespoon vegetarian Worcestershire sauce\", \"1 tablespoon honey\", \"1 tablespoon blackstrap molasses\", \"0.25 teaspoon cayenne pepper\", \"0.25 teaspoon celery seed\", \"0.25 teaspoon ground cumin\", \"0.25 teaspoon salt\", \"0.5 teaspoon ground coriander\", \"0.5 teaspoon dried thyme\", \"0.5 teaspoon oregano\", \"0.5 teaspoon paprika\", \"1 pinch ground black pepper\", \"hamburger buns\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat oil in a deep, 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat. Cook the onion in the oil until translucent. Crumble the tempeh into the skillet; cook and stir until golden brown. Add the green pepper and garlic; cook another 2 to 3 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Stir in the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, honey, molasses, cayenne pepper, celery seed, cumin, salt, coriander, thyme, oregano, paprika, and black pepper; stir. Simmer another 10 to 15 minutes. Spoon hot onto hamburger buns to serve.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"6\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT40M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Norma\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Love it, even my picky eater son like it !!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ginny Hein\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We loved it but I used 8 oz of tomato sauce and ketchup and only 1 package of tempeh. Also I did not add as much thyme and no cayenne pepper. I also added homegrown green beans and zucchini. I will make again and may try it with black beans instead of tempeh like someone suggested.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jessie Furman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Solid recipe with great flavors. I made as written, then added tweaks for my personal preferences. I prefer a big-flavored \\\"sloppy joe\\\" than a \\\"dry joe\\\" so I doubled the tomato sauce and added ~25% more of each spice. Really delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"natashawmarsh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really yummy! The best I've ever managed to make tempeh taste. The only problem was it was on the dry side. I will add a little broth and more tomato sauce next time.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Community\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"When I initially made this, it came out a little drier than I like for my sloppy joes so I doubled the recipe. The flavor is really good, but is not a \\\"normal\\\" sloppy joe. If I were to make it again, I would probably use more tomato sauce and less, if not none at all, of coriander.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Arnette Warren\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Added a little catsup and mustard. Used Ro-Tel tomatoes instead of tomato sauce\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Monique Albrecht\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Amazing ! Love it. But I used Lightlife Smart Ground and added carrots !\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"C Angell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good, excellent spice level and very tasty. Used Gardein Vegetarian Chipotle Black Bean Burgers (4 of them). In place of the tomato sauce, I used canned diced tomatoes and their liquid.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"redheadtrip\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a great recipe! I followed many of the other suggestions and used more tomato sauce. I also used tempeh and veggie crumbles to double the recipe (so I didn't have to go to the store), and it turned out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a great recipe. I use no salt added tomato sauce for a low sodium, vegan dish.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Beth168\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is so good even meat eaters will love it! I made it exactly according to the recipe, and it was fantastic. Highly recommend!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shayla\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delish! I omitted the Worcestershire sauce (I am vegetarian and there are anchovies in most of those sauces) I used ketchup and chipotle seasoning instead. Topped with some nice cheese and soft rolls these were just what I needed as a comfort food on this chilly November night in New England.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JackAwesome\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We ended up using the TVP (Bob's Red Mill Textured Vegetable Protine) instead of tempeh. Before making the recipe we soaked the dried TVP in Better than Bullion vegetable broth. Using the TVP made a base that, in my opinion, was even tastier than if we had used ground beef.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ton80\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love this recipe, have made it many times. The sloppy joes are so flavorful and delicious. I do use 'Smart Ground' by a company called LightLife instead of the tempeh. I think you would be hard pressed to tell its not meat. Thanks for this great recipe, i love it so much, I created an account here just so I can rate it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Vince\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious. I doubled the sauce to make it \\\"sloppier.\\\" Definitely will make this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cheryl Lewman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I deviated from the recipe a bit by just using leftover spaghetti sauce, but otherwise followed the recipe. It was yummy!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Doyle Worcester\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Personally I think you should triple the tomato sauce and cut the cumin and coriander by at least half. The original recipe is ok but you are very aware of the above mentioned spices. Everything else about the recipe is great.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kristen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Fabulous! We used whole wheat pita pockets to keep the calories low and made the sloppy joes - neat joes! Super yummy, super tasty. My boyfriend and his roommate thought these were yummy as well. My first time using tempeh and I was very pleased! I will be making this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pete\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'm trying to reduce my my meat intake so this recipe caught my interest. I loved it. So did the boy friend who is not trying to reduce his meat intake at all. Like a lot of others I added more tomato sauce. I also added a touch of salt, more cayenne ant topped them off with Sriracha. We like it spicy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Laurie Brier\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My boyfriend loves this recipe. I double the tomato sauce and the green bell peppers because I like mine moist.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tim Mc\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made as a condiment to baked potatoes. Yum! Replaced tempeh with 15oz can of black beans. Only 1/8 teaspoon of cumin. Add 1Tablespoon cider vinegar, 1 teaspoon of chili powder. Cook green pepper same time as onions. Used entire 15 oz can of tomato sauce. Keep on burner until bubble down to thick consistency. Love the molasses &amp; spicy taste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"4Travelers\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Thanks for a new way to use tempeh, we'll make it again. I did run mine through the food processor a little to break it up more like hamburger, kids never noticed the difference. We also wanted more sauce and ended up doubling the sauce. For our house it only fed 4 1/4 people.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Miko\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was awesome. I used soy sauce instead of Worcestershire for my vegetarian friend. I did have to use 4 times the amount of tomato sauce and it still wasn't saucy though. Also I don't think I would add the thyme next time either, it kind of took away from the sloppy joe flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Georgia\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added ketchup only because I was out of sauce and substituted meatless crumbles instead of tempeh. We like using Hawaiian Bread for Sloppy Joe Sliders. My non vegetarian people like this recipe as well.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lcv inVermont\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very tasty and the family loved it made per the directions. Next time I will add more tomato sauce because I like it sloppier.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tedrick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really good for a vegetarian recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MPEBLE\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a tasty dish, but don't expect it to be interchangeable with meat sloppy joes. It's better to think of it as its own thing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lori Schreiner\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used vegetarian grillers and added 1 teaspoon of turmeric will a side of pasta salad went great with it was delious\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"kate maddick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"family favorite\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lori MacIntosh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved the taste, just didn't love the texture of the tempeh. I loved that I could make up the sauce and use it with ground beef for the guy and with tempeh for me! I'll try it again and try to brown up the tempeh more! Thanks for the recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"javajunkie314\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My wife and I loved this. I think next time I'd make more of the sauce -- I like my sloppy joes sloppy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"PrincessBS\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I had to increase the \\\"sauce\\\" 4 fold and it was delish.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"djb338\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used black beans instead of meat substitute\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"VeggiePatch\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Instead of the Tempeh, I used Tofu. For those people that don't know the difference, Tempeh is less processed than Tofu but if you can't find Tempeh, Tofu is a fine substitute. \\nI gave this only four stars because it was a little on the spicy side, which can be tweaked. However, the molasses and honey, was a great kick to this dish.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Squiggy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have and it was good, I had to replace with sugar as I didn't have any honey or brown sugar, made it a bit sweet, we are vegetarians so I used TVP in place of meat, all ingredients in the recipe are all great for the flavoring of TVP, I used catsup in place of tomatoe sause I couldn't make myself open a whole can of tomato sause just to use 2tablespoons +2tsp of tomato sause and I opened a can of roasted diced tomatoes for the liquid for the TVP made it excellent yummy next I won't use as much sugar next time I will have honey or brown sugar\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"CJ\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I did not care for this recipe as written. I added extra tomato sauce (as others suggested). I also added about 2 T chili powder, 1 T apple cider vinegar, about 1/3 cup ketchup, and an extra dash of salt &amp; pepper. \\n\\nAlso, I suggest adding the bell pepper when you add the onions, the bell peppers could use the extra cooking time for a softer result.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Krystal\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very yummy! My whole family enjoyed these! We used Lightlife's Veggie \\\"ground beef\\\" instead of tempeh and you'd never know you were missing meat! Also, skipped the molasses. Keeping this in our rotation.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"noelman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a solid recipe. That being said, I'm totally going to be that guy who made something very different from what the recipe says to do...\\n\\nI made my own unseasoned marinara to serve as the base. Dice a tomato or two, an onion and some garlic. Mix in tomato paste and a touch of water. Then season that sauce with the spices listed in this recipe until it tastes that way that you want it to taste. I didn't use Worcestershire sauce. I used Bragg's amino acids instead. I do think it would be better the next time with a touch of brown sugar. \\n\\nI used the fake crumbly hamburger meat stuff instead of the tempe. I mixed in some fresh black and pinto beans that i cooked in my pressure cooker. I used some green and red pepper. I served on a fresh organic ciabatta roll that I found in my grocery store's bakery. \\n\\nThis is totally in the rotation.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Renee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I didnt like tempeh. The recipe was dry. I ended up adding the whole can of tomato sauce. I ended up adding it to my vegetarian soup in order for me to eat it. - Renee\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"DOODLE012\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My only comment is that this can be a bit dry (using veggie crumbles). I'd use just one 12 oz package; I tried using 16 oz, per the recipe (for tempeh). I'd also add a whole small can of tomato sauce...more than a 1/4 cup. Otherwise, the flavors were awesome in this recipe. Best veggie sloppy joe I've had so far!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Erin Lange\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great! I used a full can of tomato sauce, as recommended, left out the cayenne pepper for the little ones (would have been even better with it) and used protein veggie crumbles instead of tempeh or beef. Turned out great. Just the right amount of \\\"sloppiness\\\".\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Teresa\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I thought these were excellent! Maybe the tempeh gave it a deeper flavor? I didn't have molasses nor coriander so left those out. I would definitely try this with maybe turkey next time!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pam\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent, also doubled tomatoe sauce and garlic, and added tomatoe paste then used 'Smart Ground'. We are not vegetarians, but my family loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Diana\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"fantastic. Such a hit, it was requested a second time! Tempeh is awesome. Thank you!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brett\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very nice recipe. It was a solid meal, but ends up being almost impossible to hold together on a burger bun -- may be best served in a pita pocket or tortilla shell for eating.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tracy Gregory\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The recipe would have received a 5 star if not for the fact that I had to add more tomato sauce, which technically changes the recipe. I don't know if different brands of Tempeh are more moist than others, so that may have been a factor. Flavor is five star, texture is great too. Will be making this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MOHara87\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Being a vegetarian, I have had A LOT of vegetarian sloppy joe's. These were the best ones I have ever had! My boyfriend has recently jumped the meat train and joined me as a veg head, so he sometimes can be difficult to please, and he said these were the best Sloppy Joe's he has had...PERIOD!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"rachelilly23\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I think this recipe was pretty good. I did add more tomato sauce as some of the other reviewers suggested. I used only 1/2 the amount of oil to make it a little lighter and it still tasted great with all the spices. It had great flavor and my husband and 1-year-old enjoyed it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Teresa Heinz Housel\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I loved this recipe. The only things I changed were that I added a whole can of tomato sauce (I think the recipe as is is too dry), used extra firm tofu instead of tempeh, cut down on the spices slightly, and did not add the cayenne pepper at all. Put the mixture on whole wheat buns with cheddar cheese on top. Yum! I will definitely be making this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Yetenekli\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It's really good if you get the right sauce to put in it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jamie S\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"After a long search for tempeh at the grocery strore I came up empty handed, so I used veggie ground round. So this rating may be a little \\\"off\\\". However I found the combination of spices to be just to much, will not be using this recipe again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"rharris\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used 8 oz. tomato sauce to make it sloppier. So good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KatC\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I very much like this recipe and have made it several times. I use a lot more tomato sauce than the recipe calls for. I just pour until moist. I also cut down on some of the Italian seasonings to adjust to my taste. Overall, I love this recipe. Very filling and easy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Leah\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've made this a number of times and love it. I'd give it 5 stars except I always have adjustments to make. I always add way more tomato sauce - usually the entire can worth. I tend to do less tempeh and more onion and bell pepper just because I like to load up on veggies where I can as well. I always double the garlic in any recipe too. Other than that, the flavors are spot on and this is a GREAT vegetarian alternative - and we're not even vegetarian! ;)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Leah2974\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was brilliant. Since other reviewers thought it needed more tomato sauce, I started with a big can and kept adding sauce until it tasted the way I wanted it to.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ultra Nuclear Maga\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Worchester sauce IS NOT vegetarian\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Osider760\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I hate this. I have nothing against people who do not eat meat but these were not to my liking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Alberta Rose\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'll give this five stars for the flavor, but next time I'll use ground beef and pick something else for Meatless Monday. Veggie ground needs to be deeply buried in a recipe to work, not be front and centre. I love love love the flavor of the sauce though and will definitely use this recipe again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"jada_25\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good! I followed the recipe exactly. I'll make again soon!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Descolada\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a nice way to use tempeh in something other than stir fry. We did use more 1/4C additional tomato sauce. Next time we'll half the recipe since we were cooking for just 2 and this made a lot of leftovers.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Linda\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"sorry...I didn't like this at all, but the dog did! We are new vegans and I used TVP and kept adding stuff too (Homade chili sauce from up north, ketchup, ect), but still didn't like it. Thanks for sharing though..\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cupcake\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is awesome. Per others' suggestions, I added some ketchup and extra tomato sauce. Also, left out the peppers and celery seed because I didn't have any.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Wilma Laura Wiggins\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very tasty! Thanks for the recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jessie Kuhn\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"In the end the general consensus in my house was that this was pretty good, but probably won't be made again because the 20g of fat is more than we would like, not because it wasn't good though. It did need a few modifications. After I had followed the recipe exactly and sampled the results I was pretty disappointed. As other reviewers have said it needed more tomato sauce, and I added about an extra tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce. It was terribly dry and definitely did not resemble any sloppy joe I had ever had. With the additions it was much better, and as leftovers actually seemed to be much more tasty than the initial serving.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jessica Grieb Bair\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"No way! Tempeh is not a family favorite, apparently. My husband was the only one who ate a whole sandwich.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ellen Finnerty\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I had just bought my vegetarian worshtishire sauce and was surfing for a recipe to try it on... and voila'. This recipe whips up quickly. It's been over 14 years since I had a sloppy joe, but this certainly reminded me of what I used to enjoy. Small amount of clean up involved- the flavors are good with sweet initial flavor and a spicy aftertaste. I agree with another reviewer, my 8 year old thought it was too spicy, though I thought it was perfect. (I'm a mild salsa type gal). Very good flavor, I don't think it could pass as the real deal but certainly will pass this on to EVERY vegetarian/vegan I know (I think vegan use br. sugar in lieu of honey). I used MorningStar for my tempeh/meat substitute.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"UM2002GIRL\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Wow, this is really good! I used extra firm tofu instead of tempeh, since it was what I had on hand. I halved the recipe but stuck to the 1/4 cup tomato sauce. I left out the celery seed since I didn't have that on hand, either, and I used vegan worchestershire sauce. This would be a great quick weeknight meal!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"juliemay7\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Good recipe, but remember that Worcestershire sauce is NOT vegetarian unless you get a vegan version; regular Worcestershire has anchovies in it. Also, use brown sugar instead of the honey if cooking for vegans.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lovecheese\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"i have not made this recipe so i can't comment on how it tastes but i just wanted to say worceshire sauce is not vegetarian. it traditionally has anchovies in it so beware!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Renee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good and a great way to use tempeh (which we love but always use in stirfry). It wasn't as saucy as I expected, so I added more tomato sauce and a little ketchup. Good spices for us, actually too spicy for my toddlers so I'll cut back on the cayene and some others next time.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pappyabc\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved it!!! My family is not vegetarian and we loved this! Nice kick to it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jonny's Girl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Fantastic recipe! Even my carnivore husband loves it. I like to substitute extra firm tofu for the tempeh and use a full can of tomato sauce.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kazanoodle\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Thanks for the recipe, but be sure to make sure you get vegetarian Worcestershire sauce, since the original kind is made with fish. ^^ &lt;3\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mr Nothing\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is great for all your Vegetarian friends go to all recipes now, to look up this wonderful recipe NOW!\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/163867/vegetarian-sloppy-joes/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/251/main-dish/sandwiches/\", \"name\": \"Sandwich Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/14930/main-dish/sandwiches/sloppy-joes/\", \"name\": \"Sloppy Joe Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/163867/vegetarian-sloppy-joes/\", \"name\": \"Vegetarian Sloppy Joes\"}}]}}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Keto Mac & Cheese", "yields": "8 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT20M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT1H20M"}, "ingredients": ["Butter, for baking dish", "2 medium heads cauliflower, cut into florets", "2 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil", "Kosher salt", "1 c. heavy cream&nbsp;", "6 oz. cream cheese, cut into cubes", "4 c. shredded cheddar", "2 c. shredded mozzarella", "1 tbsp. hot sauce (optional)", "Freshly ground black pepper", "4 oz. pork rinds, crushed", "1/4 c. freshly grated Parmesan", "1 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil", "2 tbsp. freshly chopped parsley, for garnish"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat oven to 375° and butter a 9”-x-13” baking dish. In a large bowl, toss cauliflower with 2 tablespoons oil and season with salt. Spread cauliflower onto two large baking sheets and roast until&nbsp;tender and lightly golden, about 40 minutes.&nbsp;<br>"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Meanwhile, in a large pot over medium heat, heat cream. Bring up to a simmer, then decrease&nbsp;heat to low and stir in cheeses until melted. Remove from heat, add hot sauce if using and season with salt and pepper, then fold in roasted cauliflower. Taste and season more if needed."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Transfer mixture to prepared baking dish. In a medium bowl stir to combine pork rinds, Parmesan, and oil. Sprinkle mixture in an even layer over cauliflower and cheese."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Bake until golden, 15 minutes. If desired, turn oven to broil to toast topping further, about 2 minutes.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Garnish with parsley before serving."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.530xw:0.796xh;0.130xw,0.103xh&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-10-28T18:29:26.038699Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Keto Mac & Cheese\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.530xw:0.796xh;0.130xw,0.103xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.530xw:0.796xh;0.130xw,0.103xh&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.530xw:0.796xh;0.130xw,0.103xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.8888888888888888xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=0.530xw:0.796xh;0.130xw,0.103xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=1xw:0.84375xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29024668/keto-mac-and-cheese-recipe/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"http://instagram.com/delish\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/Delish/\"], \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/_assets/design-tokens/delish/static/images/logos/logo-jsonld.1396ea2.png\", \"width\": 312, \"height\": 60}, \"parentOrganization\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Hearst Corporation\"}}, \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29024668/keto-mac-and-cheese-recipe/\", \"isBasedOn\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/nutrition/a29024668/keto-mac-and-cheese-recipe/\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-08-28T16:21:00Z EST\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"hasPart\": [{\"@type\": \"WebPageElement\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"cssSelector\": \".content-container\"}], \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://streaming.hearstdigitalstudios.com/ac7d2931-7e46-4230-b187-64067cc156d2/video_rover_16x9_1080p_hd_1623429310_5136.mp4\", \"description\": \"We made mac and cheese keto by using cauliflower and pork rinds. Also don't forget the cheese! Mozzarella, cheddar, cream cheese and parm can be found in this dish.\", \"duration\": \"PT1M40S\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://glimmer.hearstapps.com/amp.html?embedId=cd1de441-b2a5-42c3-b95d-eebf613c8cf3\", \"name\": \"The Secret To Keto Mac and Cheese Is Cauliflower and Pork Rrinds\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/delish-190912-keto-mac-and-cheese-0116-landscape-pf-1648563264.jpg?crop=1xw:0.84375xh;center,top\", \"uploadDate\": \"2021-06-11T16:47:25.070689Z\", \"transcript\": \"(upbeat music) - [Narrator] Mac and cheese or fluff and fold. (upbeat music) - [Woman] Where's my mac and cheese? (upbeat music)\"}, \"author\": {\"name\": \"Lena Abraham\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/author/17077/lena-abraham/\", \"@type\": \"Person\", \"description\": \"<p>Lena Abraham is a freelance contributor with Delish, and was formerly Senior Food Editor, where she developed and styled recipes for video and photo, and also stayed on top of current food trends. She\\u2019s been working in the food industry for over 10 years, and will argue that the best fish tacos in the world are made in New York. Don\\u2019t @ her.</p>\", \"jobTitle\": \"Contributor\", \"image\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/846121db-9644-42e0-a4fd-cf5d105bfdf9_1576786748.file\", \"email\": \"Lena.Abraham@hearst.com\", \"sameAs\": []}, \"name\": \"Keto Mac & Cheese\", \"prepTime\": \"PT20M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT0S\", \"totalTime\": \"PT1H20M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"Butter, for baking dish\", \"2 medium heads cauliflower, cut into florets\", \"2 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil\", \"Kosher salt\", \"1 c. heavy cream&nbsp;\", \"6 oz. cream cheese, cut into cubes\", \"4 c. shredded cheddar\", \"2 c. shredded mozzarella\", \"1 tbsp. hot sauce (optional)\", \"Freshly ground black pepper\", \"4 oz. pork rinds, crushed\", \"1/4 c. freshly grated Parmesan\", \"1 tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil\", \"2 tbsp. freshly chopped parsley, for garnish\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Preheat oven to 375\\u00b0 and butter a 9\\u201d-x-13\\u201d baking dish. In a large bowl, toss cauliflower with 2 tablespoons oil and season with salt. Spread cauliflower onto two large baking sheets and roast until&nbsp;tender and lightly golden, about 40 minutes.&nbsp;<br>\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Meanwhile, in a large pot over medium heat, heat cream. Bring up to a simmer, then decrease&nbsp;heat to low and stir in cheeses until melted. Remove from heat, add hot sauce if using and season with salt and pepper, then fold in roasted cauliflower. Taste and season more if needed.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Transfer mixture to prepared baking dish. In a medium bowl stir to combine pork rinds, Parmesan, and oil. Sprinkle mixture in an even layer over cauliflower and cheese.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bake until golden, 15 minutes. If desired, turn oven to broil to toast topping further, about 2 minutes.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Garnish with parsley before serving.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"8 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeCategory\": [\"gluten-free\", \"nut-free\", \"vegetarian\", \"dinner party\", \"Sunday lunch\", \"baking\", \"comfort food\", \"dinner\", \"lunch\", \"side dish\"], \"description\": \"This keto-friendly, low-carb Mac and Cheese from is totally pasta-free, thanks to cauliflower.\", \"keywords\": \"keto mac and cheese\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.06, \"reviewCount\": 50, \"worstRating\": 1, \"bestRating\": 5}, \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \" 650 Calories\", \"fatContent\": \"56 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"30 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"1 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"165 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"791 mg\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"8 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"3 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"5 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"29 g\"}, \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Crispy Fried Chicken", "yields": ["8"], "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT35M", "total": "PT80M"}, "ingredients": ["1 (4 pound) chicken, cut into pieces", "1 cup buttermilk", "2 cups all-purpose flour for coating", "1 teaspoon paprika", "salt and pepper to taste", "2 quarts vegetable oil for frying"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Take your cut up chicken pieces and skin them if you prefer."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/5nU0U8VAu9hqa17AiG5ZB1Lzktg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepOne-068-01d35dc485ed40639ee1977a22d115c0.jpg"}], "text": "Put the flour in a large plastic bag (let the amount of chicken you are cooking dictate the amount of flour you use). Season the flour with paprika, salt and pepper to taste (paprika helps to brown the chicken)."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/xuQoJC0rMByex-L4Qgwfwg2NVKg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepTwo-069-05478afbe4a0496fb4eda6887f6c0044.jpg"}], "text": "Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk then, a few at a time, put them in the bag with the flour, seal the bag and shake to coat well."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/6XUBvt2KOC3i-oJ17WCtIR90a8I=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepThree-070-9d5a36e9361842fcb993205275fa5428.jpg"}], "text": "Place the coated chicken on a cookie sheet or tray, and cover with a clean dish towel or waxed paper. LET SIT UNTIL THE FLOUR IS OF A PASTE-LIKE CONSISTENCY. THIS IS CRUCIAL!"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Fill a large skillet (cast iron is best) about 1/3 to 1/2 full with vegetable oil. Heat until VERY hot."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/dEPpNGeDDqPdVgl8rmpOGHyI04U=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepFour-071-994f60e233dd44d19926c7166b8c776f.jpg"}], "text": "Put in as many chicken pieces as the skillet can hold. Brown the chicken in HOT oil on both sides."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "When browned, reduce heat and cover skillet; let cook for 30 minutes (the chicken will be cooked through but not crispy). Remove cover, raise heat again, and continue to fry until crispy."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/SoBuPU73KcbYHl3Kp3j8Xx4A3fc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-3x2-072-d55b8406d4ae45709fcdeb58a04143c2.jpg"}], "text": "Drain the fried chicken on paper towels. Depending on how much chicken you have, you may have to fry in a few shifts. Keep the finished chicken in a slightly warm oven while preparing the rest."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Crispy Fried Chicken\", \"datePublished\": \"1999-05-21T15:28:05.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-03-01T18:32:09.024-05:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Anonymous\"}], \"description\": \"Discover the technique for making deliciously crispy fried chicken with a crunchy coating on the outside and juicy, tender chicken inside.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/SoBuPU73KcbYHl3Kp3j8Xx4A3fc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-3x2-072-d55b8406d4ae45709fcdeb58a04143c2.jpg\", \"height\": 1125, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/lMTN4eKw-ma1DlVvV.mp4\", \"description\": \"AR0607\", \"duration\": \"PT3M6S\", \"name\": \"Crispy Fried Chicken\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/lMTN4eKw/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2020-10-21T13:09:53.835-04:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Crispy Fried Chicken\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.6\", \"ratingCount\": \"746\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT35M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"489 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"30 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"116 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"1 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"41 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"6 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"140 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"2 g\", \"fatContent\": \"22 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 (4 pound) chicken, cut into pieces\", \"1 cup buttermilk\", \"2 cups all-purpose flour for coating\", \"1 teaspoon paprika\", \"salt and pepper to taste\", \"2 quarts vegetable oil for frying\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Take your cut up chicken pieces and skin them if you prefer.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/5nU0U8VAu9hqa17AiG5ZB1Lzktg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepOne-068-01d35dc485ed40639ee1977a22d115c0.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Put the flour in a large plastic bag (let the amount of chicken you are cooking dictate the amount of flour you use). Season the flour with paprika, salt and pepper to taste (paprika helps to brown the chicken).\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/xuQoJC0rMByex-L4Qgwfwg2NVKg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepTwo-069-05478afbe4a0496fb4eda6887f6c0044.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk then, a few at a time, put them in the bag with the flour, seal the bag and shake to coat well.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/6XUBvt2KOC3i-oJ17WCtIR90a8I=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepThree-070-9d5a36e9361842fcb993205275fa5428.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Place the coated chicken on a cookie sheet or tray, and cover with a clean dish towel or waxed paper. LET SIT UNTIL THE FLOUR IS OF A PASTE-LIKE CONSISTENCY. THIS IS CRUCIAL!\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Fill a large skillet (cast iron is best) about 1/3 to 1/2 full with vegetable oil. Heat until VERY hot.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/dEPpNGeDDqPdVgl8rmpOGHyI04U=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-StepFour-071-994f60e233dd44d19926c7166b8c776f.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Put in as many chicken pieces as the skillet can hold. Brown the chicken in HOT oil on both sides.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"When browned, reduce heat and cover skillet; let cook for 30 minutes (the chicken will be cooked through but not crispy). Remove cover, raise heat again, and continue to fry until crispy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/SoBuPU73KcbYHl3Kp3j8Xx4A3fc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/8805-CrispyFriedChicken-mfs-3x2-072-d55b8406d4ae45709fcdeb58a04143c2.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Drain the fried chicken on paper towels. Depending on how much chicken you have, you may have to fry in a few shifts. Keep the finished chicken in a slightly warm oven while preparing the rest.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"8\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT80M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nina Wheeler\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This picture doesn\\u2019t do the fried chicken justice. This technique is A1!! I\\u2019ve been trying to figure out the best way to fry chicken for years. So glad I came upon this recipe. Thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Best ever! Crispy, moist, and delicious. Only thing I did different was to let the chicken marinate in the buttermilk for thirty minutes plus.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So yummy\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Marilyn A M\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is an amazing chicken recipe!!! I will be making it again soon \\ud83d\\ude0b\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"connie byrne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So crispy delicious \\ud83d\\ude0b\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"cherylls\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Poor flavor and on low eat overdone.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The crispness of the chicken coating was spot on. I did think it needed more flavour though, but I wanted to follow the recipe for the first time. The next time I make it, I\\u2019ll maybe add some garlic and onion powder to the flour too. I read the reviews before cooking, so after 5 mins hot frying, 10 mins cooler and a few mins on hot again, I then put them into the Ninja on 170 for 10 mins. It took away the oiliness and left them just as crispy. I will be using this method of frying with many of my other favourite coatings in future. Thank you.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"addie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used some different spices and it was absolutely delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"John Adams\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've been deep frying chicken and other things for many years. Even though I knew this recipe was not great I had to try it and it did confirm my belief. The chicken did turn out oily and greasy. By starting the heat of oil high and then lowering it to cook longer only makes the oil penetrate the chicken pieces. A much better result is by deep frying in about 5ltr of oil at a constant 180\\u2070C (350\\u2070F) for roughly 12-15 minutes. That way the outside is sealed and the only oil remaining is any that is left on the outer crust not deep inside the chicken where you don't want it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've been using this method for 40 years and it never fails me! My sister and son devoured the batch I just fried!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used regular milk instead of buttermilk and it was still good. Everyone loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019m 68 and live in the country in the South and this is my first try at fried chicken. Go figure. Didn\\u2019t have buttermilk so I substituted evaporated milk. It turned out really good. I mean really good. (I\\u2019ve eaten lots of fried chicken, BBQ chicken, smoked chicken, and every other kind of chicken so I know good from bad.) Thank you for sharing your recipe. There are about 25 more chickens in the freezer that I just harvested and now they\\u2019re all waiting to plop in the pan.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very mild on the spices. But flavorful. Used gluten free flour\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sunflower-Sister\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Chicken coating was hard and chewy :(\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Linda Oconnor\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was crunchy but it was almost burned before it got to crunchy. I definitely overcooked it to get the crunch by then it was to hard to eat. It may be a good recipe but I'm not going to waste another chicken and dinner. If you are going to try it, be careful of the cooking time!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"i would like to try this recipe, but i have a question. what is the trick to not having the outside burned by 350 oil? i tried to fry some chicken the other day in about an inch of oil, and it all burned on the outside, and was really undercooked inside. thanks in advance! /\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"cgray\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the best fried chicken I've had in a long time. Recipe is just what the author said. I made no changes and it didn't take all that long to complete the task. It's even good cold. I'm going to keep this recipe as my go-to for really tasty fried chicken.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ric\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Turned out perfect!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Momita\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have made fried chicken before, first dredged in flour, then egg and finally flour. For whatever reason it comes out hard and dry. This recipe however, was simple with fewer steps and came out better. I love finding methods that work, and allow room for my own tastes and tweaks. Thank you for the method. It was a hit at dinner. 'Very crispy and super moist. The only change I made, was that I used coconut oil.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ernursjen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Mind you, although I am a great cook, I have never been able to fry chicken, which is astounding to me. This chicken was so overcooked. I cooked between a temp of 350 to 375 to start and then turned heat to low for the 30 minute cook. Then back up to finish the cooking like it says in the instructions. It was crispy! But tasted like nothing, as I\\u2019m sure the crust being overcooked just obliterated all the spices I put in the flour. The meat was SO tough and overcooked! This was bad! And a waste of time/oil... Fried chicken is definitely an art. You either have it or you don\\u2019t I guess.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Angela Malloy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was a hit!!! My family loved it, there was no left overs.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kathi Bolin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Chicken Fingers\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe for crispy chicken. I added some of my own seasonings to the flour and it was really crispy, moist and tasty. This will be my go to fried chicken recipe from now on. Almost forgot to mention it was really easy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JillyB\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"These wings were as good as a restaurant.I\\u2019ve made them a few times\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Aisha W\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Perfect! I've fried chicken a few times before and this is the best. I used an electric skillet and kept the temperature at 375 for browning and 200 for cooking it through. I didn't have buttermilk so I used 1 cup of milk and an egg instead. I used drumsticks with the skin on. The outside was nice and crispy and the meat was super moist.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"amani haddad\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love this recipe! it is my first time making fried chicken. The tips helped me a lot. It turned out perfect. Thank you\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lee Bennett\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love allspice and use it all the time. I don\\u2019t think I\\u2019ve ever written a review to date. I thought my grandma made the best fried chicken, but I was wrong. I like my chicken crispy and this was crispy. The most tender fried chicken I\\u2019ve ever had. The only things I did different were to add some old bay seasoning and some garlic salt. I used an electric skillet and browned the chicken on high then reduced heat to 300 and fried for 24 minutes covered, turning the chicken half way through. Then I cranked it back on high to make crispy. I also placed on a cooling rack when done versus laying in paper towels. Awesome method for fabulous fried chicken!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mike\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this recipe! Never made my own fried chicken but recently bought a BIG cast iron skillet. I used chicken drums and it turned out so crispy. \\n\\nI am going to experiment with the spices but the technique makes juicy and crispy fried chicken. Thanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Snave\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First time I ever made fried chicken and I consider it a great success. I added more spices to the flour: more paprika, Mrs. Dash, cayenne pepper. And I soaked the chicken (all skinless thighs) in buttermilk for several hours rather than just dipping. I cooked it for about 15 minutes total, until it was the dark brown I like. Pretty good chicken for my first time!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Anita Rivera-Lopez\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe worked out so wonderfully, I\\u2019ll continue to use it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"maurin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I seasoned the oil first by adding garlic onion and green pepper for a couple minutes. \\nChicken turned out super crispy, the buttermilk made a BIG difference. highly recommend\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JFlack\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious... I soaked my chicken in the buttermilk for 2 hours before breading then and letting them rest. We made all drum sticks using a deep fryer. We fried them for 5 minutes and flipped them once. We started to check each drum stick at 2 minutes with a meat thermometer. Depending on the size of the drum stick it would take up to 5 minutes to reach 165 degrees all the way through. The chicken was tender and delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Barbara\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have never given a food review and I am terrible at frying chicken, but this was the best chicken I\\u2019ve ever had in my life and the recipe was simple. I made my own buttermilk mix and added a smidgen of thyme. This one is a keeper. Thank you.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mary Perez\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a simple recipe but the technique is something I\\u2019ve never tried before. It works and it works really well. Time to let the chicken sit after coating may take a while and like the author said, this is crucial for best results. I marinated the chicken in buttermilk a few hours and for the dredge I added rotisserie chicken seasoning. It turned out really good. Thank you. This is my go-to fried chicken recipe from now on.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Shelbi Viers\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I really enjoyed this recipe and I\\u2019m not even a fan of chicken or fried foods! This recipe is easy, has an awesome foundation that will give great results every time, but it also leaves room for experimentation which I love. I added 1 tsp. Onion powder, 1 tsp. Garlic powder and 1 tsp. Chili powder to the flour mixture and my family really enjoyed it. It was crispy but also very juicy. I served this Fried Chicken with Red Beans and Rice and Corn on the Cobb. But any side would work with this dish. Thank you for submitting this recipe it\\u2019s going in my cookbook for sure! :) \\n\\nP.S. Chefs be sure to watch your chicken carefully as it fries so not to burn it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bigeater\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tender, crispy and delicious is the way I would describe this great recipe. I used chicken tenders that I had on hand in an attempt to satisfy my daughter\\u2019s KFC craving and it worked! Thanks for the recipe and valuable cooking tips!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mousielove\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good. Even better so \\\"brine\\\" the chicken in the buttermilk and seasonings the night before. Then do everything as listed. Thanks for posting a winning recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"eclmt98\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Recipe was delicious! Chicken was great hot or cold.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"miamigirl086\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"DEFINITELY 5 STARS! My husband went turkey hunting yesterday and I was looking for a good recipe to use with the wild turkey breast meat. This worked out perfectly. I sliced the turkey breasts into nuggets and marinated them in seasoned buttermilk for a couple of hours and then tossed the nuggets in my seasoned flour in a ziplock bag. Followed instructions until I achieved the paste consistency and then fried them up in a cast iron pot. Since they were smaller nuggets, total cook time was less than 5 minutes. Will definitely be making these nuggets again. So good!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"chefntraining\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good! Had to make my own buttermilk, since I didn't have any in the house (I kept an article from previous email from all recipes).\\nI would definitely add more spices to this recipe.\\nSide note: I used boneless skinless thighs, (1) because that's what I had &amp; (2) didn't have thermometer to gauge the oil temp...I cooked until deep golden brown(about 20-25 min).\\nMoist and absolutely crispy!!\\nA definite keeper\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Leisa Shannon Corbett\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The chicken was as crispy on the outside as the description said. The meat was moist and tender. We used a deep fryer, but the chicken didn't use much oil. Yay! It wasn't greasy\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nancy Coleman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have never made fried chicken before; I remember my grandma's, which was delicious, but I rarely fry things. My 84 year old dad did not have a terrific appetite and I asked what would taste good...he said fried chicken. I added about a tablespoon of garlic powder and onion powder, and increased the paprika a bit, but followed the prep directions exactly. \\nMy dad just called and said it was the best chicken he has ever had *in his life*. \\nThanks Elaine!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Anne Collins\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The chicken was crispy but lacked seasoning; maybe if the recipe had garlic powder and onion powder it would of been better..I was disappointed.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sharon\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the best fried chicken I\\u2019ve ever made\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"leeleebs9\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I read all of the reviews for knowledge, but honestly a lot of you are over thinking this. I put whatever seasonings. But the gist is the buttermilk, &amp; flour resting. Used my electric presto with thermostat. Did wonderfully. I mean, use common sense to adjust seasoning &amp; spices. Threw a turkey leg in the middle. Fab. Electric: Started at 375 until a bead of water danced. Turn, Turn after a light brown, I watched at this point! Then I changed dial to 300* &amp; put lid on for 10 min/flipped-reset timer/flipped to = 30 min. Cranked to 375 &amp; quickly flipped. Than tree in last two drumsticks on 350* &amp; watched\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kelley Ellyse\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The method seemed fine, and I put on my own spices into the flour mix to get the flavor that I wanted. My biggest problem with this recipe is that there's no specificity or even ballpark figures. She says that the oil needs to get hot, but how hot? Should be bubbling? Should it be smoking? And then when she says to put the chicken in the flour and then let it rest until the flower gets to a paste-like consistency, how long should that take? Approximately how long should that take? I know that it probably can change depending upon how much flour you put on it, if you double battered it, or other factors, but for someone who's trying this recipe for the very first time, are we talking about something that should take 5 minutes, or 2 hours? I have no idea, and I felt that the recipe was riddled with non specific things that assume you're already a fried chicken expert before you try this recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Maureen Dipietro\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Ive been cooking for 45 yrs and this is the best fried chicken recipe ever! I did add garlic powder and didnr have buttermilk so i soured some milk with vinegar...the secret is to let the coating sit until pasty...yummm!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Angela Gregory\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Ok so this technique worked perfectly (with some changes mostly because I was using boneless skinless chicken breast). I had been using another recipe that was far more complicated (involving triple dipping) but the problem with it was that the coating, while delicious, wasn't sticking to the chicken! Kind of a problem. My chicken breast recipe calls for the chicken to be marinated overnight in the buttermilk, and spices, so this was PERFECT. I pulled it out of the bag that it was marinating in, dipped it in the flour/seasoning bag (I only seasoned a bit because there's quite a bit of seasoning in my marinade) and WAITED for the paste like consistency. It took about an hour and 25 minutes just fyi. We then cooked it at 350 (the whole time because it wasn't whole pieces) for about 6 to 7 minutes I want to say (until it was crispy and brown) and it was PERFECT. And the coating STUCK!!!! And it was easier. So thank you!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cindy Rogers\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"OMG! OLD TIME CRISPY, TASTY FIED CHICKEN THAT WAS DELICIOUS HOT OR COLD. MY HUSBAND MADE THIS WITH NO TROUBLE. TRY IT!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Judy Vecchio\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My family really liked the chicken fixed . It was nice and crispy and moist,I will make it again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mcooks\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"very crispy, buttermilk works good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"el grande\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added seasoning to everything, the brine, the flour, the wash, it all got more seasoning! It turned out great! Nice and moist. Good crispy skin. I\\u2019ll make this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Alphahunter\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"You make great chicken, and no one makes better chicken than you.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Margaret Jane McCampbell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Fixed chicken legs in my first cast iron skillet. I didn't have paprika so I used tumeric, and make my own buttermilk with vinegar added to whole milk. Turned out great--but the direction to \\\"turn down heat, cover and cook 30 minutes\\\"\\nwasn't clear enough for me to know how much to turn down.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nelson Steinke\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the first one I\\u2019ve tried, so maybe I\\u2019m underrating it at 4 stars, but I\\u2019d say it\\u2019s a good sign that I\\u2019m comparing it to fast food chicken. The crispyness of the fried chicken needs some flavoring but overall the chicken was very good. I\\u2019m going to tinker with the seasoning to make the skin more flavorful\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Miss Keshia\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was an ez win on super bowl Sunday\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chancey\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My family loved this! The breading didn't fall off like every other time I've tried frying anything. I did flip the chicken and check the internal temp of the chicken during the 30 mins. I didn't need to cook it for the full 30 mins. The chicken ended up crispy on the outside and juicy. Will make again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ladybug\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The taste was bland, I would recommend adding seasoning with flavor before dipping the chicken in buttermilk\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"abbie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have finally made a fried chicken that my husband would eat! I basically did everything described. I used smoked paprika and garlic pepper with he salt. I didn\\u2019t let the chicken sit long enough to get gooey. I will be sure I do that next time. I used the kernel of popcorn method to get my oil hot enough to brown the chicken. I then reduced the heat to medium low and covered my cast iron. I set a timer for 30 minutes and waited it kind of close. After 30 minutes, I removed the lid, increased the heat to just above medium (electric stove) and it took 10-15 minutes for the chicken to crisp. I turned halfway through the cooking time for browning and crisping. Our chicken looked like grandma\\u2019s fried chicken and had good flavor. We like plain spices, so I didn\\u2019t add hot pepper flakes or anything like that. I filled my cast iron skillet (with high sides) about 1/3 full. I hope my review is helpful to inexperienced cooks.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MsIndy69\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"One of my boyz favorite meal. They requested it on a weekly basis. I marinate it overnight in hot sauce and other seasonings. You have to double coat like the instructions say to come out perfectly.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Benji\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was amazing I ate the whole thing by myself. I made it for my wife and then she got mad and left me for my brother. So single I am.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lissybell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Chicken is perfect!! Oil temp should be 375. It will cool down once the chicken is in, then keep around 325 while frying. I love fried chicken with hot spices, but my grandkids don\\u2019t appreciate spicy foods, so I think the minimal seasonings in this are perfect. I added turmeric. Will be making again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Teresa\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my go to chicken recipe from now on. Your technic is awesome. Followed the instructions to a tee. Sorry no pic, cause we ate it fast!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Omgirl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this using chicken breasts cut into strips. I added a touch of garlic powder, otherwise exactly as written. Cooked it maybe 15 mins. It got rave reviews from all my kids. And my husband, who is stingy with compliments even said how delicious it was. I\\u2019ll definitely make this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mike Farrell\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really good\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Katherine Rosten\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was the first time making fried chicken, and this recipe delivered! Recipe was easy to follow, produced chicken that was juicy and crispy. Will definitely make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michelle Lee Thomas\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this tonight an I am sad to say that I won't make it again. The breading had no flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Donna witten\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Stuck to the recipe. Delicious!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stevie Oakley\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My mommy made THE BEST chicken (like ALL mommys do!) And I've been frying chicken forever, sometimes in buttermilk or Ranch, even 1000 Island on zingy flavor nights.. but i just KNEW there was something i was missing. Let the Chicken coating become a paste!!! Thank you! When i read that i remembered how mommy would put the chicken in the fridge, i had just forgot why.. xoxo to you for the \\\"secret\\\" that i forgot!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Aliza Binford\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this chicken for my kids last night and they loved it! Had some leftover so that'll be my lunch today! Thanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tracy Leys\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Finally!!!!!! Thank you! Just add your own spice preference. Perfection!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Gomez Addams\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was great. I followed it closely including letting the battered chicken set for over an hour. Was generous with salt, pepper, and paprika, putting it on chicken before the buttermilk wash as well as in the flour mixture. The family loved it! We will make this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Annie Ngo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First time making fried chicken here.. roughly used Food Network's recipe, but followed this technique, since reviews said the recipe was bland. And i believe it, bc the recipe i used was a tad step up but i wasn't excited about the flavor, and it's a bit too salty. I had 5 chicken legs (not quite 2#) brined overnight, rinsed and let it drain and warm with ambient temperature. I substitute buttermilk, 1/8C almond milk to 3/8C to make 1/2C \\\"buttermilk\\\" substitute; for the mix i used: 1.5C flour, 1T salt (plan to cut to 2tsp next time!), 1T black pepper, 1/2T garlic, 1/4T onion, 1/2tsp paprika, 1/2tsp red(cayenne) pepper; I used my carbon steel wok and had it filled with just enough oil to submerge half the chicken. Fried the first side for 15min before flipping to other side for 10min to try to mitigate overfrying. I ended up overfrying and inside was maybe just a smidge undercooked? just nuked in microwave for 1min to be on safer side. I did not do the cook through with lid cover...so will do that next time (I was afraid of losing crispiness after already overfried the outside)! Still had at least half of the flour-mixture remain - so it's a good amount.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Regina Parker\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I browned in the deep fryer then put in a frying pan and covered and simmered for 1/2 hour. Put it in a large baking pan warmed at dinner time in a hot oven . Very good and will definitely make again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"seniorHoney\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So disappointed I love fried chicken but stay away from the frying, so gave it a try anyway, the technique was good but no taste at all, OK no raw chicken but no flavor to this, and took so long to make. made only two whole legs and of course way tooooo much flour, but will have to play with the spices. thank you anyway. I love Allrecipes\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michelle S\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Steven Sanders\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely fabulous fried chicken! Did add a few additional spices, 1/2 tsp of poultry seasoning, garlic powder, onion powder and Emeril\\u2019s and used House Autry Chicken Breader in place of the flower. Fry as directed, then place on absorbent paper. Drained the oil through a strainer and retained the extra crispy\\u2018s back into the pan adding 1/4 cup of the breading mix with 3 tbsp of the oil on high heat stir until smooth then add 2 cups milk adding salt and pepper to taste, stirring constantly heat until a rich creamy consistency, serve over mashed potatoes!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Donna May\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Definitely love this technique! Didn\\u2019t have any buttermilk so I just used eggs instead, but next time I will get buttermilk. I love the technique of letting the chicken sit once floured, you can definitely see and taste a difference! Husband and son loved it! Great recipe!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Barb W\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made this for dinner a few nights ago. Followed the recipe except for the addition of some hot sauce mixed in with the buttermilk. Chicken came out moist and juicy on the inside and crisp and crunchy on the outside. Hubs especially liked it. Will definitely be making this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ron Cross\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'm rating 5 stars because I KNOW this is a great recipe. But it didn't turn out as good as I hoped (there was still none left, mind you). I'm going to do it again now that I know the following:\\n\\n1. After reading MANY reviews I finally found one reviewer (AFTER I cooked it) who revealed the flour can take 30 minutes to reach that \\\"pasty\\\" consistency, which is critical to this working. The recipe doesn't give you an idea how long it takes, so if you've never done it you really don't know how long you should expect it to take. That may explain people jumping the gun on this step (like I did).\\n\\n2. I think real Buttermilk (not a substitute like I used) is a critical component to getting that paste. I could be wrong here but I'll use the real stuff next time.\\n\\n3. Mine was a little bland, like many others. But I think that's because if you're someone who likes to taste a lot of seasoning it takes a lot more than the recipe calls for to cut through 2 cups of flour. I could taste it a little but I'll add quite a bit more next time.\\n\\n4. I used one of these counter-top electric fryer-type things, so I was able to dial in the temp to 375. But my chicken got more brown than I wanted it to, and it got there pretty quickly. Even without fully reaching the pasty phase though, I could tell the skin was definitely different.\\n\\nNext time I'll either cook it at a lower temp or omit the Paprika, since it's a browning agent.\\n\\nOther things were a little unclear because the instructions differe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"GrandmasKitchen07\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I never knew how to make fried chicken so I never made it. I made this recipe and I am a believer. This recipe is remarkable. \\nThank you, Elaine O for sharing !!\\nThis is my new Sunday nite dinner.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"pao1985\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this yesterday and I couldn't agree more with the comments. This recipe works because of the technique**.\\nThe choice of seasoning and quantities is up to you! But do make sure that after you dip (or marinate) in buttermilk you toss the chicken in a bag with the flour mixture (in batches) and let it sit**** for at least 30 minutes!!!. Also I did follow instructions and covered the chicken while it was sitting in the flour mixture, I think this helps keep the coating wet. I used my cold oven to house the cookie sheets with the covered chicken. 20 min after I started heating up the oil in a cast iron dutch oven and by the time 30-35min passed the oil was hot and ready. The chicken is going to have a sticky paste coating when ready. One more thing, make sure your oil is hot and stays hot. Between 350*F to 375*F. I made chicken wings and boneless strips so I didn't have to cover and let cook for 30 min. 10-12 min is all my chicken needed. I gave the recipe 4 stars because it's pretty vague so you need to have some cooking experience to get a successful batch but the technique is the key**\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bruno\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious! I'm an amateur cook so I found this recipe so simple yet heavenly. The crispiness was perfect and the texture was amazing. The only problem was that it wasn't very flavorful but I fixed that problem by frying the chicken in coconut oil (instead of vegetable oil) with a pinch of chili oil. Apart from that, my family and I loved it! Will definitely cook again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Shelley Eckardt\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Elaine O Ty so much for this recipe. Fried chicken was something I made one time and it was ok for a first timer. BUT this made me a pro! I heavily seasoned the flour with Lawry's seasoned salt. Followed your instructions and it was better than Popeye's. It did take hours tho. That's the ONLY bad thing. This was some bangin chicken.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Angelica Pomarico\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Best fried chicken I\\u2019ve ever made hands down.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ant\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe turned out pretty good. It would have helped if the amount of salt and pepper were listed rather than. Season to taste made me a little skittish about adding to much salt. I will use this in the future with a few additions such as some brown sugar and more salt.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Patricia Hansen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this exactly as written. The chicken stayed juicy and tasted delicious. The coating browned up nicely and was crispy. However, it lacked flavor. I'm probably used to restaurant fried chicken, and maybe theirs is nothing like the real deal - I don't know. But this tasted like a crunchy coating of flour on my chicken. There was zero flavor. For the time and effort involved, it wasn't worth mine.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"L Lopez\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have made fried chicken with this recipe twice now and both times it has turned out wonderful. I will be using the recipe from now on!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cindy Nguyen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I just added some garlic powder and onion powder as others did. I made my own buttermilk. They were so crispy and so good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sandy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious! I deviated a little from the original recipe but not the advice to let the flowered chicken sit covered until it becomes a little pasty. This takes about a half hour. The recipe said to lower the heat, and cook for 30 minutes, then increase the heat again. I kept cooking the chicken at relatively high heat, just lowered slightly, and turned frequently. It turned out great.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Joe Denning\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this without brining the chicken on the first attempt and it was even better the next day cold. I am trying it this time and brining the chicken in kosher salt water with brown sugar , soy sauce, and olive oil. The chicken is much more moist and it didn't take nearly as long for it to turn the coating into a paste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bette McCracken\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Put in about 1 tsp of Adobo seasoning instead of salt and pepper. Very fussy about oil, so used peanut oil to fry. Very nice. Perfectly cooked, crispy, moist. I have no deep fryer, nor an appropriate thermometer. Put my gas \\\"power burner\\\" on at high for the browning, low for the slow cooking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"chrissyc\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Comes out perfect every time!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"dani\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"you real deserved many thank \\nthank alot\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Todd Marsh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was the perfect recipe for a novice like me, very easy to follow. I used seasoned salt instead of just adding the paprika on its own and loved the taste. Was too impatient to let the battered chicken sit and get that paste-like consistency as was suggested before frying lol, but I'll do it right next time and it still tasted great when I made it the first time regardless!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Crystal Elaine Lyons\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made exactly as directed. Easy, moist, &amp; crunchy crispy delicious. 1 change when I make this next time will be to season the flour and/or chicken as it was a little bland.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Frank Cogan\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"When my Mother made fried chicken I remember she coated the chicken with the flour mixture and put it in a skillet of hot oil to fry it. In this recipe they want you to brown it in the hot oil then cook for an additional 30 which I found odd. When the oil got to be the right high temp I ended up cooking each side for five to six minutes and it came out great. In fact the skin was super crispy and crunchy. No additional 30 min needed on a low temp. Just saying.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rebecca\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I use exactly the same frying method with my chicken but adding the buttermilk is great\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jennifer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely fantastic and absolutely perfect.\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/8805/crispy-fried-chicken/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/201/meat-and-poultry/chicken/\", \"name\": \"Chicken\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/650/meat-and-poultry/chicken/fried-chicken/\", \"name\": \"Fried Chicken Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/8805/crispy-fried-chicken/\", \"name\": \"Crispy Fried Chicken\"}}]}, \"reviewedBy\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Test Kitchen\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/allrecipes-test-kitchen-7553892\"}], \"lastReviewed\": \"2023-03-01T18:32:09.024-05:00\"}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Philly Cheesesteak Cabbage Wraps", "yields": "4 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT30M"}, "ingredients": ["8 large green cabbage leaves (from 1 head)&nbsp;", "2 tbsp. vegetable oil, divided&nbsp;", "1/2 large onion, thinly sliced&nbsp;", "2 large bell peppers, thinly sliced&nbsp;", "1 tsp. dried oregano&nbsp;", "Kosher salt&nbsp;", "Freshly ground black pepper", "1 lb. skirt steak, thinly sliced", "6 slices provolone&nbsp;"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large pot of boiling water, use tongs to dip cabbage leaves in water for 30 seconds to blanch. Place on a paper towel–lined plate to dry.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a large skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon of oil,&nbsp;then add onion and bell peppers. Season with oregano, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until onions and peppers are tender, about 5 minutes. Remove from skillet and add remaining tablespoon oil to skillet."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Add steak in a single layer and season with salt and pepper. Cook until steak is seared on one side, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook until the steak is seared on second side and cooked to your liking, about 2 minutes more for medium."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Add onion and peppers back to skillet and toss to combine. Top mixture with an even layer of provolone and cover skillet with a tight-fitting lid. Cook until cheese is melty, about 1 minute.&nbsp;"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Place a scoop of steak mixture onto the center of a cabbage leaf. Fold short end of leaf over mixture, then roll up the long side&nbsp;like a burrito with an open end. Repeat with remaining ingredients and serve immediately.&nbsp;"}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.681xw:1.00xh;0.173xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-02-19T19:31:55.547642Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Philly Cheesesteak Cabbage Wraps\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.681xw:1.00xh;0.173xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.681xw:1.00xh;0.173xw,0&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.681xw:1.00xh;0.173xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.9057777777777778xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=0.681xw:1.00xh;0.173xw,0&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=1xw:0.82801766437684xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a26279552/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps-recipe/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"http://instagram.com/delish\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/Delish/\"], \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/_assets/design-tokens/delish/static/images/logos/logo-jsonld.1396ea2.png\", \"width\": 312, \"height\": 60}, \"parentOrganization\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Hearst Corporation\"}}, \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a26279552/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps-recipe/\", \"isBasedOn\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a26279552/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps-recipe/\", \"dateModified\": \"2022-08-04T16:40:00Z EST\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"hasPart\": [{\"@type\": \"WebPageElement\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"cssSelector\": \".content-container\"}], \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://streaming.hearstdigitalstudios.com/23618268-fbf5-49b0-9b52-bda245ead611/video_rover_16x9_1080p_hd_1550603276_23522.mp4\", \"description\": \"Love Philly cheesesteaks but trying to lay off the carbs? This easy recipe solves that problem!\", \"duration\": \"PT58S\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://glimmer.hearstapps.com/amp.html?embedId=45abd45c-b5c8-401c-a942-59c2bfb0a759\", \"name\": \"These Cheesesteak Cabbage Wraps Are A Low-Carb Savior\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/philly-cheesesteak-cabbage-wraps1-1659544911.jpg?crop=1xw:0.82801766437684xh;center,top\", \"uploadDate\": \"2019-02-19T19:28:36.769807Z\", \"transcript\": \"(light upbeat music) - [Narrator] Have a cheesesteak! (upbeat dance music) - [Announcer] Oh god. Oh, Oh. - Dr. Cheesesteak.\"}, \"author\": {\"name\": \"Lena Abraham\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/author/17077/lena-abraham/\", \"@type\": \"Person\", \"description\": \"<p>Lena Abraham is a freelance contributor with Delish, and was formerly Senior Food Editor, where she developed and styled recipes for video and photo, and also stayed on top of current food trends. She\\u2019s been working in the food industry for over 10 years, and will argue that the best fish tacos in the world are made in New York. Don\\u2019t @ her.</p>\", \"jobTitle\": \"Contributor\", \"image\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/846121db-9644-42e0-a4fd-cf5d105bfdf9_1576786748.file\", \"email\": \"Lena.Abraham@hearst.com\", \"sameAs\": []}, \"name\": \"Philly Cheesesteak Cabbage Wraps\", \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT0S\", \"totalTime\": \"PT30M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"8 large green cabbage leaves (from 1 head)&nbsp;\", \"2 tbsp. vegetable oil, divided&nbsp;\", \"1/2 large onion, thinly sliced&nbsp;\", \"2 large bell peppers, thinly sliced&nbsp;\", \"1 tsp. dried oregano&nbsp;\", \"Kosher salt&nbsp;\", \"Freshly ground black pepper\", \"1 lb. skirt steak, thinly sliced\", \"6 slices provolone&nbsp;\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a large pot of boiling water, use tongs to dip cabbage leaves in water for 30 seconds to blanch. Place on a paper towel\\u2013lined plate to dry.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a large skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon of oil,&nbsp;then add onion and bell peppers. Season with oregano, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until onions and peppers are tender, about 5 minutes. Remove from skillet and add remaining tablespoon oil to skillet.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add steak in a single layer and season with salt and pepper. Cook until steak is seared on one side, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook until the steak is seared on second side and cooked to your liking, about 2 minutes more for medium.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add onion and peppers back to skillet and toss to combine. Top mixture with an even layer of provolone and cover skillet with a tight-fitting lid. Cook until cheese is melty, about 1 minute.&nbsp;\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Place a scoop of steak mixture onto the center of a cabbage leaf. Fold short end of leaf over mixture, then roll up the long side&nbsp;like a burrito with an open end. Repeat with remaining ingredients and serve immediately.&nbsp;\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"4 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeCategory\": [\"gluten-free\", \"low-carb\", \"30-minute meals\", \"weeknight meals\", \"dinner\"], \"description\": \"Cabbage makes these Philly Cheesesteaks from Delish.com the perfect low-carb option. \", \"keywords\": \"American, dinner, gluten-free, weeknight meals, Philly Cheesesteak Cabbage Wraps, cabbage wrap recipe, philly cheesesteak recipes, low-carb recipe, easy weeknight dinner recipes, cabbage recipes, \", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.3333335, \"reviewCount\": 6, \"worstRating\": 1, \"bestRating\": 5}, \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Sloppy Joes", "yields": ["6"], "time": {"prep": "PT5M", "cook": "PT30M", "total": "PT35M"}, "ingredients": ["1 pound lean ground beef", "0.25 cup chopped onion", "0.25 cup chopped green bell pepper", "0.75 cup ketchup, or to taste", "1 tablespoon brown sugar, or to taste", "1 teaspoon yellow mustard, or to taste", "0.5 teaspoon garlic powder", "salt and ground black pepper to taste", "6 hamburger buns, split"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir lean ground beef in the hot skillet until some of the fat starts to render, 3 to 4 minutes. Add onion and bell pepper; continue to cook until vegetables have softened and beef is cooked through, 3 to 5 more minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Stir in ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, and garlic powder; season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ALLMxp_JsluPy2d3x1ZZYr1AHxk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/24264-sloppy-joes-dianne-1x1-1-ca246f276afe4196b0ea921df2574466.jpg"}], "text": "Divide meat mixture evenly among hamburger buns."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Sloppy Joes\", \"datePublished\": \"2000-09-30T22:23:24.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-11-17T06:24:36.704-05:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tamara\"}], \"description\": \"Sloppy Joes are easy to make with lean ground beef, basic pantry ingredients, and hamburger buns. A comforting classic the whole family will enjoy!\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ALLMxp_JsluPy2d3x1ZZYr1AHxk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/24264-sloppy-joes-dianne-1x1-1-ca246f276afe4196b0ea921df2574466.jpg\", \"height\": 1500, \"width\": 1500}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/4JiVXV11-K3AjnAEN.mp4\", \"description\": \"This top-rated recipe for homemade sloppy joes will instantly take you back to your childhood. The classic ground beef recipe comes together in one pan with bell pepper, onion, and a salty-sweet \\u201csloppy\\u201d sauce that\\u2019s way better than the canned stuff. It\\u2019s a cheap way to feed a crowd (or your family), and it\\u2019s versatile enough for lunch or dinner. The best part? If you load extra meat into the bun, you can enjoy the bits that fall out of your sandwich as a dip with salty potato chips \\u2013 it\\u2019s almost like a sweet-and-salty nacho. This nostalgic sandwich is a comforting classic that\\u2019s famously easy to make and more delicious than it usually gets credit for.\", \"duration\": \"PT3M57S\", \"name\": \"How to Make Sloppy Joes | Easy Homemade Sloppy Joes\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/4JiVXV11/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2022-08-15T16:52:48.758-04:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Sloppy Joes\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.7\", \"ratingCount\": \"7790\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT30M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"243 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"11 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"57 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"0 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"14 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"6 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"397 mg\", \"fatContent\": \"16 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT5M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\", \"Lunch\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 pound lean ground beef\", \"0.25 cup chopped onion\", \"0.25 cup chopped green bell pepper\", \"0.75 cup ketchup, or to taste\", \"1 tablespoon brown sugar, or to taste\", \"1 teaspoon yellow mustard, or to taste\", \"0.5 teaspoon garlic powder\", \"salt and ground black pepper to taste\", \"6 hamburger buns, split\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir lean ground beef in the hot skillet until some of the fat starts to render, 3 to 4 minutes. Add onion and bell pepper; continue to cook until vegetables have softened and beef is cooked through, 3 to 5 more minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Stir in ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, and garlic powder; season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ALLMxp_JsluPy2d3x1ZZYr1AHxk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/24264-sloppy-joes-dianne-1x1-1-ca246f276afe4196b0ea921df2574466.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Divide meat mixture evenly among hamburger buns.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"6\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT35M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"madcrafts\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Oh my gosh these were so good. Hubby son and I loved them!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"vbaddict\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a lot less brown sugar, and instead of plain salt and pepper used Lawry's seasoned salt and pepper. Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Penipal\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love this recipe. I do a little bit of a change though. Instead of 3/4 cup of ketchup, i use 1/2 cup of ketchup and 1/4 cup of chili sauce. Since my husband isnt a fan of garlic, I dont add any garlic powder. We dont add any peppers either, but if I did, I\\u2019d only use red peppers. The sweet taste is perfect for us. Its definitely a keeper in my recipe book.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Anne Gilbert Harriman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the only sloppy joes I will make. No more Manwhich in my cupboard. I add a little more ketchup and some water because my husband eats them open face and wants them sloppy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bev R\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Didn't use peppers, not a fan, but the other ingredients made a fantastic sandwich that I genuinely liked very much.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Julia Perl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First time making Sloppy Joe from scratch. Delicious recipe. So much better than store made.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"gayle rivas\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made is just like the recipe but doubled it and it was delicious!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I did make changes, although I had not planned on it. First of all, I hadn\\u2019t thought about it but we only use Dijon mustard. The second change is that I only had 1/2 cup catsup on hand, so we ended up substituting the last quarter with Caribbean jerk sauce. It turned out great, so I am pretty sure the original recipe would have been please to us. Thank you for such an easy and tasty recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Micki Kremer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This has become my new go-to recipe. No more packaged mixes for me! I just eliminate the green pepper, as I don't care for that. Used all the rest of it and made a quick dinner with enough left over for another meal. I simply freeze the leftover and defrost as needed. Love this!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cindy Abella\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I absolutely loved this!! Thank you so much for recipe. After reading reviews the only difference was using 1/2 chili sauce and 1/2 ketchup as I had some on hand and wanted to use up. I also toasted buns and added a slice of cheese on top. This will be a regular addition to our weekly menu.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Loves2cook\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Outstanding, I made it just like the recipe directions. With 1 exception. I substituted 1 minced clove of Elephant garlic for the powdered garlic. It was awesome. Thanks Nicole for yet another great recipe to add to my file. No more CANNED MIX again ever.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Patty A.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was excellent as written. Just in time for a quick dinner when all ingredients in pantry and freezer\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Castaway\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My kids loved it! Way better then the can!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe! I add sliced black olives to ours\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tom Zimmer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I always use yellow mustard on top, adds a tang and offsets the sweetness.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'm from small town Iowa, and our \\\"sloppy joes\\\" AKA \\\"taverns\\\" never had green pepper nor brown sugar in the recipe. We also BOILED the ground beef, onion, Ketchup, water and a hint of mustard..not fried it..therefore using the leanest ground beef available. Church stands at town and county fairs always preferred this method and served the sandwiches on warmed buns with a dill pickle slice ( or two).\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Felice\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Only difference for me was that my Mom would toast the buns. Yum!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jim Shanks\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've made this recipe before, but I do it now with Chili Sauce rather than Ketchup. My wife doesn't like Ketchup and it seemed a good substitute. In my opinion, it's better.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kormath\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is almost identical to the recipe i've been eating for nearly 50 years. only difference is we use seasoning salt to season the ground beef after draining the grease and before mixing in the ketchup and mustard and stuff. Awesome to see others enjoying a classic like this. My favorite has always been sloppy joes and homemade coleslaw, gotta have a crunch with all the soft textures of the sloppy joes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Paulette Jolivette Mishali\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Hubby loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Dena Schultz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Added onion powder cause hubby doesn't like texture of oinions in a receipe. Added smoke paprika for kick. Yum's for tummy's says everyone else!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bkipps\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My family loved it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Susan S.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was easy and quick to make. I made the recipe as written. The meat mixture was very good though I will use less mustard next time.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"tlemily\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good basic sloppy Joe recipe! I just added a little tomato paste, cider vinegar, worchestershire, and a little water. It was excellent!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sharon\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added a 1/2 can of tomato sauce with 1/2 cup of ketchup. I did not add the mustard this time. Family thought it was amazing. So did I!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"LC\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the recipe I've been using for a long time. The only change I make is using 1/2 cup ketchup &amp; 1/4 cup Sweet Baby Ray's barbecue sauce. Sometimes I add a little water if it seems to dry. This brings the rating up to a 5!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"dinner is ready\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is fantastic. Soooo good and soooo easy. Tastes so fresh and flavorful. I will never buy a canned mix again. This only takes a few more minutes than it does to open a can of preservatives. I do make 1 change and that is I use a red pepper instead of green pepper. Try topping it with a slice of cheese. Mmm. Thanks for a great recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Asia S\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Giving 5 stars cause I didn\\u2019t follow your recipe exactly but close enough to know this recipe was amazing. I used tomato paste, ketchup and water. Also I wanted more spice so added 1 Serrano pepper and some bell pepper. Other than that followed everything else. Recipe was amazing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mary Benedetto McGlynn\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy dish and tastes great! We use it when we go camping and other trips that way we have something easy for dinner when we arrive at our destination. Works out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Octavia Graves\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kyle&Kev'sMom\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019ve been making this for at least 20 years ( when you had to print them out! ) since my kids were little. It\\u2019s perfect every time always enjoyed and looked forward to. It\\u2019s a real easy quick delicious dinner!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jack Browning\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A fast easy and very satisfying meal that will please almost anyone. Just walk past the Manwich\\u00a9 can and go get extra ketchup because you will want to do this again and again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I really enjoyed this recipe. Personally, I love onion, so I octupled (yes, you read that right) the amount of onion (half red onion, half vidalia) and left out the bell pepper because I didn't have any on hand. I added a teaspoon each of apple cider vinegar and worcestershire sauce, I added some smoked paprika as well to incorporate a little smoky flavor, and doubled the amount of sauce as one review I saw suggested. I was happy with the consistency and sauciness. However, it came out a little on the sweet side (I suspect because I doubled the sauce and added all the extra onion). Nothing a little cayenne pepper couldn't fix! The balance of sweet and spicy wound up being quite delicious. Next time I would leave out the brown sugar entirely, I personally don't think it was necessary given the alterations I made. This was the first time I made slopy joes myself and I was very happy with the results!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"twin1\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delish as written. For the person who said it was so sweet her kids wouldn\\u2019t eat it, excuse me? One tablespoon of brown sugar for one pond of ground beef is not too sweet.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michelle Hefley\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added a couple of shakes of Worcestershire sauce and left out the green pepper..delicious!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"beau6974\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Wonderful recipe. Works like a charm. It's so easy that when I used to run out to Burger King etc. I recall this and in less time that I could get there and back I've got great sloppy joes. My grown daughters lament I never made this for them as kids. You will not use manwhich again. Sometimes I don't use the green pepper as I may not have any. Some like it with and some without but they. like it either way. Thank you very much.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The best!!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jenna Madrid\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I think the recipe needs more chopped onion, more chopped green bell pepper and less ketchup to taste but if you add pasta salad to the recipe it turns out delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mbenton\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love it! The only difference that I make to the recipe...is double it!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I just made this, and my baby grandson who is 15 months old loved it so much that he ate a sandwich and a half! The rest of the family liked it too! Thanks for a simple recipe with sneaky veggies that I'll make over and over!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe! Actually added a touch more sugar for the kids, but the recipe as written was great as well!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very simple to whip together on a busy weeknight. Great as is. You can modify this a million ways to simply use what you have on hand.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I wish people would stop giving recipes 5 stars after changing everything about it. I made this because it had a good rating. But I didn't read the reviews until after. I used half the sugar, but it was still way, way too sweet. My kids won't eat it. I ended up throwing half in the garbage.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved it and will definitely make again instead of using canned manwhich. Tweaked a few things. I used condensed tomato soup and tomato paste for the ketchup, more garlic powder, added yellow and orange peppers, added 1 teaspoon chili powder and doubled the sauce as I like it to simmer in the oven with baked beans and mac &amp; cheese!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cyndi D.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used the recipe as a starting point. I added about 3 T. worcestershire sauce, substituted the green bell pepper for 1 yellow, 1 red, and 1 orange sweet pepper, omitted the sugar, doubled the garlic powder, and substituted dijon mustard for the yellow mustard. Yum!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Walter Cote\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Love this recipe! Topped it off with dill pickle slices and a Buffalo ranch sauce on a pretzel bun. Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Caryn Jaeschke\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only thing I changed was that I made it with 1/4 cup red bell pepper and poblano pepper. (we're not green bell pepper fans) They were delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Super easy and super good, I like clean food no additives, this was easy and good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was amazing! I used Anaheim peppers instead of bell (because that\\u2019s what I had) and I doubled the sauce. I think it would have been very dry if I hadn\\u2019t. But the flavor\\u2014SO GOOD \\ud83d\\ude0a\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the recipe I have been looking for! Although I hate to be \\u201cthat person\\u201d who compliments the recipe but changes everything, I did make one minor tweak. Instead of 3/4 cup of ketchup, I used half ketchup and half Heinz chili sauce. Turned out perfect! No more Manwich!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lisicdrake4\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Had some leftover meat from tacos I made. My child wanted sloppy joes so I took the leftover taco meat made this sauce and my kid loved it. Thank you will make again. Made it exactly as the recipe stated.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Sloppy Joe doesn't need to be complicated, does it? If you don't like the stronger taste of green pepper, try red or orange or yellow. I also increase the wet ingredients because I like to let it simmer longer. Like almost anything like this, even better when reheated.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Just as I had growing up as a kid. Before Manwich\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was very good. I used sugar free ketchup and coconut sugar instead of brown sugar.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stephanie Geyer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I use ground turkey, double the sauce ingredients, and add can of diced tomatoes- no salt added. Very good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rhondalr\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was good. I didn\\u2019t add any sugar, as the ketchup was sweet enough. Will be making it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cassie Hodgson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I didn't add the brown sugar and I used garlic salt instead of the powder and it still was good\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Candaceabc\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tasty recipe, but the proportions seem to be off. There is no way this would feed 6 people unless the portions were very small.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"First time trying it\\u2026no ketchup in the house so i used tomato paste an spicy tomato sauce\\u2026other than that, more onion\\u2026.pretty simple and tasty!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have never made sloppy Joe like this before. I will have to say it was very tasty. \\ud83d\\ude01\\ud83d\\udc4d\\ud83d\\udc4d\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Katie Pederson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Sooo yummy! If you are looking for a more savory sloppy joe, this is it! I do not use peppers in mine.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Celina Clavero\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious, great flavor easy to make with items you already have in the pantry and fridge.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cherri\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made it as the recipe suggests but I did add just a tad of minced garlic and a little more of everything else because I like it \\\"saucy\\\" and moist. Few ingredients which makes it easy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"dhisrael\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is just what I had in high School in the Lunchroom, what my wife and I have cooked since we were fifteen years old and dating. A Great Recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"iuokie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Better than what you get in a can. I added extra ketchup because it was a little too dry for my liking.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is awesome the way it is. Only thing I did different was use a colored bell pepper instead of a green one. Love this sloppy Joe. I do not understand why people give it four or five stars and then say they change the recipe from the regional. Makes no sense. I rated it a five with out changing it. Just make sure you add a tad water every so often or the dish will stick to the pan while cooking it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Elad Fitz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good, a little sweet for us, but that's my fault knowing catsup is already sweetened, and I did think about that but still put in the brown sugar.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Arlene Cumberbatch\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My husband's new fav!!! #HimPlate\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"it was awesome\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Almost exactly like my mom used to make\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"IS THAT DELICIOUS OR WHAT!!!?\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ann Kovarik\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It is the best recipe for SLOPPY JOES! Instead of 1/4 C of green pepper (gives me acid reflux) so I substituted it with my homemade pickle relish! I made 20 LBS for a gathering with adults and children. They couldn't get enough of it! Making it again tonight!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"SHuG68\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is super fast and so good! Sometimes we put cheese on our sandwiches, wrap in foil and bake for a bit. Amazing! Never thought I'd feel this way about sloppy joes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Yiskah Sarah Cafazzo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I doubled the recipe subbed onion powder for the garlic powder (I'm allergic) and used a sweet twister pepper for the bell pepper and coconut sugar for the brown sugar. Also I added a few shakes of liquid smoke and a sprinkling of nutritional yeast. These were a HUGE hit with the kiddos and they requested that it be added to the weekly rotation! Super easy and super yum!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mara\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Mmmmmmmm. I made it exactly as stated, with ONE change: I skipped the brown sugar, as it was PLENTY sweet from the ketchup. (If your taste buds are different, you can always add the sugar later). I will cease looking for any other sloppy joe recipe as this can't be topped, IMO! As other reviewers have said, it REALLY IS better than Manwich! But the best reason to keep it: it is easy, quick, few ingredients, and all were on hand!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have used this recipe many times. It doesn't need any changes. It is hands down the easiest and most delicious sloppy joes I've ever made. I don't always have bell peppers but I always have everything else in this recipe, as do most households. Thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"poc2484\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Don\\u2019t think it needs the brown sugar. Would increase the garlic powder.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Awesome! Never made from scratch. Tweaked it a bit since we love garlic and anything with brown sugar. Change from green bell peppers to yellow and red. Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sue Gibson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is the only sloppy joe my hubby will eat, and that's saying a lot considering he's not a fan of sloppy joes!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've made these a few times for carry-ins at work and at least one person has asked for the recipe each time. It's a keeper!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shell2\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Double the sauce\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lisa\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious. Thank you\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Green Witch\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"BF really liked it, I thought it was a bit too sweet. Last time I made it I cut the brown sugar in half and added a bit of worcestershire.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sparky\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is my go to recipe! I also add a splash of Worcestershire sauce as I like that flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"leigh0311\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this recipe tonight, using a toasted bagel. I used posada instead of ketchup which reduced the sweetness from sugar. I added a wee pinch of chili flakes for a bit of heat. I had sone leftover homemade coleslaw as a side. It was a tasty and easy meal. Easily adaptable to what you have on hand.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Claudine Bullough Achter\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Yummy ! Reminds me of my childhood.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Islandgirl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added chicken broth to mixture to make more sauce!! Didn\\u2019t use bell peppers. My kids love it!! Thanks\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Missy Helwig\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My \\\"go to\\\" standard recipe. Couldn't be easier or tastier. Nothing extra and no changes either!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ButtonsBrooks\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019ve never liked sloppy joes before but every few years I retry them and these were delicious!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cathy P.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I mixed the onions in last just to make them more crispy. The recipe was really good! My husband even complimented me on it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bonnie615\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I read about all of the modifications and we had a very big one. We are vegan and whenever I want comfort food, I simply find the most popular recipe here and use it for a vegan version. So our base was a mix of lentils, black beans, mushrooms, and quinoa but I followed everything else and this recipe was delicious! We've made three batches in the last week!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Haven't had sloppy joes in probably over a decade, so I decided to try this out! I followed the recipe exactly as it said. Super quick and easy and I only had to spend less than $10 for buns, ground beef, onion, and green pepper since I had the rest of the ingredients at home already. Delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"PlumGirl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Needed to feed a large crowd for a get together of 60 and used this recipe. So very tasty and easy! Definitely a crowd-pleaser!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sweet Pea\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely perfect:)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made the recipe, ingredients were great together. I did add 1/2 C of diced celery and 1 T of tomato paste, thought the ingredients blended with the recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"WORKING2PAY\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"YUMMY So easy to make and delicious. Just like mom made.. No canned sauces for us!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Argyletraveler\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Have already made it twice. The second time with ground turkey and it was as good, even better, than with beef. I too doubled the sauce. Used half ketchup, half BBQ sauce, jalape\\u00f1o instead of bell pepper, no sugar and added a few drops cayenne garlic Tabasco (we like it more spicy than sweet). Grilled the buns and added some shredded cheddar cheese. An easy, delish dinner!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My husband doesn't even like sloppy joes but really liked this recipe. I loved it as well.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I had made hamburgers for company but had some raw hamburger left over and wanted to use it in a different way. I remembered my Mom making it so thought I would see what was on All Recipes. I added some green chilies and some black olives and Baby Ray's in place of ketchup.\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/24264/sloppy-joes-ii/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/251/main-dish/sandwiches/\", \"name\": \"Sandwich Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/14930/main-dish/sandwiches/sloppy-joes/\", \"name\": \"Sloppy Joe Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/24264/sloppy-joes-ii/\", \"name\": \"Sloppy Joes\"}}]}, \"reviewedBy\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Test Kitchen\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/allrecipes-test-kitchen-7553892\"}], \"lastReviewed\": \"2023-11-17T06:24:36.704-05:00\"}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Classic Risotto", "yields": "4 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT10M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT50M"}, "ingredients": ["4 c. store-bought or homemade low-sodium chicken broth", "5 tbsp. unsalted butter, divided", "1 medium white onion, finely chopped (about 1 1/2 c.)", "2 1/2 tsp. kosher salt, divided", "1 1/2 c. arborio or carnaroli rice", "1 c. dry white wine", "3 oz. Parmesan,&nbsp;finely grated (about 1 1/2 c.)&nbsp;", "3/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In a medium pot over medium-high heat, heat broth until steaming. Reduce heat to low, cover, and keep warm."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, melt 4 tablespoons butter. Add onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, translucent, and sweet to the taste, 8 to 10 minutes. Add rice and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent around the edges, 1 to 2 minutes more."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Add wine and cook, stirring, until liquid is absorbed, 3 to 4 minutes. Add 3 cups warm broth, stir to incorporate, and bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is just tender, 10 to 15 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Uncover and add 1/2 cup warm broth. Return to a simmer over medium heat and continue to cook, stirring, until broth is absorbed, 1 to 2 minutes more. Taste and, if rice is still slightly al dente, add remaining 1/2 cup broth and continue to simmer, stirring, until absorbed and rice is tender."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Remove from heat. Stir in Parmesan, pepper, and remaining 1 tablespoon butter until cheese and butter are melted; season with remaining 2 teaspoons salt, if needed. Serve immediately."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.5xw:1xh;center,top&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2019-11-25T23:45:23.133967Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Classic Risotto\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.5xw:1xh;center,top&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.5xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.5xw:1xh;center,top&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.6666666666666666xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.5xw:1xh;center,top&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.8888888888888888xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a29786303/risotto-rice-recipe/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"http://instagram.com/delish\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/Delish/\"], \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/_assets/design-tokens/delish/static/images/logos/logo-jsonld.1396ea2.png\", \"width\": 312, \"height\": 60}, \"parentOrganization\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Hearst Corporation\"}}, \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a29786303/risotto-rice-recipe/\", \"isBasedOn\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a29786303/risotto-rice-recipe/\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-10-17T20:38:00Z EST\", \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://streaming.hearstdigitalstudios.com/73b841b8-2901-468a-a5b0-553b627ca935/video_rover_16x9_1080p_hd_1697574639_51072.mp4\", \"description\": \"Arborio rice is simmered in chicken broth and finished with grated parmesan and black pepper for a risotto that\\u2019s as simple to make as it is delicious to eat.\", \"duration\": \"PT7M11S\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://glimmer.hearstapps.com/amp.html?embedId=194734a4-ee1e-4dce-9cfa-57dfaa919977\", \"name\": \"We've Discovered The Best Hack For Making Perfect Risotto Every Time\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/del089923-risotto-web-001-ab-index-64e7a1083b54e.jpg?crop=0.8888888888888888xw:1xh;center,top\", \"uploadDate\": \"2023-10-17T20:37:25.285725Z\", \"transcript\": \"- Hey everyone, it's TA in the Delish Kitchen and I'm gonna show you how to make the creamiest risotto you've ever had. Most people think that risotto is crazy complicated and difficult, but this recipe has just a few ingredients and very little stirring involved but you still get that creamy, comforting result. Let's get started. Let's talk about the star of the show, the risotto rice. To make risotto, you're going to need either arborio or carnaroli rice. So let's talk about those two. They're very similar. Both are short grained and they have this very starchy coating on the outside and that's the thing that's essential to get that creamy, creamy texture we're looking for. Arborio rice, when it's cooked, will cook a little bit faster and also can go mushy faster if you overcook it. Carnaroli, on the other hand, is going to hold its shape and appear more distinct, even when it's fully cooked. And for that reason, I honestly prefer it. This is the one that we're going to be using today. So the first thing that we're going to do is to get our broth in a pot and get it all warmed up, just to a bare simmer so that it's ready when we need it for our risotto. Next to the rice, the broth is the most important ingredient in risotto because whatever your broth tastes like, your risotto's gonna taste like. So actually taste your broth. Like, when you buy it from the store, actually try it. If you don't like what it tastes like just on its own, you are not gonna like what your risotto ends up tasting like. Another thing, definitely always get low sodium. Low sodium broth is great because it allows you to control the salt level of your dish. You can always add more salt if it's not salty enough, you can't take it away. While our broth is warming up, we are gonna get our onions started so we are gonna add some butter to our pan and then the chopped onions along with a little pinch of salt. We are gonna cook those down until they're nice and sweet and translucent, should take about eight to 10 minutes. Our broth is simmering now so we're gonna cut the heat and cover it. We just want it to stay warm until we need it. All right, let's see if these are ready. (light music) Yep, we're there. It's soft, it's tender, but not mushy, and it's sweet to the taste. It also tastes like butter. So we are ready now to add our rice. We toast the rice, just for a couple minutes, to intensify the flavor. Toasting is the same thing basically as caramelizing. It's the same thing as when you sear a steak and get those lovely brown bits on the outside. It's gonna deepen and develop the flavor and just make a much more delicious risotto. We're gonna toast this rice, stirring, stirring all the while, just until it starts to go slightly golden on the edges. You don't wanna take it too far, just slightly. See how this is all just nice and golden just around the edges, not too much? That's where you want it to be when you add your wine. Lots of people think they should go out and buy cooking wine to cook with. You don't need to, just use whatever you would drink. So here I have a nice chardonnay, that's gonna be perfect. Pinot Grigio would be great too. Seriously, whatever you like to drink with your dinner. One exception, you do not wanna use champagne in that, just save it for yourself. Once the wine is gone in, you're gonna just stir it until the liquid is absorbed completely. That should take about three to four minutes. As you can see, most of the liquid is absorbed and all you can really see are those starchy trails the rice is leaving, which is just what you want. Now it's time to add our broth. All right, so now we are gonna take our broth and pour three quarters of it, which is about three cups, into our risotto. We're gonna bring this up to a boil, reduce the heat to low, cover and simmer until the rice is just barely tender, which is about 15 minutes. Most people think that it is sacrilegious to put this much broth in and that you need to add it a little bit at a time, but you really don't. The natural starch on the outside of the rice is what is gonna make this risotto creamy, not the constant stirring. Yes, you should add the last bit of broth little by little because you don't always know how much you're gonna need. I might need this full cup, I might need only half of a cup and you don't wanna drown your risotto so you're going to finish the last bit slowly by hand stirring, but most of it, it can just do its thing by itself. That rice has got it covered. It doesn't need you. So our rice has been simmering for 15 minutes. The liquid is absorbed and it looks like it should be just about tender. This is the point when we are going to start adding in the remaining broth, bit by bit, like you would think you would traditionally. At this point, the liquid that we just added is absorbed but before we add the rest, we're gonna taste and see if it's tender. You don't want it mushy at all. You just want it to be al dente. (light music) It's almost there. It just needs the rest of that broth. (light music) All right, that's ready. It's tender, but it's not mushy and that's exactly where you want it to be. We're gonna cut the heat now and finish it off. So to finish our risotto, we're just gonna add a little bit more butter, a lot of Parmesan cheese, pepper, and salt to taste. It's creamy and comforting, and while it did take some care and attention, it definitely did not take 30 minutes of nonstop stirring in front of the stove. This is comfort food that you can make on a weeknight. It can be ready for your family in no time flat but it's also elegant and classy enough that you can make it maybe for a date night, maybe to impress. It's rich and just so comforting and soul-satisfying. This is the king of comfort food. The broth is giving that incredible, just simple but dependable back note of flavor. You get the nice acidity from the wine that's been cooked out and then the Parmesan comes in to give that rich nuttiness and that little bit of salt. And the black pepper is the perfect accent that goes over the top. If you have leftovers, which I doubt, you can always save them in the refrigerator and then the next day, you can roll this day old risotto into balls and deep fry it, make some arancini, delicious. So for this and other comfort food recipes, stick around on delish.com. (upbeat music)\"}, \"author\": {\"name\": \"Taylor Ann Spencer\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/author/233853/taylor-ann-spencer/\", \"@type\": \"Person\", \"description\": \"<p>Taylor Ann Spencer is the assistant food editor at Delish, where she develops recipes, creates recipe videos, and styles food. With a background in writing and theater as well as professional cooking, she enjoys sharing her love for global flavors and all things baking through informational posts, hosted videos, and just plain everyday conversations. When she's not cooking, she's brainstorming her next culinary mash-up. Mac 'n' cheese chili rellenos, anyone?</p>\", \"jobTitle\": \"Assistant Food Editor\", \"image\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/37b1c6a7-d6d1-4464-8eaf-a6e9b24393a1_1674012081.file\", \"sameAs\": []}, \"name\": \"Classic Risotto\", \"prepTime\": \"PT10M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT0S\", \"totalTime\": \"PT50M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"4 c. store-bought or homemade low-sodium chicken broth\", \"5 tbsp. unsalted butter, divided\", \"1 medium white onion, finely chopped (about 1 1/2 c.)\", \"2 1/2 tsp. kosher salt, divided\", \"1 1/2 c. arborio or carnaroli rice\", \"1 c. dry white wine\", \"3 oz. Parmesan,&nbsp;finely grated (about 1 1/2 c.)&nbsp;\", \"3/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In a medium pot over medium-high heat, heat broth until steaming. Reduce heat to low, cover, and keep warm.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, melt 4 tablespoons butter. Add onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, translucent, and sweet to the taste, 8 to 10 minutes. Add rice and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent around the edges, 1 to 2 minutes more.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add wine and cook, stirring, until liquid is absorbed, 3 to 4 minutes. Add 3 cups warm broth, stir to incorporate, and bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Uncover and add 1/2 cup warm broth. Return to a simmer over medium heat and continue to cook, stirring, until broth is absorbed, 1 to 2 minutes more. Taste and, if rice is still slightly al dente, add remaining 1/2 cup broth and continue to simmer, stirring, until absorbed and rice is tender.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Remove from heat. Stir in Parmesan, pepper, and remaining 1 tablespoon butter until cheese and butter are melted; season with remaining 2 teaspoons salt, if needed. Serve immediately.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"4 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [\"Italian\"], \"recipeCategory\": [\"date night\", \"dinner party\", \"romantic meals\", \"weeknight meals\", \"comfort food\", \"rice\"], \"description\": \"Arborio rice is simmered in chicken broth and finished with grated parmesan and black pepper for a risotto that\\u2019s as simple to make as it is delicious to eat. \\r\\n\", \"keywords\": \"Italian, Most Popular, comfort food, date night, dinner party, rice, romantic meals, weeknight meals\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \" 724 Calories\", \"fatContent\": \"30 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"18 g\", \"transFatContent\": \"0 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"76 mg\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1181 mg\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"68 g\", \"fiberContent\": \"3 g\", \"sugarContent\": \"3 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"30 g\"}, \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Chef John&#39;s Buttermilk Fried Chicken", "yields": ["4"], "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT25M", "total": "PT410M"}, "ingredients": ["1 (3 1/2) pound chicken, cut into 8 pieces", "1 teaspoon black pepper", "1 teaspoon salt", "1 teaspoon paprika", "0.5 teaspoon white pepper", "0.25 teaspoon dried rosemary", "0.25 teaspoon ground thyme", "0.25 teaspoon dried oregano", "0.25 teaspoon dried sage", "0.25 teaspoon cayenne pepper", "2 cups buttermilk", "2 cups flour", "1 teaspoon salt", "0.5 teaspoon paprika", "0.5 teaspoon cayenne pepper", "0.5 teaspoon garlic powder", "0.5 teaspoon white pepper", "0.5 teaspoon onion powder", "2.5 quarts peanut oil for frying"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Toss chicken pieces, black pepper, salt, paprika, white pepper, rosemary, thyme, oregano, sage, and cayenne together in a large bowl."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Stir in buttermilk until chicken is evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Combine flour, salt, paprika, cayenne, garlic powder, white pepper, and onion powder in a large shallow dish."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Remove chicken from buttermilk and dredge each piece in seasoned flour; shake off any excess and transfer to a plate."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Heat peanut oil in a large Dutch oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Add chicken pieces to the hot oil and fry for 10 minutes. Turn chicken pieces and fry for another 10 to 15 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C)."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "image": [{"@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Y60mehwWKTGE6B-xuFe2cz7qR14=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/3548106-chef-johns-buttermilk-fried-chicken-CHEF-JOHN-1x1-1-564e58d7b77e4aaa8330aa7ce8734676.jpg"}], "text": "Transfer fried chicken to a cooling rack set over a paper towel-lined baking sheet. Let sit for 10 minutes before serving."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\", \"NewsArticle\"], \"headline\": \"Chef John&#39;s Buttermilk Fried Chicken\", \"datePublished\": \"2012-02-08T13:41:55.000-05:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-08-11T12:57:20.165-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chef John\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/author/chef-john/\"}], \"description\": \"Buttermilk fried chicken that&#39;s crispy and tender. Whole chicken pieces are soaked in buttermilk, coated in seasoned flour, then fried until crisp.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Y60mehwWKTGE6B-xuFe2cz7qR14=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/3548106-chef-johns-buttermilk-fried-chicken-CHEF-JOHN-1x1-1-564e58d7b77e4aaa8330aa7ce8734676.jpg\", \"height\": 1000, \"width\": 1000}, \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/w3Tc7LxP-GaWYtJLt.mp4\", \"description\": \"Get ready to experience the ultimate comfort food with Chef John's Buttermilk Fried Chicken recipe. In this mouthwatering video, join us as we embark on a culinary journey to create perfectly crispy and tender fried chicken. Chef John shares his tried-and-true techniques, from marinating the chicken in buttermilk to creating a flavorful coating and achieving the ideal frying temperature. Learn his secrets for locking in moisture and achieving that coveted golden crust. With each bite, you'll savor the succulent and juicy chicken that will have your taste buds dancing with delight. Elevate your fried chicken game with this classic recipe that will leave you craving more.\", \"duration\": \"PT4M7S\", \"name\": \"Buttermilk Fried Chicken\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/w3Tc7LxP/poster.jpg?width=720\", \"uploadDate\": \"2023-06-15T13:36:44.556-04:00\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Chef John&#39;s Buttermilk Fried Chicken\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"487\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT25M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"1262 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"56 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"179 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"3 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"66 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"16 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"1443 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"6 g\", \"fatContent\": \"85 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"Southern\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"1 (3 1/2) pound chicken, cut into 8 pieces\", \"1 teaspoon black pepper\", \"1 teaspoon salt\", \"1 teaspoon paprika\", \"0.5 teaspoon white pepper\", \"0.25 teaspoon dried rosemary\", \"0.25 teaspoon ground thyme\", \"0.25 teaspoon dried oregano\", \"0.25 teaspoon dried sage\", \"0.25 teaspoon cayenne pepper\", \"2 cups buttermilk\", \"2 cups flour\", \"1 teaspoon salt\", \"0.5 teaspoon paprika\", \"0.5 teaspoon cayenne pepper\", \"0.5 teaspoon garlic powder\", \"0.5 teaspoon white pepper\", \"0.5 teaspoon onion powder\", \"2.5 quarts peanut oil for frying\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Toss chicken pieces, black pepper, salt, paprika, white pepper, rosemary, thyme, oregano, sage, and cayenne together in a large bowl.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Stir in buttermilk until chicken is evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Combine flour, salt, paprika, cayenne, garlic powder, white pepper, and onion powder in a large shallow dish.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Remove chicken from buttermilk and dredge each piece in seasoned flour; shake off any excess and transfer to a plate.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Heat peanut oil in a large Dutch oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Add chicken pieces to the hot oil and fry for 10 minutes. Turn chicken pieces and fry for another 10 to 15 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Y60mehwWKTGE6B-xuFe2cz7qR14=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/3548106-chef-johns-buttermilk-fried-chicken-CHEF-JOHN-1x1-1-564e58d7b77e4aaa8330aa7ce8734676.jpg\"}], \"text\": \"Transfer fried chicken to a cooling rack set over a paper towel-lined baking sheet. Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"4\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT410M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Furbalotopus Furbamayovich\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tried this today, and it's really, really good. Just the perfect flavor. I say double the flour mixture though, especially if you are making tenders.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BABYLADY907\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've prepared this recipe a few times. First time following instructions as written. Lately I've been using whole chicken wings. Double each spice to kick it up a bit. Overnight marinade makes all the difference in the world. Couldn't tell much of a difference between using vegetable oil verses peanut oil. This is a keeper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"375F for 20-25 minutes, and you'll be fishing out a few pieces of charcoal. I did mine at 325F for about 12 minutes and it was perfectly done. Also, as another poster mentioned, double the spices in the flour mixture. Other than those two things, it turned out great.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Meryll Dawson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have questions. This sounds wonderful but I can\\u2019t help but question the calorie count for two pieces of chicken. On the KFC site the extra crispy version of a breast is around 400 calories and a thigh is about 300 calories. The extra crispy versions are the higher counts and they are coming in at almost half the calorie count. I read the disclaimer regarding the buttermilk, but\\u2026? It just feels off to me and I do rely on nutritional values when looking at recipes. I\\u2019m very aware that this would not be a diets friend but I believe there is room for everything in a balanced diet.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lacyanne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"That is some tasty fried chicken! As a southern woman, I am expected to impress with my fried chicken skills. However, that really wasn't something I had much experience cooking. Thankfully CJ saves the day. The husband was very impressed! I made as written minus the peanut oil as I only had canola. This will be the go-to, special occasion recipe from here on out. Thanks, Chef John!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"michele\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very yummy, tasted almost like KFC !!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jean Breslin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy taste was wonderful\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Quilter\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used boneless skinless chicken breasts and soaked them for 6 hours. I then cut them into 1/2\\\" thick pieces and returned them to the buttermilk spice mix before flouring them. Initially I tried air frying one breast but the flour stuck quite badly to the rack. The next three were fried in a pan with about 3/8\\\" of canola oil. My family loved these, even the air fried ones. We will be having the pan fried ones from now on. They are better than any we have eaten out!! Thanks Chef John. As my husband says - \\\"You can never go wrong using a Chef John recipe!\\\".\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Amazing\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made a few small tweaks to this, and it\\u2019s my new goto fried chicken recipe. My only changes are replacing a quarter of the flour with cornstarch and another quarter with baking powder; and doubling the cayenne pepper but subbing with Aleppo pepper because that\\u2019s what I have on hand. I also find that if I pour a little of the buttermilk marinade into the flour mixture and stir it up to make little lentil sized clumps, the crunch factor is through the roof. Really far better than anything I\\u2019ve gotten out\\u2026 maybe ever? Thank you Chef John!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"pandasmommy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So the only thing I did different was fry the chicken in duck fat that I bought off Amazon. Really amazing.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tara Renner\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Although I tried to keep my oil at the right temp, the outer skin still burned. I think the trick is to keep the pan covered to keep the heat even so the meat cooks evenly. Remove the lid at the end to crisp the skin.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"James McAllister\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"End product is good, only things I took off stars for is -1 for the cooks note, it says to hold in 300 degree oil for 25 minutes? -1 for using peanut oil, it doesn't improve the quality of the finished product but is more expensive and more likely to have allergic reactions.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy recipe few steps the only reason I didn't give him a five-star. Was very very unhealthy I'd like to see his version of air frying. But to his credit he did say how many times you make this once a year he obviously doesn't know how much we love fried chicken around here. Lol order in the South how unhealthy people are how they will eat fried chicken about every 3 or 4 days if they can.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely delicious. Needed a purpose to use up my homemade (butter)buttermilk so i tried this recipe. I did 10 pieces of legs and thighs and all night soak vs recipie's 6 hours and 8 pieces. Had a tangy sweet taste. I still have some leftover buttermilk so i can do it again. \\ud83d\\ude0b\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"jana\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"bland\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kathryn Matousek\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019ve made this recipe before, but this time I soaked the chicken overnight in the buttermilk and spices which makes all the difference! We fried the chicken 5 minutes on each side, then put the pieces on a cookie sheet in the oven at 400 until they were done (25 minutes?). The meat was soooo tender and flavorful!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sal.harman1\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We subbed the flour for Gluten Free Plain Flour and it was AMAZINGGGGGGGG\\n\\nBest GF coated chicken I've ever had in my life. So tasty. So juicy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"1653863\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I only used 2 1/2 cups of flour and it was plenty.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JoeP\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made this with just chicken legs &amp; thighs. Came out very tasty complemented with mac &amp; cheese and green salad side. Has some pieces leftover so ate them cold the next day. Still yummy.\\n\\nI did not have buttermilk so I combined 2 tbs of white vinegar and 2 cups of whole milk. Let is sit on the counter for 30 minutes. Then poured over chicken in a zip lock bag in the refrigerator for only 4 hours. I would have let in soak longer but started late.\\n\\nCooked in a air fryer at 380 degrees for 25 minutes., turning once.\\n\\nAdded to my favorites and will make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"LifenDaBurg\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only thing I changed was the flour. I didn't have any on hand, so I used pancake mix. \\n\\nTurned out perfectly! Just like the previous time I made it using regular flour. Scrumptious! No one wanted to share, zero leftovers! Favorite recipe of ours!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"hildigunnur\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent recipe like everything I've tried from Chef John. Crispy on the outside and soft and juicy on the inside. I only used skinless thighs and fried 3 at a time in a deep fryer so I only needed 10 minutes for the batch. Will make again and again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Julianna S\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I've never made such delicious fried chicken! So easy! Try this recipe as soon as you can!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"walshpj\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a very good and easy to follow recipe. I used boneless chicken breasts so I adjusted the cooking time . My family loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Glen C\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great fried chicken. This was the first time I've tried to fry chicken and it came out beautifully. I did increase the seasonings x2 only because I like spicy food (tablespoon of cayenne pepper), and it turned out terrific. Thanks chef John!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Edward Schultz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Wish I read the reviews before hand. Chicken came out fine but this recipe is far too bland. You almost need to triple or quadruple the amounts of season. Also at 350 I feel the cook time is was off. 25 minutes to fry chicken is a bit much. At that temp it should take 14-15 minutes total to avoid burning. I cooked this a little slower and checked internal temps just to be safe. But the breading really left something to be desired.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Nick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I would buy pre cut chicken next time. Life\\u2019s too short. It\\u2019s not hard to make and as long as you don\\u2019t cause a house fire it\\u2019s fun to make. I recommend it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"CookingJewel\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"DELICIOUS! Moist, flavorful chicken with a tasty, crispy coating. WOW! We enjoyed this recipe so much, it's a keeper! Thank you very much for sharing, Chef John. We made the recipe exactly as written and it came out perfect. The chef's note on oil temperature was especially helpful the first time we made it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"steve\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Love this recipe! The only modifications I made: 1) used just chicken breasts, 2) used only 12oz of peanut oil to fry. Used four \\u201cCostco sized\\u201d chicken breasts, pounded them to flatten to about 1 inch thick before marinading. Fried each breast 2-3 minutes each side then put (carefully) on a baking sheet and baked 20 minutes at 400F.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Dan Williams\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Awesome. I had a chicken dry brining so I omitted the buttermilk. Super crispy, with none if the dark patches I normally get. Chicken is sweet and crunchy, even cold the next day! Follow his tip on 2.5 quarts of oil. Totally worth it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chrissy Wen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Substituted kefir for the buttermilk and it turned out great!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Michael Buckley\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Excellent! Chicken was very moist and great flavors. Easy dish to make\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"skp321\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made two changes. I used organic plain yogurt to marinade the chicken, refrigerated 20 hours and I used finely crushed Corn Flakes instead of flour. Otherwise, I followed the recipe. I\\u2019m not sure if those were the culprits but there wasn\\u2019t much flavor. The chicken tasted plenty salty but flavors weren\\u2019t absorbed. I\\u2019ll consider trying this again using flour as Chef John has written but I\\u2019m not sure that will help the spice flavors. The spices are those with substantial flavor so I expected to find those flavors within the meat but that wasn\\u2019t the case.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ian Stu\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A way to a woman's heart is through her stomach. This is the second time I have made this and it was perfect. The first time I waited for the canola oil to boil which it never did until I put the chicken in. Last time it was too hot and burned the chicken. For twenty min. it did not turn brown until the last five. My wife loved it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Eric W.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was very good. Would totally make this again. For me, this turned out to be a deep fry instead of a pan fry.\\nThe leftovers were also really good, but of course, not really crispy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chris\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made a double batch for 5 people, nothing left over. Everyone loved the chicken!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Melinda Recchia\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was delicious. The only thing I did differently was and use chicken thighs instead of a whole chicken, add I added 1\\\" of oil to my cast iron dutch oven instead of 10 cups. I did over cook the chicken a bit (I did 10 mins each side instead of 8-9 because I do not have a thermometer and erred on the side of caution. Don't do that. 20 minutes ). This recipe is a keeper (pinned and saved).\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Southflgal\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only difference is that I used chicken tenders. Went exactly as the recipe said; it was very good and not dry at all. My husband liked the spice but would prefer a bit more kick next time. \\n\\nI hope next time I make this, I will have an air fryer to lessen the caloric intake.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jensings2\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Good recipe. I didn't exactly follow the directions for frying, because I didn't have that much oil, but I think next time, I will turn the temperature down 25 degrees. I will also add more of the spices to the flour mixture to get more flavor. Lovely, but very mild flavor. Will definitely make again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cherie Lytle Moyer\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Disappointing. Not much flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"3ric\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Yummy! Doubled the seasoning in the flour as others suggested. Used a gallon of oil and a big roasting pot (chicken was massive, around 8 lbs). Cooked the breasts about 25 min, others 15-20 min. Will definitely save this for another time this summer.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"James Donaldson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This actually tasted A LOT like KFC. Was actually surprised how much, only better.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"whats4dinner?\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Moist and tender, so flavorable and lick-your-fingers good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bruce Bain\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"tasted great\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Davv\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"it was so juicy and tender\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Liz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy and very crispy. Just be sure your oil is hot enough\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Product Junkie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I just made this last night and everything went great except the chicken lacked punch. There weren't enough spices or herbs. Next time I'll double or even triple the amount . The buttermilk really makes a difference in keeping the chicken moist. \\n\\nFried it in my cast iron skillet instead of a Dutch oven since I was only frying 4 thighs. I also had a candy/deep fry thermometer to make sure I had the right temp of oil at 350 degrees F. Took me about 30 minutes to cook. \\n\\nWill definitely try it again, but a lot more spices &amp; herbs! Bon App\\u00e9tit!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JustMeCookin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I\\u2019ve made this three times now\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mari\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was recommended by a friend although I did modify a little. I didn\\u2019t have buttermilk so I made my own and I used skinless boneless chicken breast in strips and I added more seasoning then recommended and it came out great. My husband even likes it and he is really picky about his chicken. I made ranch dressing and paired it with a salad. The next time I make I will definitely make sure I have buttermilk to see if it makes a difference in texture and flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"chris elliott\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have used this recipe twice and the chicken came out amazing both times. The crust looks and tastes incredible and by marinating in the buttermilk and spices overnight the seasoning was perfect.\\n\\nIf done right this recipe will be a crowd pleaser.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tara L Smith\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used this recipe to teach my 17 yo son. It was super easy to follow, and turned out absolutely delicious!!! He was so excited to know he could prepare this amazing dish that he's chomping at the bit to make more like it!\\nThe flavor was amazing, and the skin turned out nice and crisp. It was just like my Great Grandma's chicken, and every bite took me back to her kitchen.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rebecca\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I don't fry chicken very often. But decided to do so for dinner tonight and tried this recipe. My husband LOVED it! He even asked me to make certain that I didn't lose this recipe. Will definitely make again! Thank you Chef John--as usual your recipes are wonderful.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Linda Champlin Sharp\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"When I measured all the spices I made them \\\"heaping\\\". Excellent results, having only made fried chicken once before I found it a bit hard to maintain the oil temp but all turned out ok. When it got close to the time it should be done I pulled out a piece and used my instant read thermometer. Chef John, I know you were born in Clifton Springs. I was born in Geneva and spent many summers at Raquette Lake in the ADK. Have made several of your recipes, my son Rob suggested I check your recipes out, glad I did.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kat Blue\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I left out the white pepper. The rest of the recipe I did as recipe called for.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Candice Slowik Perlin\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I rarely leave reviews but I want to say a BIG THANK YOU to Chef John as this is now one of many recipes of his that our family has made and absolutely loved. And this one too will be added to our \\u2018go to\\u2019 recipe list. I almost always make modifications to new recipes that I try out, but not with Chef John! He just nails every recipe down to a tee. This fried chicken was amazingly delicious, crunchy and perfectly seasoned. Thanks again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jennifer_1206\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"this was my first time making fried chicken. with that being said it took me a while to figure out how to best to coat the chicken tenders to get a nice crust. my family enjoyed the recipe but i felt it was a bit bland. i will try this again and double up the spices.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"liz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a deep fryer and set it between 325 to 350 degrees. At 350 chicken was too brown. I used all thighs without the bone. Added a bit more cayenne ... we like it spicy!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MamaShaw\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"For the most tender I use only thighs with skin on and I cut them in half so that they cook well internally. I also dip 4 pieces in in flour and fry small batches at a time and add oil as I need it. My daughter asked that I make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lisa Seidel\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This chicken recipe is awesome! It was crispy on the outside. Inside, so tender &amp; moist. Even though I didn't have any thyme, the seasoning was perfect. This will definitely be my one and only recipe for fried chicken. Great job!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"billy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used a gallon of peanut oil for frying. The oil maintained at 275 F, but the chicken still came out pretty good!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"foxx83086\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a great fried chicken recipe!! The only changes I made were minor. I didn\\u2019t have peanut oil - used vegetable oil. I didn\\u2019t have enough oil for Dutch oven or deep fryer so I fried in pan - same overall cooking time as recipe. I also only marinated for 3 or 4 hours - didn\\u2019t have enough time to go full 6 hours or overnight - but the chicken was still very moist with wonderful flavor. I will definitely make this again! Thanks for sharing Chef John - I never go wrong with any of your recipes!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brenda Haddock\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this chicken! Left out the cayenne pepper (not our kind of thing) but still fabulous.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Linda 13\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I loved this and it was pretty easy to make. Came out perfect. Was like my Mom used to make. I did finish off in the oven to cook through, used bone in thighs. Was great as leftovers too. Can't wait to make it again. No photo, we ate it all\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bjlong1274\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have now made this several time using gluten free flour. It makes the best fried chicken.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brent Berkeypile\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I fried mine in a cast iron skillet and it turned out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rhonda Alvarez\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was delicious!! I even got my husband liking chicken again. Neither of us are big rosemary fans, but I think this is going to change my mind. We will be making this on a regular now.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Beverly Anne Carman\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Best Fried Chicken Ever !!! \\n\\nFrying Tips : Don't over crowd the pan. Always work in batches and let the oil come back to the proper temp before adding more chicken. After coating your chicken in the flower mixture, let it rest for a few minutes before you fry it. This will help keep your crust on nice and tight to the chicken.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Elizabeth\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"delish\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Layne\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I love Chef John's recipes! They work every time! I don't have a deep fat fryer, so I followed his large frying pan option. And, used all thighs (my favorite piece). Otherwise I made no changes to his recipe and it received rave remarks from everyone who tasted it. I also happen to have a soft spot for cold left over fried chicken, and this did NOT disappoint! I will absolutely make this again, and have added it to my top 10 favorite recipes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mark Knowles\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"John...amazing! (you made me look like I knew what I was doing) Thanks!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Barbara Hill\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"my go to recipe for fried chicen works great for just wings also\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"red52magoo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was so amazing the first time I made it! I will be definitely be making this again! The chicken was so moist from sitting in the buttermilk and the breading was perfect!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Roslyn Grace\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The flavor is EXCELLENT! Chef John, you're awesome!\\n\\nI made this for dinner tonight and we loved it. The only change I have to make, and this has NOTHING to do with the recipe itself. I used my cast iron skillet and it browned a little too much. So, the next time I make this I'll be cutting back on the actual time it's in the oil. I did put it in the oven at 350 while I cooked everything else. So yes, my chicken was done to the correct temperature. THAT IS THE ONLY CHANGE I'M MAKING! \\n\\nI have a Culinary Degree and I've got to admit, this chicken is better than mine. So this is now the only way I'll be making fried chicken!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"buzz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Chicken was moist with a nice crunchy coating. I deepfried the chicken for 10 mins. then baked it to finish.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sweethulachick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I did a double dredge (dredged the chicken, dunked it back in the buttermilk, then dredged again) and let the chicken sit for a few minutes before frying. I deep fried for 12 minutes. SO crispy and juicy, my family said it was some of the best fried chicken they've ever had. I will so be doing this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Flo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious, moist,, my family begs for this chicken\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Gotrecipe?\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Years ago (way before I knew there was a Chef John!) I came up with this exact method!! I am still remembered for my fried chicken even though I've gone on to a much healthier diet. Every once in awhile my husband and grown children request this...for old time sake! I never had any measurements (just threw it together) so it's nice to have this in written form so I can pass it on to my family. Occasionally I would soak the chicken in salted water instead and when ready to fry I would then dip it in the buttermilk, etc. This is really a wonderful way to fry chicken and always brings compliments!!!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Poosh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My hubby and I both agreed this was just as good as any crispy chicken we had had before from ANYWHERE. So juicy and the crispy outside was absolutely delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Marianne Kistler DeGreen\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely the best fried chicken recipe! I followed everything exactly, with the exception of white pepper ( I don't have any). My husband LOVED it. Will definitely always use this recipe\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kristin Barner\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this tonight because the grocery store had chicken legs on sale. I decided to make half of them this recipe and half of them Chef Johns Nashville Hot chicken (check over there for that review). Flavor wise, they turned out great! Super crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. However, I used the same temperature (I used a deep fryer so it maintains the correct temperature) and they came out super brown looking. They didn't taste burnt but they didn't look great. But they tasted great! So, if you're going for presentation and trying to impress someone, I would maybe go for a lower temperature for a longer time. My husband and I were the only ones to eat them, so they were good enough for us. I love Chef John and would love to cook with him someday, it's on my bucket list!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"David Holdwick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used crushed red pepper instead of cayenne in buttermilk solution(out and improved) and let sit for 30 hours prior to dredging in flour. By far my favorite fried chicken\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"username\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great flavor- I do the frying in a Lodge cast iron wok outside on a propane camp burner.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lori Rowe\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used boneless chicken thighs and boneless breasts cut in 3. I also switched out the flour for PC All purpose gluten free flour and fried in a frying pan on the stove top. Brought about 1 inch of oil to a boil and added chicken pieces turning them after about 10 minutes. Be very careful using this method, do not leave the pan of frying chicken unattended as oil can spatter out of the pan and cause fire if not monitored. Very tasty will make again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pa Murphy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The flavor of his spices were good, next time I am going to add marjoram to it. The chicken stayed moist. I will make this over and over again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tally\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tasted great. I used 8 chicken thighs, double breaded them, and had just enough flour. I used Cajun seasoning instead of the sage, extra cayenne and marinated for 24 hours. For the thighs, 350 was definitely too hot, so I set it to about 315 for 15 minutes, and if the middle still had trouble cooking, I cut each thigh open and fried them for an extra minute .\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mama Dukes\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe for chicken. Took some of the advice from reviews. Browned in peanut oil for 6-8 min then on rack in oven at 350 for 30 min. Nice and moist and crispy outside. Used 24 drumsticks , had enough to make another dozen pieces.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jane Guzauskas Ruby\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Way too peppery--but that's just me. Buttermilk marinade worked and chicken was moist and tasty. I fried in skillet instead of Dutch oven. Nice crunchy breadlng. Will try again with less pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Deb\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added cornstarch into mix with floured herb mix and an egg to make a batter. I used an Italian herb mix and chervil. Lots of garlic salt and kosher salt. I kept my buttermilk marinate then dipped in flour and again in buttermilk then flour for 2 dips and coatings before frying it. Coating was delicious and chicken inside soft moist delicious. I used thighs so frying was not enough to cook them through. After frying I baked them for 20 minutes more with some oil in pan. Did not need any sauce. Plain was delicious. Ate them with a veg mix of carrots peas and corn buttered with salt and pepper. Next day I made potato salad for another meal.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Samboo\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe came out great!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jay\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Followed the recipe to the letter and they came out looking great but was not impressed with the flavor after adding all the ingredients.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"lkbunch\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"very nice but I changed it up a bit, added cornstarch h for part of the total flour, for extra crispy and it worked well.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"margaret merrill\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made it as directed and it was very good. I will make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Susan S.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very crispy and very tasty! I \\\"double fried\\\" it. I'll definitely make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"TBS55\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was good. Not enough spice for me. I'll probably try it again and add more paprika and cayenne.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jay\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My hubby took a bite and said, \\\"mmmm this might be better than KFC!!!\\\" And he's a KFC lover! I'd definitely make this again and my kids loved this! I gave it 4 stars because as per a reviewers suggestion, I doubled the spices to go in the seasoned flour (except the salt) and it really needs that. It would be quite bland without it. Also I didn't have any buttermilk so made it with whole milk and vinegar and I just shallow fried it in a large pan which took about 16 minutes (used drumsticks). Edit: I fried some the next day but this time left the chicken dredged in flour for over an hour. The result was the crispy outside was falling off the chicken when it left to cool after frying. I won't be doing that again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BirasCreek\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The recipe was perfect, although I did add some Frank\\u2019s Red Hot to the buttermilk for a little heat. The chicken was amazing!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bruce Edwards\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Sweet Baby Jesus these were amazing! Anyone who enjoyed this should consider using Chef John's recipe for chicken fried steak, since the batter is different and IMO, only SLIGHTLY better than this one - mostly due to the fact that the baking soda used in the other one makes the breading a little more fluffy. Still, the flavor on these was amazing, and I didn't have the time to marinade in the buttermilk (only about 40 minutes). I really winged it since I had a lot more chicken than is listed in recipe. Also I had a couple of chicken breasts that I cut to be more or less the same size as the tenderloins. My suggestions/modifications: I could have used half the flour called for. I also cut back a little on the cayenne since my picky kids donna lika the spicy! :D\\n\\nAlso, I would pull the chicken out earlier than I did and that is suggested in recipe. Some of my pieces were extremely juicy, but most were just a BIT dry. Of course I used a blend of peanut and canola since I didn't have enough peanut, and put about 2-3 inches deep oil in a large, deep skillet (I don't own a dutch oven). Worked great and not very messy at all as I was expecting (grease was not everywhere). \\n\\nAs always from CJ, an amazing recipe. Any recipes on here from him that aren't delicious? Crazy.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Vinnie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Definitely make it again...might just put a bit more spice in it but that\\u2019s just me\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"nathanhotdog\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Quick, delicious and very easy. I\\u2019ve never made any bread or worked with yeast before.\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/220128/chef-johns-buttermilk-fried-chicken/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/201/meat-and-poultry/chicken/\", \"name\": \"Chicken\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/650/meat-and-poultry/chicken/fried-chicken/\", \"name\": \"Fried Chicken Recipes\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/220128/chef-johns-buttermilk-fried-chicken/\", \"name\": \"Chef John&#39;s Buttermilk Fried Chicken\"}}]}}, \"about\": []}"}
{"recipe_name": "Zucchini Ravioli", "yields": "4 serving(s)", "time": {"prep": "PT15M", "cook": "PT0S", "total": "PT1H5M"}, "ingredients": ["Extra-virgin olive oil, for baking dish", "4 medium zucchini", "2 c. ricotta", "1/2 c. freshly grated Parmesan, plus more for garnish", "1 large egg, lightly beaten", "1/4 c. thinly sliced basil, divided", "1 clove garlic, minced", "Kosher salt", "Freshly ground black pepper", "2 c. marinara", "1/2 c. shredded mozzarella"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Preheat oven to 375° and grease a large baking dish with olive oil."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Make the noodles: Slice two sides of each zucchini lengthwise to create two flat sides. Using a vegetable peeler, slice each zucchini into thin flat strips, peeling until you reach the center. These are your “noodles.”"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Make the filling: In a medium bowl, combine ricotta, Parmesan, egg, 2 tablespoons basil, garlic, and season with salt and pepper."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Assemble the ravioli: Lay two strips of zucchini noodles so that they overlap lengthwise. Lay two more noodles on top, perpendicular to the first strips. You should end up with a “T” shape. Spoon about 1 tablespoon of filling in the center of the zucchini. Bring the ends of the strips together to fold over the center, working one side at a time. Turn ravioli over and place in the baking dish seam-side down. Repeat with remaining zucchini and filling. Pour marinara around zucchini and top ravioli with mozzarella. "}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Bake until zucchini noodles are “al dente” and the cheese is melty and golden on top, 25 to 30 minutes."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Top with remaining basil and Parmesan before serving."}], "body": "{\"@type\": \"Recipe\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.669xw:1.00xh;0.0619xw,0.00244xh&resize=100:*\", \"datePublished\": \"2016-07-26T17:17:00Z EST\", \"headline\": \"Zucchini Ravioli\", \"articleBody\": null, \"wordCount\": null, \"image\": [{\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 1200, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.669xw:1.00xh;0.0619xw,0.00244xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.669xw:1.00xh;0.0619xw,0.00244xh&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 900, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.669xw:1.00xh;0.0619xw,0.00244xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.8891228070175439xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}, {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"height\": 675, \"thumbnail\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=0.669xw:1.00xh;0.0619xw,0.00244xh&resize=100:*\", \"url\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=1xw:0.8435280189423836xh;center,top&resize=1200:*\", \"width\": 1200}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a48392/zucchini-ravioli-recipe/\", \"@type\": \"WebPage\"}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Delish\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://twitter.com/delishdotcom\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@delish\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/delish\", \"https://www.facebook.com/delish\", \"http://instagram.com/delish\", \"http://www.pinterest.com/Delish/\"], \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/_assets/design-tokens/delish/static/images/logos/logo-jsonld.1396ea2.png\", \"width\": 312, \"height\": 60}, \"parentOrganization\": {\"@type\": \"NewsMediaOrganization\", \"name\": \"Hearst Corporation\"}}, \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a48392/zucchini-ravioli-recipe/\", \"isBasedOn\": \"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a48392/zucchini-ravioli-recipe/\", \"dateModified\": \"2019-05-16T17:02:00Z EST\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"hasPart\": [{\"@type\": \"WebPageElement\", \"isAccessibleForFree\": \"False\", \"cssSelector\": \".content-container\"}], \"video\": {\"@type\": \"VideoObject\", \"contentUrl\": \"https://streaming.hearstdigitalstudios.com/9270eee4-12d0-4d6b-851f-e85864acddaf/video_rover_16x9_1080p_hd_1547834252_68007.mp4\", \"description\": \"Zucchini Ravioli is our newest zoodle obsession. It's the best low-carb way to get your ravioli fix. \\u200bSay \\\"Arrivederci!\\\" to carbs! \\u200b\", \"duration\": \"PT58S\", \"embedUrl\": \"https://glimmer.hearstapps.com/amp.html?embedId=16598eb2-89aa-4da2-b931-90636a3def13\", \"name\": \"Zucchini Ravioli Is The Most Genius Low-Carb Hack\", \"thumbnailUrl\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/190419-zucchini-ravioli-horizontal-230-1558016038.jpg?crop=1xw:0.8435280189423836xh;center,top\", \"uploadDate\": \"2018-03-13T21:24:30.992421Z\"}, \"author\": {\"name\": \"Lauren Miyashiro\", \"url\": \"https://www.delish.com/author/15834/lauren-miyashiro/\", \"@type\": \"Person\", \"description\": \"<p>Lauren Miyashiro is the former Food Director of Delish. She graduated culinary school in 2016 and mastered the art of the <a href=\\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a52078/crunchwrap-supreme-recipe/\\\">Crunchwrap</a> in 2017.</p>\", \"jobTitle\": \"Freelance Contributor\", \"image\": \"https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/f7a9bc6d-c4b2-4f97-bf20-4507bed87c57_1523821695.file\", \"sameAs\": [\"www.instagram.com/laurenmiya\"]}, \"name\": \"Zucchini Ravioli\", \"prepTime\": \"PT15M\", \"cookTime\": \"PT0S\", \"totalTime\": \"PT1H5M\", \"recipeIngredient\": [\"Extra-virgin olive oil, for baking dish\", \"4 medium zucchini\", \"2 c. ricotta\", \"1/2 c. freshly grated Parmesan, plus more for garnish\", \"1 large egg, lightly beaten\", \"1/4 c. thinly sliced basil, divided\", \"1 clove garlic, minced\", \"Kosher salt\", \"Freshly ground black pepper\", \"2 c. marinara\", \"1/2 c. shredded mozzarella\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Preheat oven to 375\\u00b0 and grease a large baking dish with olive oil.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Make the noodles: Slice two sides of each zucchini lengthwise to create two flat sides. Using a vegetable peeler, slice each zucchini into thin flat strips, peeling until you reach the center. These are your \\u201cnoodles.\\u201d\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Make the filling: In a medium bowl, combine ricotta, Parmesan, egg, 2 tablespoons basil, garlic, and season with salt and pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Assemble the ravioli: Lay two strips of zucchini noodles so that they overlap lengthwise. Lay two more noodles on top, perpendicular to the first strips. You should end up with a \\u201cT\\u201d shape. Spoon about 1 tablespoon of filling in the center of the zucchini. Bring the ends of the strips together to fold over the center, working one side at a time. Turn ravioli over and place in the baking dish seam-side down. Repeat with remaining zucchini and filling. Pour marinara around zucchini and top ravioli with mozzarella. \"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bake until zucchini noodles are \\u201cal dente\\u201d and the cheese is melty and golden on top, 25 to 30 minutes.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Top with remaining basil and Parmesan before serving.\"}], \"recipeYield\": \"4 serving(s)\", \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\", \"Italian\"], \"recipeCategory\": [\"gluten-free\", \"low-carb\", \"low sugar\", \"nut-free\", \"vegetarian\", \"date night\", \"weeknight meals\", \"dinner\", \"main dish\"], \"description\": \"Looking for an easy zucchini noodle recipe? This Zucchini Ravioli Recipe from Delish.com is the best.\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": 4.8, \"reviewCount\": 15, \"worstRating\": 1, \"bestRating\": 5}, \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"220 calories\"}, \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\"}"}
{"recipe_name": "Portobello Mushroom Stroganoff", "yields": ["4"], "time": {"prep": "PT10M", "cook": "PT20M", "total": "PT30M"}, "ingredients": ["3 tablespoons butter", "1 large onion, chopped", "0.75 pound portobello mushrooms, sliced", "1.5 cups vegetable broth", "1.5 cups sour cream", "3 tablespoons all-purpose flour", "0.25 cup chopped fresh parsley", "8 ounces dried egg noodles"], "instructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add egg noodles, and cook until al dente, about 7 minutes. Remove from heat, drain, and set aside."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "At the same time, melt butter in a large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add onion, and cook, stirring until softened. Turn the heat up to medium-high, and add sliced mushrooms. Cook until the mushrooms are limp and browned. Remove to a bowl, and set aside."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "In the same skillet, stir in vegetable broth, being sure to stir in any browned bits off the bottom of the pan. Bring to a boil, and cook until the mixture has reduced by 1/3. Reduce heat to low, and return the mushrooms and onion to the skillet."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Remove the pan from the heat, stir together the sour cream and flour; then blend into the mushrooms. Return the skillet to the burner, and continue cooking over low heat, just until the sauce thickens. Stir in the parsley, and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve over cooked egg noodles."}], "body": "{\"@context\": \"http://schema.org\", \"@type\": [\"Recipe\"], \"headline\": \"Portobello Mushroom Stroganoff\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-09T22:50:39.000-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2023-08-22T12:11:05.019-04:00\", \"author\": [{\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chordata\"}], \"description\": \"This vegetarian mushroom stroganoff made with saut\\u00e9ed portobello mushrooms and sour cream is so creamy and delicious you won&#39;t miss the meat.\", \"image\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ONY0aqzZ2D9quMtds9FZFK75RFY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/48196-f866474a713745a89ea0cdffb1b9146a.jpg\", \"height\": 960, \"width\": 960}, \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com\", \"logo\": {\"@type\": \"ImageObject\", \"url\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Z9lwz1y0B5aX-cemPiTgpn5YB0k=/112x112/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/allrecipes_logo_schema-867c69d2999b439a9eba923a445ccfe3.png\", \"width\": 112, \"height\": 112}, \"brand\": \"Allrecipes\", \"publishingPrinciples\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/about-us-6648102#toc-editorial-guidelines\", \"sameAs\": [\"https://www.facebook.com/allrecipes\", \"https://www.instagram.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.pinterest.com/allrecipes/\", \"https://www.tiktok.com/@allrecipes\", \"https://www.youtube.com/user/allrecipes/videos\", \"https://twitter.com/Allrecipes\", \"https://flipboard.com/@Allrecipes\", \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allrecipes.com\", \"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/allrecipes-dinner-spinner/id299515267\", \"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.allrecipes.spinner.free&hl=en_US&gl=US\", \"https://www.youtube.com/c/foodwishes\", \"https://www.linkedin.com/company/19312/admin/\"]}, \"name\": \"Portobello Mushroom Stroganoff\", \"aggregateRating\": {\"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.3\", \"ratingCount\": \"574\"}, \"cookTime\": \"PT20M\", \"nutrition\": {\"@type\": \"NutritionInformation\", \"calories\": \"525 kcal\", \"carbohydrateContent\": \"53 g\", \"cholesterolContent\": \"101 mg\", \"fiberContent\": \"4 g\", \"proteinContent\": \"13 g\", \"saturatedFatContent\": \"17 g\", \"sodiumContent\": \"295 mg\", \"sugarContent\": \"5 g\", \"fatContent\": \"30 g\", \"unsaturatedFatContent\": \"0 g\"}, \"prepTime\": \"PT10M\", \"recipeCategory\": [\"Dinner\"], \"recipeCuisine\": [\"American\"], \"recipeIngredient\": [\"3 tablespoons butter\", \"1 large onion, chopped\", \"0.75 pound portobello mushrooms, sliced\", \"1.5 cups vegetable broth\", \"1.5 cups sour cream\", \"3 tablespoons all-purpose flour\", \"0.25 cup chopped fresh parsley\", \"8 ounces dried egg noodles\"], \"recipeInstructions\": [{\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add egg noodles, and cook until al dente, about 7 minutes. Remove from heat, drain, and set aside.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"At the same time, melt butter in a large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add onion, and cook, stirring until softened. Turn the heat up to medium-high, and add sliced mushrooms. Cook until the mushrooms are limp and browned. Remove to a bowl, and set aside.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"In the same skillet, stir in vegetable broth, being sure to stir in any browned bits off the bottom of the pan. Bring to a boil, and cook until the mixture has reduced by 1/3. Reduce heat to low, and return the mushrooms and onion to the skillet.\"}, {\"@type\": \"HowToStep\", \"text\": \"Remove the pan from the heat, stir together the sour cream and flour; then blend into the mushrooms. Return the skillet to the burner, and continue cooking over low heat, just until the sauce thickens. Stir in the parsley, and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve over cooked egg noodles.\"}], \"recipeYield\": [\"4\"], \"totalTime\": \"PT30M\", \"review\": [{\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Krisie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great flavor and texture, don\\u2019t even miss the meat \\ud83e\\udd69 delicious\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe was OK, but not my favorite. My wife liked it, though! My suggestion would be to use more mushrooms (I will admit to some fault here, since I used pre-sliced ones) to start. I'd also cut back on the sour cream a little and make the sauce a little thinner. When I was done it was tasty, but really just reminded me of noodles soaked in sour cream (not that that's a bad thing...).\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"SDL\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Absolutely loved this recipe. Trying to find ways to make inexpensive meals and this one is a keeper for sure!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Cec\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great recipe. I did use fresh dill instead of parsley which was delicious\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Katie B\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very rich and hearty. I scaled down the recipe for one serving and I couldn't eat it all! No room for salad or sides either. Changes: I used unsalted butter and low-sodium beef broth to keep within my sodium limit. I only used about 1/2C of the sour cream and as it was this is over-the-top creamy. Really good for an occasional indulgence. :-)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My family loves this recipe, we have it a few times a month! The only thing I change, is adding a few tbsp of soy sauce to the vegetable broth.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jane\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Instead of flour add one pkg mushroom gravy mix, then add sour cream\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"IggySparkleBooty\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Unfortunately it just wasn't for me. It was nice and thick and had plenty of flavor, it just wasn't flavor that I personally liked.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jacob Golick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good recipe. I doubled the sauce as we love the sauce.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Glenn Taverna\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is awesome\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"pear\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A favorite in our house. Absolutely delicious. I've made it over a dozen times now. We usually do it over pappardelle pasta (another kind of egg noodle) rather than the normal spiral egg noodles.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"jwright1379\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My kids love this. Being that they are vegetarian and I am lactose intolerant, I use plant based butter and sour cream. still very delicious!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"handiwife\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I followed pinkypink's recommendations, added some seasoned salt and pepper, and it was really good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mamasan\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"We loved it! I added 1 tsp of dried thyme and generous sprinklings of garlic powder and roasted garlic powder. I would have preferred fresh garlic but mine was too old. This is a very filling meal. The umami flavor of mushrooms made it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Diana Macku\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"It was okay. It's missing something but I can't put my finger on it. Salt helped. So did more pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sunday Morning\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Like others have written, this falls flat without modifications.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"sport1girl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was delicious! Those who cut back on the sour cream \\nand are adding tomato sauce, etc, you know it's stroganoff, right? Of course, you leave all the sour cream in. Also, why would you add garlic? I used lots of pepper, salt of course, and my Eastern Europe spices. Keep the measurements because they are perfect. \\n\\nI remember the first time I had beef stroganoff as a kid, it was wonderful. I'm vegetarian now, so I loved having the same amazing dish without meat. Thank you!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Alissa\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really enjoyed this recipe! I added aome freshly grated Parmesean cheese and a little milk to the sauce while it thickened and it was terrific!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jenna Tuttle\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Was really good! Definitely will be having this again\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ora Walsh\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tastes good - used less sour cream and still found very thick. Make sure to mix flour and sour cream very well :-)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"CLJAKE\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is very good. I wasn't sure how I would like the Portbello Mushrooms but they were so good. Easy, fast and great tasting. It's going to be a go-to when we need a creamy hot meal.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Reannon??\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Hey ! I\\u2019m 15 and I made this and it\\u2019s AWESOME! It\\u2019s so easy and my mom and brothers love it!! I usually double the recipe and it\\u2019s awesome !\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chris Sr\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I always follow the recipe the first time I make something. We found this to be a little on the bland side. Next time will try it with some garlic or pepper to help it along.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"TheLockes\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Well liked by everyone who ate it. My vegetarian daughter even enjoyed it! :-)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Debbie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I followed the recipe (almost) and my husband who is a meat eater loved it. We both did. The only difference was I used 3 tsp of arrowroot instead of all purpose flour which made it gluten free.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Jill\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Even with only one half cup of sour cream, it was too much sour cream. It was good before any sour cream was added.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Chef_Acceber\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good! Followed the second reviewers recommendations adding white wine, soy sauce, worchester sauce, and only 1/2 cup sour cream. I didn\\u2019t remove the mushrooms and simmered in broth until desired thickness was reached . It only made about 3 servings of this is the only item being served.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pam Heller Griffith\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"As others have stated, I\\u2019m rating the dish created with the changes I have made. It was delicious!! I sauteed the onions for 15 to 20 minutes until caramelized and then added the mushrooms(1/2 Pound portobello, 1/2 pound Shiitake. I also added 1/2 cup red wine to the mushrooms. After the mushrooms became limp, I removed them and put in a bowl. I added the vegetable broth to my pot and added 2 TBS of Worcester sauce and 1/4 c soy sauce. I then mixed 2 TBS flour with 1/2 c sour cream. I wished this until well blended and started to thicken, I then added the mushrooms back and added salt and pepper to taste. I then served mine on top of steamed spaghetti squash. I will be making this again!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BakingAuntieDeeDee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"If my husband and son eat it, that's a win.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Toni Carver\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"My rating for this recipe is based off of preparing the dish as the recipe reads. I figure if I have to make changes to it than I am preparing a different recipe so here goes. Bland! Very little flavor. I would recommend reading the reviews before you prepare this dish and making some of those changes. It was very easy to prepare.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pip\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this recipe as written and it didn\\u2019t turn out very well. Way too much sour cream and the onion taste was overwhelming. Otherwise it was very bland. I will not make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bardkun\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This is one of our go-to recipes! Easy, tasty, keeps in the fridge and freezes well. I like to add some fake seasoned meat (Boca or Tofurky) and play with the spices, but all in all it's fantastic as a base for experimentation or on its own. Yum!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Texas-Grrl\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I took the advice of others and included some chopped garlic and Worcestershire sauce. Also, I added about 2 tsp of Greek seasoning. \\n\\nAnd I didn't start the egg noodles until the sauce was simmering.\\n\\nWith these changes, this recipe was quite good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bryan Thompson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Terrible. Just don't do it unless you love sour cream.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sukismom\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"As written this is bland. With some changes however, this is wonderful. I did add garlic and sauteed in brown butter. Used beef broth (no veggie broth on hand) and reduced with mushrooms and onions still in the pan. I added cornstarch to the sour cream and a splash of soy sauce and Worcestershire then warmed it all. This was delicious. It's definitely going into my meatless meal file.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brenda Sue Smith\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Delicious! Just took longer than I anticipated. Will make again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"a0ella\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"as is, this is good, but bland. i took the advice of other reviews and added a generous splash of red wine, some minced garlic, and far less sour cream (about 1/2 cup), and it was delicious. i\\u2019m vegetarian, but i cooked some beef tips separately for my meat eating guests, and they LOVED it. absolutely scarfed it down. it was delicious with egg noodles and quite rich. thank you.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"GreenFingers\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Looked great, but tasted bland. Missing something.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"cowgirll\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"These two carnivores didn't even miss the meat in this recipe. It hits all of my stroganoff craving requirements, and is perfect for Meatless Mondays. I'm keeping this recipe close at hand for sure.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"ImpoverishedBlonde\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used baby Bella and sauteed sirloin steak strips in a separate pan for my meat eating boyfriend. I made the recipe as is for me and added about 4-5 ladels of the sauce to his strips. We both thought the meal was excellent. We will be making this again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"EriNnRuss\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good, this was my family's vegetarian night. Would definately make again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Halie Renee Ransom\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"As many others have said, this is pretty bland as written. I added garlic and lots of garlic salt and it made it a 4. And if you aren't vegetarian I would use beef broth, but it still is good without it.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brian Warwick\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Will definitely make this again. The family loved it. Followed some of the suggestions listed in the reviews. Added some garlic, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce for flavor. Also I doubled the recipe and used 1\\\\2 cup each of red and white wine instead of just broth. Absolute winner in my book.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Safiya Shirazi\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was okay. It was pretty easy to make, and I think the fact that I wasn't wowed by this recipe was more the result of circumstance than anything else. It took a while between finishing the meal and getting it onto the table, and it is not at its best at room temperature. \\n\\nI did make it with shallot butter instead of regular, which I think added some flavor.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Darknlovely\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very good!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BRG\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Pretty good. I did not remove the mushrooms from the pan. Also didn't mix the flour and sour cream together before adding to the mushrooms - that would have been way too many dishes. Added some Worchestershire and truffle salt at the end.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Ellie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved this recipe. A few changes. I added tofu and garlic when you add the mushrooms. Add salt, pepper and paprika once everything is fried. While the vegetable broth reducing, add 1 tsp soy sauce, 1 tsp apple cider vinegar and 1 table spoon tomato paste. Only use 3/4 cup of sour cream. Really delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stephanie Moss\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made it as is and it was tasty.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"shouthurray\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this as written. I wish I had read the other reviews first.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Tiffany Wisser\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Quite tasty! Good meatless yet hearty dish. I took the suggestions of some other reviews and cooked the onions longer and lower until caramelized, added 2 cloves of garlic, and subbed 1/2 cup of red wine for 1/2 cup of the broth. I used the full 1 1/2 cups of sour cream and it was perfect for a stroganoff...I'm not sure why so many reviewers are cutting it back to 1/2 a cup, I don't think I would even taste it at that ratio. I will definitely make this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Karen Riechers\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added 1 garlic clove, 1 tsp. Soy sauce, 1/2 tsp. Worchestire sauce, 1/4 cup red wine. Great flavor!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"justbake\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Made it vegan by using vegan sour cream. Used mushroom broth instead of vegetable broth to intensify the mushroom flavor and also added one Not Beef bouillon cube to add the beef flavor. Really good recipe!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Donna\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Great vegetarian take on an old favorite.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"1\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Katy Lynn Patterson\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Incredibly bland and thin. I added half my spice rack and it finally had taste.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Victoria\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Two stars as-is. With recommended changes (sort by most helpful) this could be five stars.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"2\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lin Zagorski\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Unfortunately, I did not read the critical reviews before cooking. If you create this recipe as-is, I hope you really love the flavor of sour cream.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Knitduck\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Tried it as is this first time; am thinking I will add some garlic powder next time for just a little kick. Otherwise, it was great and I will definitely make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"myrnie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Very tasty!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kate Lepine\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was a good recipe. I followed some of the other reviewers modifications, 1/2 cup sour cream and caramelized onions. I also add some cooking sherry and it really enhanced the flavors, plus some salt and pepper.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"grilled__cheese\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"5/5 in terms of taste (if you follow the reviews.)\\nMy mom, who normally hates sour cream said it reminded her of tuna noodle casserole, and ate a large plateful. It made enough for 2 people, eating two generous portions each, and it's easy and cheap enough for a weeknight meal.\\n\\nI was out of fresh garlic, and don't normally have fresh parsley or worcestershire sauce, so I subbed garlic powder, dried parsley, and seasoned salt. It was actually very good, even without fresh ingredients. I used 3/4 lb. of button mushrooms, next time I'd use at least a pound. I used 3/4 bag of egg noodles. Next time, I would use the whole bag (there was enough sauce left over for one more medium-small portion.)\\n\\nSauce: I would add less flour next time. This one is because of my technique, I cooked the sauce for a few extra minutes to get rid of the floury taste, and the sauce continued to thicken. I added about 4 scoops of pasta water to thin it (bonus is it helps the sauce stick to the pasta) while it cooked. I whisked the flour in without the sour cream, after adding the veggies back in, thinking it would work, and there were a few lumps I had to scoop out. Next time, I'd add the flour and whisk before adding the veggies back in. I added 1/2 Tablespoon of soy sauce as well, and I think that really made it. I actually thought the sauce was really good without the sour cream, so if you're out of it or with someone who doesn't like it, you could maybe add a pat or two of butter instead. You defini\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Annio\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Hubby said it was very good. Stayed with recipe except for splash of worcheshire. This time I used beef broth because it was all I had.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"meme\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"i added lots of veggies and it was kinda more sour than i thought it would be\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"KosherHottie\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because I had to adjust the recipe but overall it was pretty good. I cut the sour cream to 1/2 cup, only 1 tsp. of flour and several generous shakes of salt, pepper, soy sauce, worcheshire sauce and 3 clove of garlic.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lhay Thriffiley\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Easy, hearty meat-free dish! I used vegetarian bullion paste and a little extra water, and it was delicious.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Justin Metz\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Loved the Recipe. Thought it was delicious as is. Very easy to make. The parsley is totally unnecessary and nearly ruins the dish. Otherwise this is a quick 30 minute dinner and easy to make.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"CKS\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Came out tasty - made the mods discussed below, soy sauce, Worcestershire, beef broth, garlic. I used four large mushrooms and the ratio was just about right. Used about 1 1/2 cups of sour cream (all of one of those small containers). Thickness of the sauce was good, enough to coat the noodles but not runny. I am making this again!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Stephanie Richards\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Based upon Pinkypink's review/modifications, this recipe came out perfect...even for my non-vegetarian family.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Pamela Faught\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Really delicious!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"mainedee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Not sure what we did wrong but it didn't taste like much. We were so looking forward to this stroganoff, will definitely try again and see how to improve it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Allrecipes Member\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Not sure what we did wrong but it didn't taste like much. We were so looking forward to this stroganoff, will definitely try again and see how to improve it\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"bellablue\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"So good! I did add a little lemon and fresh dill. I also deglazed with white wine AND the broth. I will be making this again! Thanks!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Teresa B\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I used plain yogurt (without high fructose) in lieu of sour cream and I cooked the onion in avacado oil in lieu of butter. It was delicious. Very easy to make.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"BEDTIMEBEAR\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I am so disappointed! I wish I'd read the reviews, because everything smelled and tasted *amazing* right up until I added in the sour cream. Then all the lovely flavor of the onions, mushrooms, and broth were gone and I could only taste sour cream. I tried to save it. I added in some Worcestershire sauce and more broth, but I still only tasted sour cream. After doctoring it and doctoring it (more broth, more Worcestershire, a bit of tomato paste, some salt), it's now better, something I can eat a whole bowl of. But I wish I could go back to right before I put in the sour cream, when it was very nearly perfect, and only add 1/2 cup or so of sour cream. I will be trying this one again, but following the reviews instead of the recipe. Sorry.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Designer Davis\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Creamy, yummy, easy, even my husband loved it and he doesn't often rave about my cooking. (I do better at baking, truth be told). I added Gardein Meat Crumbles to the mushroom mixture and that made it extra thick and hearty. Of course I added a tad more sour cream too. Hardly any leftovers.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kaceygee\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I guess I need to tweek this one a little bit. I really missed the ground beef.....\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Rye Collins\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I doubled everything but the sour cream and noodles and added peas and a dash of Worcestershire sauce. Very well received.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kitchenhoney\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"A wonderful idea and is so close to the regular Beef version. Only changes,... I used beef broth (I'm not a vegetarian) instead and a can of \\\"Healthy Recipe\\\" mushroom soup instead of all that sour cream. A single dollop on top was enough sour cream for authenticity.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"kgalardi\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I added a can of cream of mushroom soup and reduced the amount of flour. Delicious! My husband loves it...and he's a picky eater!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Lisa Hicks\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was awesome! My whole family loved it. Made it the way it said in the directions. Will be making this again very soon.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"trynewthings921\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I just made this for dinner and it was absolutely amazing!! As someone who likes to eat vegetarian as much as possible, I really appreciated this recipe. The only change I made was adding a little salt to each plate which really brought out the flavors. Also, don't skip the parsley since it really added a lot!!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MothraMandy\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Used reduced fat cream and sour cream\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"H2O\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made some of the changes suggested. I added 2cloves of chopped garlic and used 1/2 cup of red wine with 1cup of vegetable broth. I also added soy sauce and worsteshire. Cut the sour cream to 1 cup. It was good and I will make it again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bunny\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe is a great alternative to using beef. All it needs is a few cloves of chopped garlic and a little less onion :)\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"miss ugly\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I cut back a tad on the broth and added Sherry, which is what I use when I make it w/beef. Excellent!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Donna\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Doubled this recipe. The family plus guest's loved this and they usually have a meat version so needless to say this was a huge success. So satisfying ??????????\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"orcasislandmastiffs\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This recipe turned out awesome! I read the reviews and added a dash of soy and Worcestershire. Used beef stock. Added zucchini and broccoli and wow, my husband inhaled it. Will make this agin often.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Heather Sunshine Rivera\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"This was very tasty and serves a great purpose. Meatless Mondays! Only one skeptical child, but my older daughter and husband enjoyed it. Next time, I may try adding beer for added flavor. As we are not vegetarian, just looking to consume less meat, I actually used beef broth instead of vegetable broth. Additionally, I was unsure about how it was served and mixed the sauce in with the egg noodles. Big mistake. It still tasted great, but I won't due that again.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Brooke Widdicombe\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I loved this recipe with a couple of tweaks made after I read some reviews and different recipes. I cut the sour cream to one cup and the vege stock/broth to one cup. I also added 2 tsp of minced garlic, 2 tsp of soy sauce, a 2 tsp of paprika and about a half of a 1/4 tsp of cinnamon. Loved it and managed to finish it all myself in 24 hours. Oops.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kelly H.\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I'm a college student, so I tried to make this as easy as possible on me. I replaced the portobellos with baby Bella's, the sour cream with Greek yogurt, but I did take the advice of adding some soy sauce and a bit of red wine to the sauce. WORTH IT!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Bex Atilano\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Added garlic, worshtisire and soy. So good.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Roxann\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Even though I don't eat mushrooms I cook them for my vegetarian grandson. I have to say the end result of cooking this was it smelled very good!! Thanks for all the suggestions as I don't taste these mushroom dishes that I cook the thanks and yumms I got were evidence that this recipe is a def keeper. Cut the sour cream as suggested, used 3 T. flour, soy and Worcestershire sauce with a dash of white wine. Will be making this to take with me to Easter dinner at the daughters house. Thanks for sharing\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Sheryl \"}, \"reviewBody\": \"loved this; wasn't sure what to expect- the flavors were rather complex! I followed the reviews of others who reduced sour cream to half a cur, added half a cup of sherry, one cup of broth, half tspn soy, 4-dashes of Worcester. It took a little time to cook, but I enjoyed every bite!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Staci Tongate Schuster\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I loved this after reading the reviews and making changes. I just wanted to add for any vegetarians... worchestire sauce is not vegetarian unless your lucky enough to live in an area that sells a veggie version.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Mitchell Dorris\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Add white pepper (prefer Chinese style) for the final \\\"it's missin something\\\" touch that sets your Stroganoff..OFF.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"3\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Keith Rice\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I liked this but my wife did not care for it. I used less than half of the recommended sour cream but it still overwhelmed the sauce very much. Use less sour cream and this is a solid recipe.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"RACHHESS\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I have to disagree with the reviewers who say this needs any alterations to be a 5-star recipe. I've made this several times and it is simple and fantastic! The only specific thing I do is to use Better Than Bouillon Mushroom Base as the vegetable broth. My \\\"I hate mushrooms\\\" husband pushes aside the portobello slices but loves the sauce.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"merlion\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"I made this per the recipe except for the vege broth - I used beef broth instead and found it very tasty. You really won't miss the meat. The portobello mushrooms are very \\\"meaty\\\"!\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"momj74\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Soooo delicious, not missing the meat at all. Took a couple of pages from other reviewers and added some soy sauce to the cooking mushrooms, would have added worchestershire sauce too if i had it but the soy sauce alone added a good bit to the meatiness of the dish. Also added a couple of small cloves of garlic, a few pinches of dried thyme, and kept the onions and mushrooms in the pan when i added the veggie broth. Next time I'll make a double batch because this went fast and there were arguments over who got more.\"}, {\"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": {\"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\"}, \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"MiloTheMayor\"}, \"reviewBody\": \"Skeptical at first, but turned out great.\"}], \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\"@type\": [\"WebPage\"], \"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/60923/portobello-mushroom-stroganoff/\", \"breadcrumb\": {\"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [{\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/1116/fruits-and-vegetables/\", \"name\": \"Fruits and Vegetables\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipes/15172/fruits-and-vegetables/mushrooms/\", \"name\": \"Mushrooms\"}}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/60923/portobello-mushroom-stroganoff/\", \"name\": \"Portobello Mushroom Stroganoff\"}}]}}, \"about\": []}"}
